Other optional details include floor, pickup point, postal code, room number, state/province, and residential indicator. The address can be residential or commercial. The object is required to include company name, address line, residential indicator, phone, city, country code, and contact name.

Number.description: Phone number

flattened_text: This object represents a phone number for a pickup address. It includes properties for the phone extension and number. The phone extension can be up to 10 characters long, and the phone number can be up to 25 characters long. The phone number is required.

ServiceCode.description: Refer to Service Codes in the Appendix for valid values.

Quantity.description:
Number of pieces to be picked up. 
Max per service: 999

DestinationCountryCode.description:
The destination country code as defined by ISO-3166.
Refer to Country or Territory Codes in the Appendix for valid values.

ContainerCode.description:
Container type. Valid values:
- 01 = PACKAGE
- 02 = UPS LETTER
- 03 = PALLET

Note: 03 is used for only WWEF services

PickupCreationRequest_PickupPiece.description:
The container providing the information about how many items should be picked up. 
The total number of return and forwarding packages cannot exceed 9,999.

flattened_text: This request is for creating a pickup piece, specifying details like the container type, destination country code, quantity of items to be picked up, and service code. The container code can be PACKAGE, UPS LETTER, or PALLET. The destination country code follows ISO-3166 standards. The quantity of pieces should not exceed 999. The service code indicates the type of service requested. The total number of return and forwarding packages cannot exceed 9,999.

Weight.description:
The weight of the package. 
One decimal digit is allowed. Example: 10.9

UnitOfMeasurement.description:
The code representing the unit of measurement associated with the package.
LBS = Pounds
KGS = Kilograms

PickupCreationRequest_TotalWeight.description: Container for the total weight of all the items.

flattened_text: This object represents the total weight of items in a pickup creation request. It includes the unit of measurement (e.g., LBS for pounds, KGS for kilograms) and the weight of the package (allowing one decimal digit). Both the unit of measurement and weight are required fields.

TrackingNumber.description: Tracking number for return shipment or forward shipment packages.  Tracking number(s) that have been previously used to pay for on-call pickup cannot be used again.

PickupCreationRequest_TrackingData.description:
Container for Return Service and Forward Tracking Numbers.  Accept no more than 30 TrackingData.

TrackingDataWithReferenceNumber and TrackingData container cannot be present at the same time.

flattened_text: This object, `PickupCreationRequest_TrackingData`, is used to store tracking numbers for return or forward shipments. It can hold up to 30 tracking numbers but only one at a time. The `TrackingNumber` property is a string of 18 characters that cannot be reused if previously used for on-call pickup.

ReferenceNumber.description: The reference number associated with the tracking number.

PickupCreationRequest_TrackingDataWithRe.description: Container for Tracking Number with its associated reference numbers.  This container should be populated to provide visibility into shipment tied to pickup being scheduled.  TrackingDataWithReferenceNumber and TrackingData container cannot be present at the same time.

flattened_text: This object is used to provide tracking information for a shipment when scheduling a pickup. It includes a tracking number and associated reference numbers. You can include up to 3 reference numbers, each up to 35 characters long. The tracking number must be 18 characters long. Note that you cannot include both reference numbers and tracking data in the same request.

OriginServiceCenterCode.description: Origin SLIC. This will be obtained from submitting a pickup service center request. See PickupGetFacilitiesServiceCenterRequest.

OriginServiceCountryCode.description: Country or territory of Service Center SLIC chosen to drop off.

PickupCreationRequest_FreightOptions.description: Container will be used to indicate Service options, add optional Original service center, destination address and shipment details related to the UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday.

flattened_text: This object, `PickupCreationRequest_FreightOptions`, is used to specify service options, origin and destination details, and shipment information for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday. It includes properties for destination address, origin service center code, origin service country code, shipment details, and shipment service options. The `ShipmentDetail` property is required.

OriginLiftGateIndicator.description: Presence indicates OriginLiftGateRequiredIndicator is present.  Conditionally requirements. Must not be present if DropOffAtUPSFacilityIndicator is true

DropoffAtUPSFacilityIndicator.description: Identifies service center location information for Origin List of UPS Facilities.

HoldForPickupIndicator.description: Identifies service center location information for Destination of UPS Facilities.

flattened_text: This section defines optional indicators for shipping services. It includes indicators for drop-off at UPS facilities, holding for pickup, and lift gate requirements at the origin. Only one indicator can be used at a time.

City.description: The city of pickup address if available.  It is required for non-postal country Ireland (IE).

StateProvince.description:
1. It means district code for Hong Kong (HK)
2. It means county for Ireland (IE)
3. It means state or province for all the postal countries  It is required for non-postal countries including HK and IE.

PostalCode.description: Postal Code for postal countries.  It does not apply to non-postal countries such as IE and HK

CountryCode.description:
The pickup country or territory code as defined by ISO-3166. 
Refer to Country or Territory Codes in the Appendix for valid values.  Upper-case two-letter string.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for the destination address when setting up freight options. It includes fields for the city, country code, postal code, and state/province. The country code follows ISO-3166 standards. Specific requirements are outlined for postal and non-postal countries like Ireland and Hong Kong. The destination address is required to include the country code.

FreightOptions_ShipmentDetail.description: Refers to the ShipmentDetail Container under Freight Options

flattened_text: This object, FreightOptions_ShipmentDetail, contains information about a shipment, including whether it contains hazardous materials and references to pallet information. It can only have one instance and is represented in XML as ShipmentDetail.
This component defines the details of a shipment pallet, including its dimensions. It allows for specifying only one pallet per shipment.

This section defines the dimensions of the largest pallet. It includes properties for height, length, width, and unit of measurement. The unit of measurement is required. The data type for all dimensions is a string.

Code.description:
- IN = Inches
- CM = Centimeters

Description.description: See Code above.

Dimensions_UnitOfMeasurement.description: The code representing the unit of measurement associated with the package.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for package dimensions. It includes a code (IN for inches, CM for centimeters) and a description. The code must be exactly 2 characters long, and the description can be up to 35 characters. The code is required.

PRN.description: Pickup Request Number generated by UPS pickup system when a successful pickup is scheduled.Same PRN will be returned if a pickup request already exists for a pickup address/ point.

WeekendServiceTerritoryIndicator.description:
Indicates if the pickup address qualifies for WST (Weekend Service Territory). Returned if the pickup date is Saturday and subversion greater or equal to 1607. Valid Values:
- Y = WST
- N = Non-WST

PickupCreationResponse.description: The response for scheduling an on-callpickup.

flattened_text: The `PickupCreationResponse` object is the response for scheduling an on-call pickup. It includes a Pickup Request Number (PRN) generated by UPS when a pickup is successfully scheduled. The response also contains information about the rate result, rate status, response details, weekend service territory, and an indicator for weekend service eligibility. The `Response` and `RateStatus` properties are required.
This response contains information about a pickup creation request. It includes an alert, response status, and transaction reference. The response status is required.

SatWST.description:
Indicates if the pickup address qualifies for WST (Weekend Service Territory). Returned if the pickup date is Saturday and subversion greater or equal to 2007. Valid Values:
- Y = Saturday WST
- N = Non-Saturday WST

SunWST.description: Indicates if the pickup address qualifies for WST (Weekend Service Territory). Returned if the pickup date is Sunday and subversion greater or equal to 2007. Valid Values: - Y = Sunday WST - N = Non-Sunday WST

PickupCreationResponse_WeekendServiceTer.description: WeekendServiceTerritory Container.Returned if the  subversion greater or equal to 2007.

flattened_text: This response indicates if a pickup address qualifies for Weekend Service Territory (WST) based on the pickup date being Saturday or Sunday. It includes properties SatWST and SunWST with values 'Y' for qualifying and 'N' for non-qualifying addresses. The response is returned for subversions equal to or greater than 2007. The properties are required and the response is in an object format named WeekendServiceTerritory.

Code.description:
The rating status.
- 01 = Rate available
- 02 = Rate not available
- 03 = Rate not apply
- 04 = Rate not requested

- If 01 is returned, then OnCallPickupRateResult will also be returned with rate details.
- If 02 is returned, then OnCallPickupRateResult will not be returned.
- If 03 is returned, then OnCallPickupRateResult will not be returned. The rate option is not appliable to this return pickup. The requester will not be charged.
- If 04 is returned, then OnCallPickupRateResult will not be returned. The requester did not ask for rating this on-callpickup.

Description.description: The matching description of rating status code (see above).

flattened_text: This response provides the status of the rating for an on-call pickup request. The "Code" field indicates the rating status with values like "01" for rate available and "02" for rate not available. If "01" is returned, details of the rate will also be provided. The "Description" field gives a brief description of the rating status.

RateType.description:
Indicates this pickup is rated as same-day or future-day pickup.
- SD = Same-day Pickup
- FD = Future-day Pickup

CurrencyCode.description: IATA currency codes for the pickup charge. Such as USD

ChargeDetail.description:
Container to hold taxes when, detailed taxes are request via RateTaxIndicator.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

TaxCharges.description:
Container to hold taxes when, detailed taxes are request via RateTaxIndicator.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

GrandTotalOfAllCharge.description: The grand total of each charge and applied tax.

GrandTotalOfAllIncentedCharge.description: The grand total of each incented charge and applied tax. Only present if 1. UserLevelDiscountIndicator = Y and User Level Promotion is applied to the pickup or 2 .if any incentive rate is applied to the pickup and SubVersion on the request is greater than or equal to 1707.

PreTaxTotalCharge.description: Total of charges before taxes. Only present when tax details requested in input.

PreTaxTotalIncentedCharge.description: Total of incented charges before taxes. Only present if 1. UserLevelDiscountIndicator = Y and User Level Promotion is applied to the pickup or 2 .if any incentive rate is applied to the pickup and SubVersion on the request is greater than or equal to 1707.

PickupCreationResponse_RateResult.description: The result of rating on-callpickup. It correlates to rate status code 01

flattened_text: This response provides the result of rating an on-call pickup. It includes details such as charges, currency code, total charges before taxes, tax details, and the type of pickup (same-day or future-day). The response also contains information on taxes and disclaimers related to the pickup. The key properties include GrandTotalOfAllCharge, CurrencyCode, PreTaxTotalCharge, RateType, TaxCharges, and TotalTax.

Code.description:
Disclaimer code. Valid values:
- 01 = Taxes are included in the shipping cost and apply to the transportation charges but additional duties/taxes may apply and are not reflected in the total amount due.
- 02 = Additional duties/taxes may apply and are not reflected in the total amount due.
- 03 = Additional duties/taxes may apply and are not reflected in the total amount due.
- 04 = Taxes were unable to be determined and may apply to the shipment.
- 05 = Rate excludes VAT. Rate includes a fuel surcharge, but excludes taxes, duties and other charges that may apply to the shipment.

Description.description: Description of Disclaimer.

RateResult_Disclaimer.description: Container to hold Disclaimer message applicable to taxes and charges. Available only when tax information is requested.

flattened_text: The RateResult_Disclaimer object contains a disclaimer message related to taxes and charges. It is provided when tax information is requested. It includes a disclaimer code with valid values ranging from 01 to 05, each indicating different tax scenarios. The object also includes a description of the disclaimer. The disclaimer code is a string with a maximum length of 2 characters, while the description has a maximum length of 512 characters. The object requires both a description and a code.

This component, `PICKUPPolDivRequestWrapper`, is an object that contains a single property, `PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListRequest`, which refers to another schema. The `PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListRequest` property is required and represents a request for political division information.

This component, `PICKUPPolDivResponseWrapper`, is an object that contains the `PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListResponse` property. The `PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListResponse` property is required and refers to another schema.

CountryCode.description: Specifies the country for which the list of Political Division 1 will be returned if available.

PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListRequest.description: This request is for client to get a list of valid Political Division 1s/State field for a specific country or territory

flattened_text: This request allows clients to retrieve a list of valid State fields for a specific country or territory. The request includes the CountryCode parameter to specify the country for which the list will be returned. The request must include the Request and CountryCode parameters.
This element is used in all services to request a list of political divisions. It includes a Transaction Reference property and is limited to one instance.

PickupGetPoliticalDivision1ListResponse.description: The response for getting a list of valid Political Division 1 or State field in the specified country or territory.

flattened_text: This response provides a list of valid Political Division 1 (State) fields in a specified country or territory. It includes the Political Division 1 field as an array of strings with a length between 1 and 50 characters. The response is required and structured as an object with a reference to a specific schema.
This response contains information about political divisions for a pickup request. It includes an alert, response status, and transaction reference. The response status is required.

This object, `PICKUPServCenterRequestWrapper`, contains a single property, `PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesRequest`, which references another schema. The property is required and the object is of type `object`. The XML element name for this object is `PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesRequest`.

This response wrapper contains information about a pickup service center. It includes details about the facilities available at the service center. The response is in XML format and must include the PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesResponse property.

Locale.description:
Origin Country or Territory Locale.  Locale should be Origin Country. Example: en_US. 
The Last 50 instruction will be send based on this locale. Locale is required if PoximityIndicator is present for Drop Off facilities.

ProximitySearchIndicator.description: Proximity Indicator. Indicates the user requested the proximity search for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday locations for the origin address and/or the airport code, and the sort code for destination address.

PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesRequest.description: This request is to retrieve UPS Facility location information including location address, phone number, SLIC, and hours of operation for pick-up and drop-off requests

flattened_text: This request is used to get information about UPS facility locations for pick-up and drop-off services. It includes details like address, phone number, SLIC, and hours of operation. The request must include the destination address, origin address, pickup pieces, and other specific details. The request also requires the origin country locale and a proximity search indicator for certain facilities.
This object represents a request to retrieve service center facilities for pickup. It contains a Transaction Reference property. The request can only include one instance of this object.

ServiceCode.description:
The service code.
96 = WWEF  Required for WWEF shipments.

ContainerCode.description:
The container type
03 = PALLET  Required for WWEF shipments.

flattened_text: This request is for getting information about a pickup piece container. It includes properties for the container code and service code, with specific requirements for each. The service code must be 3 characters long and the container code must be 2 characters long. The service code is required for WWEF shipments.

StreetAddress.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search.  Conditionally required if proximitySearchIndicator is present.

City.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search  Conditionally required if proximitySearchIndicator is present.

StateProvince.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search.  Conditionally required if proximitySearchIndicator is present and if country or territory is US/CA/IE/HK.

PostalCode.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search  Conditionally required if proximitySearchIndicator is present and if country or territory has postal code.It does not apply to non-postal countries such as IE and HK.

CountryCode.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search

PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesRequest_.description: Indicates the address of the shipper to allow for the nearest Drop off facility Search.  Conditionally required for drop off location search.

flattened_text: This request is used to specify the shipper's address for finding the nearest drop-off facility. It includes details like city, country code, postal code, state/province, and street address. Some fields are conditionally required based on certain criteria. The `CountryCode` field is mandatory.

SearchRadius.description:
Search Request range. Valied values:
- 1 to 200

Default: 200

DistanceUnitOfMeasure.description: Unit of Measure  Required if ProximitySearchIndicator is present. Example: MI or KM

MaximumLocation.description:
Maximum Number of locations. Valied values:
- 1 to 100

Default: 100

OriginAddress_OriginSearchCriteria.description: Origin Search Criteria Container  Required if Proximity SearchIndicator is present.

flattened_text: This section defines criteria for searching for origin addresses. It includes the unit of measure (e.g., MI or KM), the maximum number of locations (1 to 100, default 100), and the search radius range (1 to 200, default 200). The criteria are required when using proximity search.

City.description: Indicates the address of the consignee to allow for the nearest Pickup facility Search.  Required for non-postal country Ireland (IE).

StateProvince.description:
Indicates the address of the consignee to allow for the nearest Pickup facility Search.
1 = District code for Hong Kong (HK)
2 = County for Ireland (IE)
3 = State or province for all the postal countries  Required for non-postal countries including HK and IE.

PostalCode.description: Indicates the address of the consignee to allow for the nearest Pickup facility Search  It does not apply to non-postal countries. Example: IE and HK.

CountryCode.description: The pickup country or territory code as defined by ISO-3166. Please check check separate pickup country or territory list to find out all the pickup eligible countries.

PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesRequest_.description: DestinationAddress container.  Conditionally required for pickup location search.

flattened_text: This request is for getting pickup service center facilities based on a destination address. The address includes city, country code, postal code, and state/province. The country code follows ISO-3166 standards. The address details are used to find the nearest pickup facility. The country code is required, and specific requirements apply for non-postal countries like Ireland and Hong Kong.

PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesResponse.description: Returns service center location information for Origin UPS Facilities and Destination Facilities

flattened_text: This response provides information about service center locations for both the origin UPS facilities and destination facilities. It includes details about the response and the service center location. The response must include both the response and service center location properties.
This response container includes an alert, response status, and transaction reference. The response status is required.

PickupGetServiceCenterFacilitiesResponse.description: Locations of the nearest Service Center for Dropoff and Pickup

flattened_text: This response provides the location of the nearest service center for drop-off and pickup. It includes information about drop-off facilities and a reference to pickup facilities. The response is limited to one service center location.

SLIC.description: SLIC code for the UPS Drop off facility.

Type.description: FRT for Freight or PKG for Package

Timezone.description:
Facility's Timezone. Format:
- America/New_York
- Asia/Hong_Kong
- Europe/London

Phone.description: Phone Number of the Drop off Facility

ServiceCenterLocation_DropOffFacilities.description: Returns information for DropOff Facilities. This includes name of facility, address, business hours, and SLIC.

flattened_text: This API endpoint provides information about UPS drop-off facilities, including their name, address, business hours, and SLIC code. It also includes details like fax number, phone number, and facility type. The endpoint requires information such as timezone, facility type, address, SLIC code, phone number, and more.

AddressLine.description: Address Line of the Facility.

PostalCode.description: Facility Postal Code.

CountryCode.description: UPS Drop Off facility country or territory code.

ResidentialIndicator.description:
Indicates if the pickup address is a residential place or not. 
Valid Values:
Y = Residential address
N = Non-residential (Commercial) address (default)

flattened_text: This data structure defines the address of a drop-off facility for UPS packages. It includes fields for the address line, city, country code, postal code, residential indicator, and state/province. The address line can have up to 3 lines. The city, country code, postal code, residential indicator, and state/province have specific length and format requirements. The address line, state/province, residential indicator, postal code, city, and country code are all required fields.

This defines a data structure for a facility's operating hours. It includes the day of the week when the facility is open. The maximum number of entries is limited to one. The required field is the day of the week. The XML element name for this structure is "FacilityTime."

EarliestDropOfforPickup.description: Earliest time that a customer can drop-off a package.

LatestDropOfforPickup.description: Latest time that a customer can drop-off a package.

OpenHours.description:
Facility Open Hours. The latest local open time. Format: HHmm
- Hour: 0-23
- Minute: 0-59

CloseHours.description:
Facility Close Hours. The latest local close time. Format: HHmm
- Hour: 0-23
- Minute: 0-59

PrepTime.description: Time required by the facility to prepare your shipment for movement

LastDrop.description: Cut-off time for drop off that day.

flattened_text: This data structure represents the hours of operation for a facility on different days of the week. It includes details such as the day of the week, earliest and latest drop-off times for packages, cut-off times, open and close hours, and preparation time. The structure is designed to store this information for each day of the week.

Last50ftInstruction.description:
Last 50ft instructions that relates to an available facility and depend on the locale passing in request.
Last 50 feet instruction in the language asked in request or the English for that country.

DropOffFacilities_LocalizedInstruction.description: Localized Instruction Container.  Localized Instructions will be returned for drop off location search by proximity order.

flattened_text: This component, "DropOffFacilities_LocalizedInstruction," contains localized instructions for drop-off locations based on proximity. It includes the last 50 feet instructions specific to the requested language or English for that country, and the locale (e.g., en_US). The maximum length for the instructions is 750 characters.

Value.description:
Distance from origin address. Distance based on distance UOM in request.

Numeric value up to 200 and .2 decimal positions. Distance will be retuned for drop off location search by proximity order.

UnitOfMeasurement.description:
Unit Of Measure.
Example: MI or KM

DropOffFacilities_Distance.description: Distance from origin  Distance will be retuned for drop off location search by proximity order.

flattened_text: This data structure defines the distance from the origin to a drop-off location. It includes the unit of measurement (e.g., MI or KM) and the numeric distance value up to 200 with 2 decimal positions. The distance is returned for drop-off location search by proximity order.

SLIC.description: SLIC code for the UPS Pickup facility

Timezone.description:
Facility's Timezone. Format:
- America/New_York
- Asia/Hong_Kong
- Europe/London

Phone.description: Phone Number of the Pickup Facility

AirportCode.description:
AirPort Code for destination/pickup facility. 
Example: ATL (Atlanta)
If Airport code is not present "---" will be returned.

SortCode.description:
Sort Code for destination/pickup facility. 
Example: V1

ServiceCenterLocation_PickupFacilities.description: Returns information for Pickup Facilities. This includes name of facility, address, and business hours.

flattened_text: This API endpoint provides information about Pickup Facilities, including their name, address, and business hours. It returns details such as the facility's name, address, phone number, fax number, SLIC code, and timezone. The data includes the airport code, facility time, sort code, and type of service (freight or package). The response is in XML format and requires specific fields like timezone, type, address, SLIC, phone, fax, and name.

AddressLine.description: Address Line of the Facility.

PostalCode.description: Facility Postal Code.

CountryCode.description: UPS Pickup facility country or territory code.

ResidentialIndicator.description:
Indicates if the pickup location is commerical or residential.
Valid values:
Y = Residential address
N = Non-residential (Commercial) address (default)

flattened_text: This object defines the address details of a pickup facility for UPS. It includes AddressLine, City, CountryCode, PostalCode, ResidentialIndicator, and StateProvince. The required fields are AddressLine, StateProvince, ResidentialIndicator, PostalCode, City, and CountryCode. The ResidentialIndicator specifies if the pickup location is residential or commercial.

This object represents a container for facility time information related to pickup facilities. It includes a property for the day of the week. The day of the week is required and must be provided as an array. The XML element name for this object is "FacilityTime."

EarliestDropOfforPickup.description: Earliest time that a customer can pick up a package.

LatestDropOfforPickup.description: Latest time that a customer can pick up a package.

OpenHours.description:
Facility Open Hours. The latest local open time. Format: HHmm
- Hour: 0-23
- Minute: 0-59

CloseHours.description:
Facility Close Hours. The latest local close time. Format: HHmm
- Hour: 0-23
- Minute: 0-59

PrepTime.description: Preparation time for hold for pickup  Conditionally required if request is for hold for pickup.

LastDrop.description: Latest time a package, requiring preparation can be dropped off (Close time - Prep time).

flattened_text: This object represents the facility hours of operation for a pickup location. It includes details such as the day of the week, earliest and latest pickup times, facility open and close hours, and preparation time for hold for pickup requests. The properties include CloseHours, Day, EarliestDropOfforPickup, LastDrop, LatestDropOfforPickup, OpenHours, and PrepTime. The required fields are OpenHours, Day, and CloseHours.

This component, `PICKUPPendingRequestWrapper`, is an object that wraps a `PickupPendingStatusRequest`. It can only contain one instance of the `PickupPendingStatusRequest` object. The `PickupPendingStatusRequest` property is required.

This component defines a response wrapper for a pending pickup status. It includes a single property, "PickupPendingStatusResponse," which references the schema for the pickup status response. The property is required and the response is in XML format.

PickupType.description:
Specify the type of pending pickup.
01 = On-Call Pickup

AccountNumber.description: The specific account number belongs to the shipper

PickupPendingStatusRequest.description: This request is used to get the pending pickup status.

flattened_text: The `PickupPendingStatusRequest` is a request used to check the status of a pending pickup. It includes the shipper's account number, pickup type (such as on-call pickup), and additional request details. The account number must be between 6 and 10 characters long. The request is required and must include the pickup type and account number.

This element is used in all services and is limited to one instance. It contains a property called TransactionReference, which refers to another schema. The element is of type object and is represented in XML as "Request."

PickupPendingStatusResponse.description: The response of the pending status for on-callpickup.

flattened_text: This response object, `PickupPendingStatusResponse`, provides information about the pending status for an on-call pickup. It includes the `PendingStatus` and `Response` properties. The `PendingStatus` can be an array of items or a single item, while `Response` is a reference to another schema. Both `PendingStatus` and `Response` are required properties in this object.
This response contains information about a pending pickup status. It includes an alert, response status, and transaction reference. The response status is required.

PickupType.description:
Specify the type of pending pickup.
- 01 = on-callPickup

ServiceDate.description:
Local service date. Format: yyyyMMdd
- yyyy = Year applicable
- MM = 01-12
- dd = 01-31

OnCallStatusCode.description: A unique string identifier to identify a success pre-notification processing. Only available if end result is success.

PickupStatusMessage.description:
The status for on-callpickup.

PickupPendingStatusResponse will only display incomplete status for today and tomorrow only.
- 002 and 012 are the most common responses.
- 001 = Received at dispatch
- 002 = Dispatched to driver
- 003 = Order successfully completed
- 004 = Order unsuccessfully completed
- 005 = Missed commit – Updated ETA supplied by driver
- 007 = Cancelled
- 008 = Order has invalid order status
- 012 = Your pickup request is being processed

BillingCode.description:
Pickup billing classification for on call
- 01 = Regular
- 02 = Return
- 03 = Alternate Address (Not supported for now)

ReferenceNumber.description: Customer provided reference number for on-call pickup

PickupPendingStatusResponse_PendingStatu.description: The result of retrieving pending pickups.

flattened_text: This response provides information about pending pickups. It includes details such as pickup billing classification, contact name, status codes, PRN, pickup status message, pickup type, reference number, and service date. The response is in the form of an object and requires specific fields like service date, pickup type, PRN, and pickup status message.
This defines an "ErrorResponse" object that includes a "response" property referring to a common error response schema.

CommonErrorResponse.description: The error response containing any errors that occurred.

errors.description: The error array containing any errors that occurred.

flattened_text: This defines a common error response structure that includes an array of error messages. Each error message is defined in a separate schema called "ErrorMessage."

ErrorMessage.description: The error response containing any errors that occurred.

flattened_text: This defines an "ErrorMessage" object that includes an error code and message for any errors that occur in the response.

info.title: Quantum View
info.description:
UPS Quantum View is a suite of services that gives you and your customers details regarding UPS shipments. # Reference - Business Rules - Appendix - Errors - FAQ

Try out UPS APIs with example requests using Postman. Explore API documentation and sample applications through GitHub.

flattened_text: The Quantum View API by UPS provides detailed shipment information for UPS packages. You can access UPS Quantum View services to get shipment details for you and your customers. The API documentation includes information on business rules, an appendix, error handling, and frequently asked questions. You can try out UPS APIs using Postman with example requests and explore API documentation and sample applications on GitHub.
This OpenAPI specification defines two server URLs: one for the Customer Integration Environment at https://wwwcie.ups.com/api and one for Production at https://onlinetools.ups.com/api.

post.description: Get Quantum View Response

parameters.name: version
parameters.description:
Version of API.

Valid values:
- v3

requestBody.description: Generate sample code for popular API requests by selecting an example below. To view a full sample request and response, first click "Authorize" and enter your application credentials, then populate the required parameters above and click "Try it out".

flattened_text: This endpoint allows you to retrieve Quantum View responses by sending a POST request. You need to specify the API version (currently only v3 is supported) in the path. The request body should contain a sample JSON request for popular API actions. After authorizing with your credentials, you can test the request. The responses include successful operation, invalid request, unauthorized request, blocked merchant, and rate limit exceeded. Security is managed through OAuth2.

Valid values:

flattened_text: This endpoint is used to retrieve Quantum View responses, but it is marked as deprecated. It allows users to generate sample code for popular API requests by selecting an example. The request body includes a sample JSON request and users can view full sample requests and responses by authorizing with their application credentials. The endpoint supports various responses such as successful operation, invalid request, unauthorized request, blocked merchant, and rate limit exceeded. It requires OAuth2 security.

OAuth2.description:
Find your Client ID and Secret on your app info page.
1. Select \"Try It\"
2. In the Security section enter your Client ID and Secret.
3. Select \"Request Token\"
4. Enter any additional information in the Body and Parameters sections.
5. Select \"Send\" to execute your API request

flattened_text:
To use OAuth2 for authentication, find your Client ID and Secret on your app info page. Follow these steps:

1. Select "Try It".
2. Enter your Client ID and Secret in the Security section.
3. Select "Request Token".
4. Add any extra information in the Body and Parameters sections.
5. Click "Send" to run your API request.
This API endpoint allows you to wrap a Quantum View request in a single object. The request must include the specified Quantum View request schema.

This component is a wrapper for a Quantum View response. It contains one property, QuantumViewResponse, which refers to the detailed Quantum View response schema. The QuantumViewResponse property is required and the wrapper is represented as an object in XML with the name QuantumViewResponse.

Bookmark.description:
Bookmarks the file for next retrieval. It is a base64Encoded String. 
It contains the combination of SubscriberID + SubscriptionName + File Name if the request is for all data. 
It contains SubscriberID  if the request is for unread data. When a response comes back with a bookmark it indicates that there is more data. To fetch the remaining data, the requester should come back with the bookmark added to the original request.

flattened_text: The `QuantumViewRequest` object is a container for request information in the QuantumView API. It includes a `Bookmark` property for bookmarking files for future retrieval. The `Request` property specifies the request details, and the `SubscriptionRequest` property contains an array of subscription requests. The `Bookmark` property is optional, while the `Request` property is required.

RequestAction.description: Indicates the action to be taken by the XML service. The only valid value is  'QVEvents'

flattened_text: This component, QuantumViewRequest_Request, contains criteria for a QuantumView request. It includes RequestAction, which specifies the action as 'QVEvents', and TransactionReference. RequestAction is required and must be 'QVEvents'.

CustomerContext.description: The CustomerContext Information which will be echoed during response.

Request_TransactionReference.description: TransactionReference identifies transactions between client and server.

flattened_text: This object, Request_TransactionReference, is used to identify transactions between a client and server. It includes a property called CustomerContext, which holds information echoed in the response. The CustomerContext can be up to 512 characters long.

Name.description: Name of subscription requested by user, as one type of request criteria. Required when the customer wants to request data for a specific subscription name. Subscription name consists of up to 21 alphanumerics.

FileName.description: File name of specific subscription requested by user. Format: YYMMDD_HHmmssnnn. (nnn - sequence number: usually = 001)

QuantumViewRequest_SubscriptionRequest.description: Subscription requested by user to retrieve Inbound or/and Outbound XML formed subscription information.

flattened_text: This object represents a user's request for a subscription to retrieve Inbound or Outbound XML-formed subscription information. It includes properties such as DateTimeRange for specifying time range, FileName for the specific file name format, and Name for the subscription name criteria. The subscription name can be up to 21 alphanumeric characters.

BeginDateTime.description: Beginning date time for the retrieval criteria of the subscriptions. It is required for date time request criteria. Format: YYYYMMDDHHmmss.

EndDateTime.description: Ending date time for the retrieval criteria of the subscriptions. Format: YYYYMMDDHHmmss.  When a null or empty EndDateTime is passed in the request, it is defaulted to 7 days from the given begin date.

SubscriptionRequest_DateTimeRange.description: The range of date time of subscription requested by user, as one type of request criteria, valid up to but not exceeding 7 days into the past, starting from current day.

flattened_text: This object defines the date and time range for a subscription request. Users can specify a start date and time (BeginDateTime) and an end date and time (EndDateTime) for retrieving subscriptions. The range is limited to 7 days in the past starting from the current day. If EndDateTime is not provided, it defaults to 7 days from the BeginDateTime.

Bookmark.description: Bookmarks the file for next retrieval, It is a base64Encoded String. It contains the combination of SubscriberID + SubscriptionName + File Name if the request is for all data. It contains SubscriberID if the request is for unread data. When a response comes back with a bookmark it indicates that there is more data. To fetch the remaining data, the requester should come back with the bookmark added to the original request.

flattened_text: The `QuantumViewResponse` object is a container for QuantumView response information. It includes a `Bookmark` property that can be used to bookmark the file for future retrieval. The `QuantumViewEvents` property references detailed event information, while the `Response` property references the response data. The `Response` and `QuantumViewEvents` properties are required.

ResponseStatusCode.description:
Identifies the success or failure of the interchange. 
1 = Success, 0 = Failure

Error.description:
If an error is encountered during the interchange, the Response contains an error. If the error is present, then the ErrorSeverity and ErrorCodes are required.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

QuantumViewResponse_Response.description: Contains Errors information tags along with the success/fail status of the QuantumView request.

flattened_text: The QuantumViewResponse_Response object contains information about errors and the success or failure status of a QuantumView request. It includes properties such as Error, ResponseStatusCode, ResponseStatusDescription, and TransactionReference. The Error property indicates any encountered errors, while ResponseStatusCode shows if the request was successful (1) or failed (0). The object is required to have TransactionReference and ResponseStatusCode properties.

CustomerContext.description: The CustomerContext Information which will be echoed during response.

Response_TransactionReference.description: Container for customer provided data and the XPCI Version.

flattened_text: This response object, "Response_TransactionReference," contains customer-provided data and the XPCI Version. It includes CustomerContext information, the current ToolVersion (1.0), and the XPCI version (1.0007). The object is limited to one instance and is represented in XML as "TransactionReference."

ErrorSeverity.description: Describes the severity of the error. Required if the error is present.

ErrorCode.description: A numeric value that describes the error. Each tool defines a range of error codes. Required if the error is present.

MinimumRetrySeconds.description: Number of seconds to wait until retry. This field is populated on special conditions of the Transient Error only, as defined by the service. A number between 1 and 86400 (24 hours)

ErrorLocation.description:
Identifies the element in error.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ErrorDigest.description:
The contents of the element in error.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This response object, "Response_Error," is used to convey error information. It includes properties such as ErrorCode (numeric value describing the error), ErrorDescription (description of the error code), ErrorDigest (contents of the element in error), ErrorLocation (identifies the element in error), ErrorSeverity (severity of the error), and MinimumRetrySeconds (number of seconds to wait for retry). The ErrorLocation property is required, and the ErrorDigest and ErrorLocation properties are returned as arrays for certain versions.

ErrorLocationElementName.description: The Xpath name of the element in error. This is a valid Xpath pointing to an element in the request document.

ErrorLocationAttributeName.description: The name of the attribute in error. This is the name of the attribute contained by the Error Location element.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure of an error location object, which contains information about the attribute and Xpath element causing an error. The object includes properties for the attribute name and Xpath element name, with specific character length constraints. The object is named "ErrorLocation" and is used to identify the location of errors in a request document.

Error_ErrorDigest.description: The contents of the element in error.

flattened_text: This field contains the details of the error in a string format.

SubscriberID.description: QV XOLT subscribers ID. It is the same as the User ID.

SubscriptionEvents.description:
The event that a user receives a subset of Tracking information specific to either packages coming or packages going, after subscription request is made.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

QuantumViewResponse_QuantumViewEvents.description: The event that a user receives echoing Subscriber ID and information for subscription event, which is a subset of Tracking information specific to either packages coming or packages going, after subscription request is made, if the user requests for XML format.

flattened_text: This object represents the response a user receives after subscribing to Quantum View events in XML format. It includes the Subscriber ID (same as User ID) and a subset of tracking information for packages coming or going. The SubscriptionEvents field contains this tracking information and is returned as an array for versions >= v2, and as a single object for version = v1.

Name.description: A name uniquely defined associated to the Subscription ID, for each subscription. Required if the SubscriptionEvents container is present.

Number.description: A number uniquely defined associated to the Subscriber ID, for each subscription. Required if the SubscriptionEvents container is present.

SubscriptionFile.description:
Container holds all of the unread files associated with the subscription.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This API defines the structure of subscription events in Quantum View. Each event includes a date range, a unique name linked to the subscription ID, a unique number linked to the subscriber ID, a list of unread files associated with the subscription, and the subscription status. The subscription status is required. The SubscriptionFile element is returned as an array for versions >= v2 and as a single object for version = v1 if there is only one file.

Code.description:
Status types of subscription. Valid values:
- UN – Unknown
- AT – Activate
- P – Pending
- A –Active
- I – Inactive
- S - Suspended

Description.description:
Description of a subscription. 
Valid values: 
- Unknown (Unknown subscription status)
- Activate (Ready for the user to activate the subscription)
- Pending (In the process of waiting for privilege requests authorization)
- Active (The subscription is in good standing and is active.)
- Inactive (The subscriber puts the subscription on hold.)
- Suspended (UPS disables the subscription.)

SubscriptionEvents_SubscriptionStatus.description: Container for whether the subscription is active or not.

flattened_text: This object, `SubscriptionEvents_SubscriptionStatus`, holds information about the status of a subscription. It includes properties for `Code` and `Description`, which describe different states of the subscription such as active, pending, or inactive. The `Code` property contains short status codes, while the `Description` property provides more detailed explanations. The object is required to have a `Code` property and is represented in XML as `SubscriptionStatus`.

BeginDate.description:
Beginning date time of subscription requested by user.
Format: MM-DD-YYYY-HH-MM

EndDate.description:
Ending date time of subscription requested by user.
Format: MM-DD-YYYY-HH-MM

SubscriptionEvents_DateRange.description: The range of date time of subscription requested by user, as one type of request criteria, valid up to but not exceeding 7 days into the past, starting from current day.

flattened_text: This object, SubscriptionEvents_DateRange, defines the date range for subscription requests. Users can specify a date range up to 7 days in the past starting from the current day. It includes BeginDate and EndDate properties in MM-DD-YYYY-HH-MM format. The object is required to have a BeginDate and can have an optional EndDate.

FileName.description:
File name belonging to specific subscription requested by user.
Format: YYMMDD_HHmmssnnn

Manifest.description:
Container represents all data that is relevant for the shipment, such as origin, destination, shipper, payment method etc. It will be returned when available.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Origin.description:
Information about shipment's origin.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Exception.description:
Shipment exception data.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Delivery.description:
Container for delivery information.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Generic.description:
Container for generic record information.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This API defines a data structure for subscription events related to file deliveries. It includes information about delivery, exceptions, file name, generic record details, manifest data, shipment origin, and status type. The file name follows a specific format. The elements are returned as arrays for newer versions and as single objects for older versions. The structure is required to have a status type and file name.

Code.description:
Status types of subscription file. Valid values:
- R – Read
- U - Unread

Description.description: Description of a subscription file.

SubscriptionFile_StatusType.description: Container that displays whether the file is read or unread.

flattened_text: This object defines the status of a subscription file, indicating whether it has been read or is still unread. It includes properties for the status code (R for read, U for unread) and a description of the file. The status code is a single character, and the description is limited to 6 characters. Both the description and code properties are required.

ReferenceNumber.description:
Shipment-level reference numbers.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

PickupDate.description: Should be set equal to the date on while the packages were picked up (may be prior days date if the transmission occurs after midnight). Formatted as YYYYMMDD.

ScheduledDeliveryDate.description: The date the shipment originally was scheduled for delivery. Formatted as YYYYMMDD.

ScheduledDeliveryTime.description: Schedule delivery time. Time format is HHMMSS

DocumentsOnly.description:
If the tag is present then the shipment is a document, otherwise the shipment is a non-document. Valid values:
- 1 = Letter
- 2 = Document (Non-Letter Document)
- 3 = Non-Document
- 4 = Pallet

Package.description:
Defines a package.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ManufactureCountry.description: Country or Territory  of Manufacture of the contents of the package.

ShipmentChargeType.description:
Shipment charge type.
Valid values:
C/F - Cost and Freight
C/B - Consignee Billed Package
F/C - Freight Collect
DDP - Delivered Duty Paid
VAT Unpaid
FOB - Free On Board
P/P - Prepaid
F/D - Free Domicile
T/P - Third Party Billing

ConsigneeBillIndicator.description: Indicates if consignee will be billed the shipment.

CollectBillIndicator.description: Indicates whether or not to collect bill at time of delivery.

LocationAssured.description: Indicates Location Assured Values: Y - Location Assured accessorial requested

ImportControl.description: Import Control Indication is used to designate that the shipment is an Import Control shipment. If the shipment is an import control shipment then this element will have value. For no import shipment this will not be appear

LabelDeliveryMethod.description: Indicates Label Delivery Method, Values are: LDE Electronic Label. LDO One Attempt. LDP Print Label. LDT Three Attempt. LPM Print and Mail Label.

CommercialInvoiceRemoval.description: Commercial Invoice Removal (CIR) is an accessorial or indication that will allow a shipper to dictate that UPS remove the Commercial Invoice from the user's shipment before the shipment is delivered to the ultimate consignee. If shipment is CIR then this element will have value. For no CIR this element will not be appear

PostalServiceTrackingID.description: Postal Service Tracking ID transport company tracking number.

ReturnsFlexibleAccess.description: (RFA) UPS returns flexible access. This element will appear with value only when returns flexible access uploaded. For no returns flexible access this element will not be appear

UPScarbonneutral.description: UPS carbon neutral is a term used to reflect a generic term for the tagging to be included on any document, label, e-mail, etc. used to identify that the UPS carbon neutral fee is applied. This element will appear only when shipment is UPS carbon neutral with value. For non UPS carbon neutral shipping this element appear.

Product.description: This element will have value "PAC" for CAR shipments. For no CAR shipments this element will not be appeared.

UPSReturnsExchange.description: UPS Return and Exchange – This element will appear with value Y only when UPS Return and Exchange was requested. For no UPS Returns and Exchange then this element will not appear

LiftGateOnDelivery.description: Lift Gate On Delivery - This element will appear only when Lift Gate For Delivery was requested for UPS World Wide Express Freight Shipments. If no Lift Gate for Delivery was requested, this element will not appear.

LiftGateOnPickUp.description: Lift Gate On PickUp - This element will appear only when Lift Gate For PickUp was requested for UPS World Wide Express Freight Shipments. If no Lift Gate for PickUp was requested, this element will not appear.

PickupPreference.description: Pickup Preference -This element will appear only when Dropoff At UPS Facility was requested for UPS World Wide Express Freight Shipments. If no Dropoff At UPS Facility was requested, this element will not appear.

DeliveryPreference.description: Delivery Preference - This element will appear only when Hold for pick up was requested for UPS World Wide Express Freight Shipments. If no Hold for pick up was requested, this element will not appear.

HoldForPickupAtUPSAccessPoint.description: "Y" Indicates Shipment is Direct to Retail.

DeliverToAddresseeOnlyIndicator.description: "Y" Indicates Shipment is Deliver to Addressee.

UPSAccessPointCODIndicator.description: "Y" Indicates Shipment is Cash on Delivery in Direct to Retail

ClinicalTrialIndicator.description: An accessorial Indicator flag: Y = Clinical Trial accessorial provided in Manifest. Spaces = Clinical Trial accessorial not provided in Manifest.

ClinicalTrialIndicationNumber.description: An unique Clinical Trial associated with the shipment provided in Manifest.

CategoryAHazardousIndicator.description: An accessorial Indicator flag: Y = Category A Hazardous materials accessorial provided in Manifest. Spaces = Category A Hazardous materials accessorial not provided in Manifest.

DirectDeliveryIndicator.description: An accessorial Indicator flag: Y = Direct Delivery accessorisal provided in Manifest. Spaces = Direct Delivery accessorial not provided in Manifest.

ProactiveResponseIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that a UPS Proactive Response Accessorial is provided.

WhiteGloveDeliveryIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that a Heavy Goods White Glove Delivery Accessorial is provided.

RoomOfChoiceIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that a Heavy Goods Room of Choice Accessorial is provided.

InstallationDeliveryIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that a Heavy Goods Installation Delivery Accessorial is provided.

ItemDisposalIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that a Heavy Goods Item Disposal Accessorial is provided.

UPSPremierAccessorialIndicator.description: "Y" indicates that the UPS Premier accessorial is provided.

UPSPremierCategoryCode.description:
Indicates the UPS Premier category applied to the package Valid values:
- 'PRS' – UPS Premier Silver
- 'PRG' – UPS Premier Gold
- 'PRP' - UPS Premier Platinum

flattened_text:
The `SubscriptionFile_Manifest` object defines various properties related to a shipment manifest. It includes details like billing information, hazardous material indicators, clinical trial information, delivery preferences, package details, and special instructions. 

Key properties include `Shipper`, `ConsigneeBillIndicator`, `ShipTo`, and `CollectBillIndicator`. These properties are required for the object. The object is represented as an XML element named `Manifest`.

PhoneNumber.description: Shipper's Phone Number. US Phone numbers must be 10 digits. No formatting is allowed. Required if origin and destination countries or territories are different.

FaxNumber.description: Shipper's Fax Number. US Fax numbers must be 10 digits. No formatting is allowed. Required if origin and destination countries or territories are different.

ShipperNumber.description: Shipper's six digit alphanumeric account number.

flattened_text: This section defines the Shipper's record for a shipment. It includes details such as the Shipper's company name, contact information (email, phone, fax), and tax identification number. The Shipper's attention name and a six-digit alphanumeric account number are also captured. The Shipper's Fax Number and Phone Number are required if the origin and destination countries or territories are different.

AddressLine2.description: Address Line 2 of the Shipper. Usually room/floor information.

AddressLine3.description: Address Line 3 of the shipper. Usually department information.

StateProvinceCode.description: Shipper's state or province code. Must be valid US state. If the Shipper's country or territory is US or CA a two character code is required, otherwise the StateProvinceCode is optional.

PostalCode.description: Shipper's postal code. If the address is US then 5 or 9 digits are required. CA addresses must provide a 6 character postal code that has the format of A#A#A#, where A is a alphabetic character and # is numeric digit. Otherwise, 1 to 9 alphanumeric characters are allowed.

CountryCode.description:
Shipper's country or territory code.

Valid values: CA,MX, PR, US, AT, BE, DE, DK, ES, FI, FR, GB, IE, IT, NL, PT, SE, MC and VA

ResidentialAddressIndicator.description: If tag is present, then the address is residential address. Pickup location residential address indicator. The presence indicates residential address, the absence indicates a business address.

Shipper_Address.description: Information that specifies a physical location.

flattened_text: The "Shipper Address" object contains details about the physical location of the shipper. It includes Address Line 1, Address Line 2, Address Line 3, City, Country Code, Postal Code, Residential Address Indicator, and State/Province Code. Each field has specific character limits and requirements. The Country Code must be one of the specified values. The Postal Code format varies based on the country. The State/Province Code is required for US and CA addresses.

ShipperAssignedIdentificationNumber.description: An identification number specified by shipper.

AttentionName.description: Contact name at the consignee's location.

PhoneNumber.description: Consignee's Phone Number. US Phone numbers must be 10 digits. No formatting is allowed. Required if origin and destination countries or territories are different.

FaxNumber.description: Consignee's Fax Number. US Fax numbers must be 10 digits. No formatting is allowed. Required if origin and destination countries or territories are different.

LocationID.description: Location name that the package is shipped to.

ReceivingAddressName.description: Name of the location where the package is received.

Manifest_ShipTo.description: Address and contact information describing the location where a return is to be delivered.

flattened_text:
**Summary:**

The `Manifest_ShipTo` object contains address and contact information for the location where a return is to be delivered. It includes details such as the address, contact name, company name, email address, fax number, location ID, phone number, receiving address name, shipper-assigned identification number, and tax identification number. Some fields have specific length and formatting requirements.

StateProvinceCode.description: Consignee's state or province code. Must be valid US state. If the consignee's country or territory  is US or CA a two character code is required. Otherwise, the StateProvinceCode is optional.

PostalCode.description: Consignee's postal code. If the address is US then 5 or 9 digits are required. CA addresses must provide a 6 character postal code that has the format of A#A#A#, where A is a alphabetic character and # is numeric digit. Otherwise, 1 to 9 alphanumeric characters are allowed.

CountryCode.description:
Consignee's country or territory  code.

Valid values: CA,MX, PR, US, AT, BE, DE, DK, ES, FI, FR, GB, IE, IT, NL, PT, SE, MC and VA

ShipTo_Address.description: Information that specifies a physical location.

flattened_text: This section defines the address details for shipping. It includes fields for Address Line 1, Address Line 2, Address Line 3, City, Consignee Name, Country Code, Postal Code, and State/Province Code. Each field has specific character limits and requirements. The Country Code field has predefined valid values. The Postal Code field has specific formats based on the country. The State/Province Code is required for US and CA addresses. The overall structure is represented as an object named "Address" in XML.

Number.description: Number tag.

Code.description: Reflects what will go on the label as the name of the reference. For additional information, refer to the Reference Codes table in the Appendix.

Value.description: Customer supplied reference number. Reference numbers are defined by the shipper and can contain any character string.

flattened_text: This section defines a data structure called "Manifest_ReferenceNumber" with three properties: Code, Number, and Value. The Code property is a 2-character string, the Number property is a single character string, and the Value property is a string up to 35 characters long. The Value property is required. The data structure is represented as an object in XML format with the name "ReferenceNumber." The Code property is a label name, the Number property is a tag, and the Value property is a customer-supplied reference number.

Code.description: For addition information, refer to the Service Codes table in the Appendix.

Description.description: Description of the service code. Examples are Next Day Air, Worldwide Express, and Ground.

Manifest_Service.description: Container for service code and description.

flattened_text: This section defines a manifest service that can contain service code and description. The service code must be 3 characters long and is linked to a table in the Appendix for more details. The description field provides examples like Next Day Air and Worldwide Express. The service code is a required field in this object, which is represented as XML with the name "Service."

Activity.description:
Information about package delivery activity.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Description.description: Description of package merchandise.

LargePackage.description:
Values for LargePackage are:
- 1 - Oversize 1
- 2 - Oversize 2
- 4 - Large package

ReferenceNumber.description:
Container tag for information about the package-level reference number.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

UPSPremiumCareIndicator.description: Presence of the tag indicates UPSPremiumCare applies to this package

flattened_text: The `Manifest_Package` object contains information about a package for delivery. It includes details such as package activity, description, dimensional weight, dimensions, package service options, package weight, reference number, tracking number, and UPS Premium Care indicator. Some elements are returned as arrays based on the API version used. The `LargePackage` field specifies values for different package sizes.

Date.description: Date of package delivery activity. Date format: YYYYMMDD.

Time.description: Time of package delivery activity. Time format: HHMMSS

flattened_text: This data structure represents a package delivery activity. It includes properties for the date and time of the activity. The date should be in YYYYMMDD format, and the time should be in HHMMSS format. The maximum occurrences for this activity is 1.

Length.description:
Package length. 
Valid values: 0 to 108 IN and 0 to 270 CM

Package_Dimensions.description:
Container tag for package dimension information. 
Length + 2 * (Width + Height) must be less than or equal to 130 IN or 330 CM.

flattened_text: This section defines package dimensions for a container. The sum of the length and twice the sum of the width and height must not exceed 130 inches or 330 centimeters. It includes properties for height, length, and width, each with specific length constraints. The length must be between 0 and 108 inches or 0 and 270 centimeters. All three dimensions are required.

Weight.description: The value of package dimensional weight. A value of zero should be used for letters.

Package_DimensionalWeight.description: Container tag for package dimensional weight.

flattened_text: This object represents package dimensional weight. It includes the unit of measurement and weight value. The weight value should be zero for letters. The object is required to have both the unit of measurement and weight properties.

Code.description:
The code representing the unit of measure associated with the shipment's dimensional weight.
Valid values:
LBS - Pounds (default)
KGS - Kilograms
Defaults Unit of Measurement used in the shipper's country or territory.

Description.description: A text description of the code representing the unit of measure associated with the package weight.

DimensionalWeight_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Container tag for package dimensional weight measurement units.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for dimensional weight in a shipping package. It includes a code (e.g., LBS for pounds, KGS for kilograms) and a description of the unit. The code must be 3 characters long, and the description must be up to 35 characters. The code is required, and the default unit of measurement is based on the shipper's country.

DimensionalWeight_Weight.description: The value of package dimensional weight. A value of zero should be used for letters.

flattened_text: This field represents the dimensional weight of a package. Use a value of zero for letters. The value should be a string with a length of 6 characters. The maximum value allowed is 1.

Weight.description: Package weight. Set to 0 for package type of letters or envelops.

Package_PackageWeight.description: Container tag for package weight. Required when the package type is not UPS Letter.

flattened_text: This section defines the package weight for shipments that are not UPS Letters. The weight must be specified, except for letters or envelopes where it should be set to 0. The maximum length for the weight is 6 characters.

Package_LargePackage.description: Values for LargePackage are:1 - Oversize 1,� 2 - Oversize 2,� 4 - Large package

flattened_text: This API defines a package called LargePackage with three possible values: Oversize 1, Oversize 2, and Large package. The package value must be a single character string.

Number.description: Number tag.

Code.description:
Reference number type code for entire shipment, two-character alphanumeric. 
The code specifies the Reference name. 
Valid if the origin/destination pair is US/US or PR/PR.
For additional information, refer to the Reference Codes table in the Appendix.

Value.description: Customer supplied reference number, defined by the shipper and can contain any character string. Valid if the origin/destination pair is US/US or PR/PR.

The Number property is a simple number tag. The Value property is a customer-supplied reference number that can contain any character string. The reference number is required and can be up to 35 characters long. This information is valid for shipments within the US or Puerto Rico.

EarliestDeliveryTime.description: Earliest delivery time. Time format is HHMMSS.

HazardousMaterialsCode.description:
Indicates if the package contains hazardous materials. Valid values:
- 1 - Hazardous Material
- 2 - Electronically billed hazardous material.

If present, only one package may exist in the shipment.

HoldForPickup.description: A flag indicating if a package should be held for pickup. True if tag exists, false otherwise.

AddShippingChargesToCODIndicator.description: An indicator flag that represents a Collect on Delivery (COD) package.

Package_PackageServiceOptions.description: Defines service options used for the package(s).

flattened_text: This section defines service options for packages. It includes properties such as an indicator for Collect on Delivery packages, earliest delivery time, hazardous materials code, hold for pickup flag, and insured value. The HoldForPickup property is required.

CODCode.description:
The code associated with the type of COD. Valid values:
1 - Regular COD
2 - Express COD
3 - Tagless COD

PackageServiceOptions_COD.description: Container for cash on delivery (COD) information.

flattened_text: This section defines the PackageServiceOptions_COD object, which holds information related to cash on delivery (COD) services. It includes properties for CODAmount and CODCode, where CODCode specifies the type of COD service (Regular, Express, or Tagless). The object is limited to a maximum of one instance and is represented in XML as COD.

COD_CODCode.description:
The code associated with the type of COD. Valid values:
1 - Regular COD
2 - Express COD
3 - Tagless COD

flattened_text: This field specifies the type of Cash on Delivery (COD) payment method. Valid values include Regular COD (1), Express COD (2), and Tagless COD (3). The field is a string with a length of 1 character.

CurrencyCode.description:
The IATA currency code associated with the COD amount for the package.

Required if the value for COD amount exists in MonetaryValue tag.

Must match one of the IATA currency codes.

For addition information, refer to the Currency Codes table in the Appendix.

MonetaryValue.description: The COD value for the package. Required if CODCode is 1.Absolute maximum value is 21474836.47 (limited by the maximum value of a 32-bit integer).

COD_CODAmount.description: The amount of the COD that is to be collected for the shipment.

flattened_text: This field specifies the amount to be collected for Cash on Delivery (COD) shipments. It includes the currency code and the monetary value of the COD. The currency code must match one of the IATA currency codes. The monetary value should not exceed 21474836.47.

CurrencyCode.description: Not populated in this release.

MonetaryValue.description: The monetary value for the insured value amount associated with the package. Max value of 5,000 USD for Local and 50,000 USD for Remote.

PackageServiceOptions_InsuredValue.description: Container tag for insured value amount for the package.

flattened_text: This object, `PackageServiceOptions_InsuredValue`, is a container for the insured value amount related to a package. It includes two properties: `CurrencyCode` (not used in this version) and `MonetaryValue` (the insured value amount, with a maximum of $5,000 for local and $50,000 for remote packages). The `MonetaryValue` property is required and must be a string of exactly 8 characters.

The type of Call Tag service. 
Valid values:
00 - No return service
01 - UPS Call Tag Service
02 - UPS Print and Mail
03 - 1 UPS Pickup Attempt
04 - UPS Print Return Label
05 - Online Call Tag (3 UPS Pickup Attempts)
06 - UPS Electronic Return Label
08 - UPS Returns on the Web

flattened_text: This object, ShipmentServiceOptions_CallTagARS, is used for Call Tag services. It includes properties for the type of service and a reference number. The Code property specifies the type of Call Tag service, with valid values ranging from 00 to 08. The Number property is a reference number associated with the service, required when the Code is 01.

MonetaryValue.description: The shipment's customs value amount.

flattened_text: This section defines the customs value of a shipment. It includes the monetary value of the customs declaration. The maximum length of the value is 16 characters. The 'MonetaryValue' property is required.

- 02 - Consignee Billing
- 03 - Third Party
- 04 - Freight Collect

It includes the UPS Account number and how shipping charges were billed (Shipper, Consignee Billing, Third Party, Freight Collect). The container requires both the Account number and billing option to be provided.

CompanyName.description: The name of person or company to whom package was shipped.

AttentionName.description: The "Attention To" field for the person/company to whom package is shipped.

PhoneNumber.description: UPS Access Point's Phone Number. US Phone numbers must be 10 digits. No formatting is allowed. Required if origin and destination countries or territories are different.

Manifest_UAPAddress.description: Information about Hold for Pickup UPS Access Point Address

flattened_text: This object, "Manifest_UAPAddress," contains information about a UPS Access Point address for Hold for Pickup. It includes fields for the address, attention name, company name, and phone number. The attention name and company name fields can have a maximum length of 35 characters, while the phone number must be 10 digits for US numbers. The phone number is required if the origin and destination countries are different.

AddressLine1.description: Address Line 1 of the UPS Access Point.

AddressLine2.description: Address Line 2 of the UPS Access Point. Usually room/floor information.

AddressLine3.description: Address Line 3 of the UPS Access Point. Usually department information.

StateProvinceCode.description: UPS Access Point's state or province code. Must be valid US state. If the UPS Access Point country or territory is US or CA a two character code is required, otherwise, the StateProvinceCode is optional.

PostalCode.description: UPS Access Point's postal code. If the address is US then 5 or 9 digits are required. CA addresses must provide a 6 character postal code that has the format of A#A#A#, where A is an alphabetic character and # is numeric digit. Otherwise, 1 to 16 alphanumeric characters are allowed.

CountryCode.description: UPS Access Point's country or territory code. Valid values: CA,MX, PR, US, AT, BE, DE, DK, ES, FI, FR, GB, IE, IT, NL, PT, SE, MC, and VA

Each field has specific character limits and requirements. The address can be for various countries, with specific formats for postal codes.
