If Activity Type is "SD", this element will contain agreed upon date with Customer for delivery Date. Format will be YYYYMMDD.

flattened_text: This API defines a data structure for a generic subscription file. It includes properties such as Activity, ActivityType, BillToAccount, FailureNotification, PackageReferenceNumber, RescheduledDeliveryDate, Service, ShipTo, ShipmentReferenceNumber, ShipperNumber, and TrackingNumber. The ActivityType property specifies the type of activity with specific codes. Some properties return data as arrays based on the API version used. The TrackingNumber and ActivityType properties are required.

Number.description: Number tag.

Code.description:
Reflects what will go on the label as the name of the reference. 
For addition information, refer to the Service Codes table in the Appendix.

Value.description: Customer supplied reference number. Reference numbers are defined by the shipper and can contain any character string.

flattened_text: This object defines a generic shipment reference number with properties for a barcode indicator, a code, a number, and a value. The code reflects the reference name on the label and has a length of 2 characters. The number is a single character tag. The value is a customer-supplied reference number with a maximum length of 35 characters. The "Value" property is required. The object is named "ShipmentReferenceNumber" in XML.

Number.description: Number tag.

Code.description:
Reflects what will go on the label as the name of the reference. 
For addition information, refer to the Service Codes table in the Appendix.

Value.description: Customer supplied reference number. Reference numbers are defined by the shipper and can contain any character string.

flattened_text: This object represents a generic package reference number. It includes properties for a barcode indicator, a code reflecting the reference name, a number tag, and a customer-supplied reference number. The code and number have specific length requirements. The customer reference number can be up to 35 characters long. The Value property is required. The object is named PackageReferenceNumber in XML.

Code.description: For addition information, refer to the Service Codes table in the Appendix.

Description.description: Not used.

Generic_Service.description: Container for service code and description.

flattened_text: This is a generic service container with a code and description. The code must be 3 characters long and is linked to a table in the appendix. The description field is not used. The code is required. The container is named "Service" in XML.

Date.description: Date of package activity (i.e. YYYYMMDD). If generic record ActivityType is TC then event date is the date of first USPS scan.

Time.description: Time of package activity(i.e. HHMMSS). If generic record ActivityType is TC then event time is the time of first USPS scan.

flattened_text: This data structure represents generic information about package activity. It includes properties for the date and time of the activity. The date should be in YYYYMMDD format, and the time should be in HHMMSS format. If the activity type is TC, the date and time correspond to the first USPS scan.

Option.description:
Indicates how shipping charges for the package were billed. 
Valid Values: 01, 02, 03, 04, 99 
Value Definitions: 
01 Shipper
02 Consignee Billing 
03 Third Party
04 Freight Collect
99 International Bill Option

Number.description: The UPS Account number to which the shipping charges were billed.

Generic_BillToAccount.description: The information provided within this container identifies the shipper number and billing option the user specified to view during the subscription process.

flattened_text: This container, "Generic_BillToAccount," holds information about the shipper number and billing option chosen by the user during subscription. It includes properties for the UPS Account number (Number) and the billing method (Option). The "Option" property specifies how shipping charges were billed, with values like Shipper, Consignee Billing, Third Party, Freight Collect, or International Bill Option. Both "Number" and "Option" properties are required and the container can only have one instance.

LocationID.description: Location name that the package is shipped to.

ReceivingAddressName.description: Alias of the location where the package is received.

Bookmark.description: Bookmark of the package is shifted to.

Generic_ShipTo.description: Address and contact information describing the location where a return is to be delivered.

flattened_text: This data structure defines the information needed for shipping returns to a specific location. It includes the bookmark of the package, the location ID, and an alias for the receiving address. The location ID must be between 3 and 10 characters long, and the alias must be between 1 and 35 characters long.

FailedEmailAddress.description: Email address that failed when an attempt was made to send email to the customer

Generic_FailureNotification.description: Failure notification information containing email address and Notification code

flattened_text: This object, "Generic Failure Notification," contains information about a failed notification, including the email address that failed and a notification code. The email address is limited to 50 characters and must be provided. The object references a schema for the failure notification code.

Code.description:
Code representing type of failure email notification. Valid values:
- 01 – Package is ready to pickup at UPS Access Point - Original
- 02 – Package is ready to pickup at UPS Access Point - Reminder
- 03 – Package is delivery to alternate delivery location
- 04 – Package is returned to Sender from UPS Access Point Location

Description.description: Not used.

FailureNotification_FailureNotificationC.description: Failure notification code information describing code.

flattened_text: This object defines a failure notification code with two properties: Code and Description. The Code property represents the type of failure email notification and has a maximum length of 2 characters. The valid values for the Code property are 01, 02, 03, and 04, each representing a different notification type. The Description property is not used.
This defines an "ErrorResponse" object that includes a "response" property referring to a common error response schema.

CommonErrorResponse.description: The error response containing any errors that occurred.

errors.description: The error array containing any errors that occurred.

flattened_text: This defines a common error response structure that includes an array of error messages. Each error message is defined in a separate schema called "ErrorMessage."

ErrorMessage.description: The error response containing any errors that occurred.

flattened_text: This defines an "ErrorMessage" object that includes an error code and message for any errors that occur in the response.

info.title: Ship
info.description:
The Shipping Package API gives the application many ways to manage the shipment of packages to their destination. # Reference - Business Rules - Appendix 1 - Appendix 2 - Errors - FAQ - Best Practices

Try out UPS APIs with example requests using Postman. Explore API documentation and sample applications through GitHub.

flattened_text: The Shipping Package API provides various functions to help manage package shipments. You can access business rules, appendices, error information, FAQs, and best practices through the API documentation. You can also test UPS APIs with example requests using Postman and explore sample applications on GitHub.
This OpenAPI specification defines two server URLs: one for the Customer Integration Environment at "https://wwwcie.ups.com/api" and one for Production at "https://onlinetools.ups.com/api".

flattened_text: This API endpoint allows clients to access UPS shipping services over the internet. Clients can create shipping requests with various details like package dimensions, weight, addresses, and service options. The API supports different types of shipments, including standard, proactive response, EEI form, tax ID, carbon neutral, negotiated rates, international forms, dry ice/lithium batteries, hazmat goods, third-party billing, multi-piece shipping, UPS Access Point delivery, and worldwide economy shipping. The endpoint provides examples for different types of shipments and handles various response scenarios like successful operations, invalid requests, unauthorized requests, blocked merchants, and rate limit exceeded. The API requires authorization and offers a range of security features.

To use OAuth2 for authentication, follow these steps:

OAuth2 uses client credentials and the token URL is https://wwwcie.ups.com/security/v1/oauth/token. The authentication method is client_secret_basic.

The `SHIPRequestWrapper` object contains a single property called `ShipmentRequest`, which refers to the `ShipmentRequest` schema. The `ShipmentRequest` property is required and the object is represented in XML as `ShipmentRequest`.

This component defines a response wrapper for a single shipment response. The wrapper includes the `ShipmentResponse` property, which references the schema for the shipment response. The `ShipmentResponse` property is required and the wrapper is of type object. The XML element for this wrapper is named `ShipmentResponse`.
This is a Shipment Request object that includes specifications for labels, receipts, the request itself, and the shipment details. The object must include the Request and Shipment properties.

StateProvinceCode.description: The code of the address's admininstrative division (state, province, distict, prefecture, etc...).

PostalCode.description: Postal code

CountryCode.description: Country code

flattened_text: This API defines a data structure for a Point of Entry (POE) address, including Address Line 1, Address Line 2, City, Country Code, Postal Code, and State/Province Code. Each field has specific character limits and validation rules. The required fields are Address Line 1, City, and Country Code.

Shipment_WorldEase.description:
WorldEase is a contract service offering in the UPS shipping that decreases brokerage fees by consolidating
loose packages into one shipment for customs clearance.

GCCN.description: The Global Consolidation Clearance Number(GCCN) generated for the master shipment. This is required for child shipment.

MasterEUConsolidationIndicator.description: 1 indicates a Master Consolidation request for the European Union.

MasterHasDocBox.description: This field is a flag to indicate if the request is a master shipment. This is required for Master shipment only. If MasterHasDocBox is "0" then request is considered a master shipment.

MasterShipmentChgType.description:
Code that indicates how shipping charges will be paid.

| Code  | Name                | Description:                                                              |
| :--:  | :--                 | :--                                                                       |
| CAF   | Cost And Freight    | Shipper pays to point of import, conignee pays balance.                   |
| COL   | Freight Collect     | Consignee (with valid UPS account) pays all shipping charges              |
| DDP   | Delivered Duty Paid | Shipper pays shipping and duty, consignee pays the Value Added Tax (VAT)  |
| FOB   | Free On Board       | Shipper pays to point to export, consignee pays balance                   |
| PRE   | Prepaid             | Shipper pays all shipping charges                                         |
| SDT   | Free Domicile       | Child Shipper pays for shipping, duities and taxes                        |

VendorCollectIDNumberExemptIndicator.description: This field indicates if VendorCollectIDTypeCode and VendorCollectIDNumber should be exempt from validation. "0" indicates VendorCollectIDTypeCode and VendorCollectIDNumber fields are required.

PortOfEntry.description: Container for port of entry details

Address.description: Address of the POE. For Master/Child Shipment

flattened_text:
This API defines the Shipment_WorldEase object for UPS shipping. It includes properties like DestinationCountryCode, DestinationPostalCode, GCCN, MasterEUConsolidationIndicator, MasterHasDocBox, MasterShipmentChgType, PortOfEntry, and VendorCollectIDNumberExemptIndicator. 

Key requirements include DestinationCountryCode, MasterShipmentChgType, and PortOfEntry. The PortOfEntry property contains details like Address, ClearancePortCode, Consignee, and Name. The MasterShipmentChgType property specifies how shipping charges will be paid, with options like CAF, COL, DDP, FOB, PRE, and SDT.

RequestOption.description:
Optional Processing.  

Note: Full address validation is not performed. Therefore, it is the responsibility of the Shipping Tool User to ensure the address entered is correct to avoid an address correction fee.  Valid values:
nonvalidate = No street level address validation would be performed, but Postal Code/State combination validation would still be performed.

validate = No street level address validation would be performed, but City/State/Postal Code/ combination validation would still be performed.

SubVersion.description:
When UPS introduces new elements in the response that are not associated with new request elements, Subversion is used. This ensures backward compatibility.

To get such elements you need to have the right Subversion. The value of the subversion is explained in the Response element Description.

Example: Itemized Charges are returned only when the Subversion element is present and greater than or equal to 1601. 

Format: YYMM = Year and month of the release.

Example: 1607 = 2016 July  Supported values: 1601, 1607, 1701, 1707, 1801, 1807, 2108, 2205

flattened_text: This API defines a request container for shipping information. It includes fields for specifying processing options, version compatibility, and transaction references. The "RequestOption" field allows users to choose address validation levels. The "SubVersion" field ensures backward compatibility with new response elements. The "TransactionReference" field references a specific schema for transaction details. The request container is required to include the "RequestOption" field and is represented in XML as "Request."

CustomerContext.description: The CustomerContext Information which will be echoed during response.

Request_TransactionReference.description: TransactionReference identifies transactions between client and server.

flattened_text: This object, Request_TransactionReference, is used to identify transactions between a client and server. It includes a property called CustomerContext, which contains information echoed in the response. The CustomerContext is a string with a maximum length of 512 characters.

Description.description:
The Description of Goods for the shipment. Applies to international and domestic shipments. 

Provide a detailed description of items being shipped for documents and non-documents. 

Examples: "annual reports" and "9 mm steel screws".  Required if all of the listed conditions are true: 
ShipFrom and ShipTo countries or territories are not the same; The packaging type is not UPS Letter; The ShipFrom and or ShipTo countries or territories are not in the European Union or the ShipFrom and ShipTo countries or territories are both in the European Union and the shipments service type is not UPS Standard.

DocumentsOnlyIndicator.description:
Indicates a shipment contains written, typed, or printed communication of no commercial value. 

If DocumentsOnly is not specified then it implies that the shipment contains non documents or documents of commercial value. 

Default is a shipment contains non- documents or documents of commercial value.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored. 

Valid only for shipments with different origin and destination countries or territories. The origin country or territory is not US, and the destination country or territory is not CA, PR or MX.

GoodsNotInFreeCirculationIndicator.description: Goods Not In Free Circulation indicator.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored. This indicator is invalid for a package type of UPS Letter and DocumentsOnly.

MovementReferenceNumber.description: Movement Reference Number (MRN) information.  Must contain alphanumeric characters only. Must be a length of 18 characters. The 3rd and 4th Characters must be the Shipper country or territory ISO Code.

NumOfPiecesInShipment.description: Total number of pieces in all pallets in a UPS Worldwide Express Freight Shipment.  It is required for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday Shipment. Valid values are 1 to 99999.

USPSEndorsement.description:
USPS Endorsement.
Valid values: 
1 = Return Service Requested 
2 = Forwarding Service Requested 
3 = Address Service Requested 
4 = Change Service Requested and 
5 = No Service Selected. 
Note: For International Mail Innovations shipments use No Service Selected. International Mail Innovations shipments are applicable for Priority Mail Innovations and Mail Innovations Economy Mail Innovations services only.  Required for Mail Innovations forward shipments.

MILabelCN22Indicator.description: Indicates single label with both MI label and CN22 form.  International CN22 form is required.

SubClassification.description:
A component encoded on the barcode of the Mail Innovations label.   Valid values: 
IR = Irregular
MA = Machineable
SubClass is only required if the customer's contract have them subclass the package not UPS.

CostCenter.description:
Customer assigned identifier for report and billing summarization displays to the right of the Cost Center title.  Required for Mail Innovations Return shipments. It is shown on the bottom of the shipping label as reference 2.

Cost Center length is alphanumeric with a max length of 30 for Mail Innovations forward shipments.

Cost Center length is numeric with a max length of 4 for Mail Innovations Return shipments.

CostCenterBarcodeIndicator.description: Presence/Absence indicator. Presence of this indicator means that the customer is requesting for the CostCenter field to be barcoded at the bottom of the label.

PackageID.description: Customer-assigned unique piece identifier that returns visibility events.  Required only for Mail Innovations forward shipments. Alpha numeric values only. It is shown on the bottom of the shipping label as reference 1.

PackageIDBarcodeIndicator.description: Presence/Absence indicator. Presence of this indicator means that the customer is requesting for the PackageID field to be barcoded at the bottom of the label.

IrregularIndicator.description:
Mail classification defined by the USPS.   Valid values: 
1 = Balloon
2 = Oversize
3 = Not Applicable

MIDualReturnShipmentKey.description:
MIDualReturnShipmentKey is unique key required to process Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipment. 

The unique identifier (key) would be returned in response of first phase of Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipments. 

This unique identifier (key) would be part of request for second phase of Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipments.

Format: 
For Package return shipments, the package tracking number is concatenated with the system time (YYYY-MM-DDHH.MM.SS.NNN), followed by service code. 

For MI Return shipments, the Mail Manifest ID (MMI) is concatenated with the system time.  The unique identifier (key) is required to link the package and the Mail Innovations portion of Dual Return shipment. 

If unique identifier (key) is empty in the request for UPS Mail Innovations Return Service, the request will be treated as the first phase of the Mail Innovations Dual Returns Request. 

If the MIDualReturnShipmentIndicator is present with empty or null MIDualReturnShipmentKey in UPS Package Return Shipment, the request will be treated as the first phase of Dual MI Return Label Shipment. 

This field would be ignored if MIDualReturnShipmentIndicator is not present in UPS Package Return Shipment request.

MIDualReturnShipmentIndicator.description:
MIDualReturnShipmentIndicator is an indicator to identify a Package Shipment is part of UPS Mail Innovations Dual Label Shipment. 

Its presence means Package Shipment is part of UPS Mail Innovations Dual Label shipment.  If the indicator is present in Package Shipment request, shipment would be considered as part of a Dual Mail Innovations Returns. 

This indicator is not valid with UPS Mail Innovations Returns Service code.

RatingMethodRequestedIndicator.description:
Presence/Absence Indicator. Any value inside is ignored. RatingMethodRequestedIndicator is an indicator.
If present, Billable Weight Calculation method information and Rating Method information would be returned in response.

TaxInformationIndicator.description: Presence/Absence Indicator. Any value inside is ignored. TaxInformationIndicator is an indicator. If present, any taxes that may be applicable to a shipment would be returned in response. If this indicator is requested with NegotiatedRatesIndicator, Tax related information, if applicable, would be returned only for Negotiated Rates and not for Published Rates. The Tax related information includes any type of Taxes, corresponding Monetary Values, Total Charges with Taxes and disclaimers (if applicable) would be returned in response.

Locale.description:
Represents 5 character ISO Locale that allows the user to request Reference Number Code on Label, Label instructions and Receipt instructions (if applicable) in desired language. 
Locale is specified by the combination of language code and country or territory code - 2 character language code and 2 character country or territory code seperated by an underscore ('_') character.  If Locale element is requested along with LabelLinksIndicator, the URL to retrieve Label and Receipts (if applicable) will be returned in the requested Locale. Please note only LabelURL and ReceiptURL (if applicable) will be returned. LocalLanguageLabelURL and LocalLanguageReceiptURL will not be returned if Locale element is present in request.
Queen's English (en_GB) is the default

ShipmentValueThresholdCode.description:
Shipment Value Threshold Code. 01 = Shipment value is below or equals to threshold value
02 = Shipment value is above threshold value.     NA = Not Applicable

MasterCartonID.description: Master Carton ID. If Economy Service (17 or 72) : Economy Shipment will be associated with given Master Carton ID. If Non-Economy Service: Master Carton Shipment will be created for given Master Carton ID.

MasterCartonIndicator.description:
Master Carton Indicator. Presence of the indicator means Master Carton ID will be created and returned to client. 
This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored.                                                                  MasterCartonIndicator is only valid with Econmoy Shipment (Service Code 17 or 72). Will be ignored if master carton id present.

ShipmentDate.description: User can send up to 7 days in the future with current date as day zero. Format: YYYYMMDD

QuoteID.description: This field is used to pass the Quote ID generated from the Global Checkout API. This is mandatory to validate your Global Checkout Guaranteed Landed Cost.

flattened_text: This YAML defines a Shipment Request object with various properties like cost center, description of goods, package details, and shipment service options. It includes information such as shipment date, shipper details, and service type. The object is required to have Shipper, Service, ShipTo, and Package properties. The XML representation of this object is named Shipment.

Code.description:
Return Service types:
- 2 = UPS Print and Mail (PNM)
- 3 = UPS Return Service 1-Attempt (RS1)
- 5 = UPS Return Service 3-Attempt (RS3)
- 8 = UPS Electronic Return Label (ERL)
- 9 = UPS Print Return Label (PRL)
- 10 = UPS Exchange Print Return Label
- 11 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 1-Attempt Box 1
- 12 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 1-Attempt Box 2
- 13 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 1-Attempt Box 3
- 14 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 1-Attempt Box 4
- 15 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 1-Attempt Box 5
- 16 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 3-Attempt Box 1
- 17 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 3-Attempt Box 2
- 18 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 3-Attempt Box 3
- 19 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 3-Attempt Box 4
- 20 = UPS Pack & Collect Service 3-Attempt Box 5

Description.description: Return Service description.

Shipment_ReturnService.description: Type of Return service. When this container exists, the shipment is a return shipment.

flattened_text: The `Shipment_ReturnService` object defines the type of return service for a shipment. It specifies various return service codes such as UPS Print and Mail, UPS Return Service 1-Attempt, UPS Electronic Return Label, and others. Each code has a corresponding description. The object includes properties for `Code` (with a maximum length of 2 characters) and `Description` (with a maximum length of 35 characters). The `Code` property is required.

Name.description:
Shippers company name. 

For forward Shipment 35 characters are accepted, but only 30 characters will be printed on the label.

AttentionName.description:
Shippers Attention Name. 

For forward Shipment 35 characters are accepted, but only 30 characters will be printed on the label.  Required if destination is international. Required if Invoice and CO International forms are requested and the ShipFrom address is not present.

CompanyDisplayableName.description:
Shipper's CompanyDisplayableName.

The CompanyDisplayableName will be displayed in tracking results and notification messages in place of the name associated with the shipper account. 
The original shipper account name will be displayed for all Return Services and Import Control Shipments.  This is available for Shipper accounts enabled by UPS and applies to Forward Shipments.

TaxIdentificationNumber.description: Shipper's Tax Identification Number.  Conditionally required if EEI form (International forms) is requested and ship From is not mentioned. This element has been deprecated, replacement can be found in the GlobalTaxInformation container.

ShipperNumber.description:
Shipper's six digit alphanumeric account number.

Must be associated with the UserId specified in the AccessRequest XML. 

The account must be a valid UPS account number that is active. 

For US, PR and CA accounts, the account must be either a daily pickup account, an occasional account, or a customer B.I.N account. 

Drop Shipper accounts are valid for return service shipments only if the account is Trade Direct (TD) enabled. 

All other accounts must be either a daily pickup account or an occasional account.

EMailAddress.description: Shipper's email address.  Must be associated with the UserId specified in the AccessRequest XML.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for the Shipper's information. It includes details such as the Shipper's address, contact information, company name, and account number. Some fields have specific character limits and requirements. The Tax Identification Number field is deprecated and replaced by the GlobalTaxInformation container. Certain fields are required, such as Address, ShipperNumber, and Name. The Shipper object is represented in XML as "Shipper."

Number.description:
Shipper's phone Number.  Valid values are 0 - 9.

If Shipper country or territory is US, PR, CA, and VI, the layout is:
area code, 7 digit PhoneNumber or
area code, 7 digit PhoneNumber, 4 digit extension number.

For other countries or territories, the layout is: country or territory code, area code, 7 digit number.

A phone number is required if destination is international.

flattened_text: This object represents the shipper's phone number, including an extension if applicable. The phone number format varies based on the shipper's country or territory. For the US, PR, CA, and VI, it can include an area code, 7-digit number, and a 4-digit extension. For other countries, it includes the country or territory code, area code, and 7-digit number. A phone number is mandatory for international destinations.

AddressLine.description:
The Shipper street address including name and number (when applicable). Up to three occurrences are allowed; only the first is printed on the label.

35 characters are accepted, but for the first occurrence, only 30 characters will be printed on the label for return shipments.

City.description: Shipper's City.   For forward Shipment 30 characters are accepted, but only 15 characters will be printed on the label.

StateProvinceCode.description:
Shipper's state or province code.

For forward Shipment 5 characters are accepted, but only 2 characters will be printed on the label.  For US, PR and CA accounts, the account must be either a daily pickup account, an occasional account, or a customer B.I.N account.

PostalCode.description: Shipper's postal code.

CountryCode.description:
Shipper's country or territory code.

Refer to country or territory Codes in the Appendix for valid values.

Drop Shipper accounts are valid for return service shipments only if the account is Trade Direct (TD) enabled.

Shipper_Address.description:
Address tag Container.  The package should be returned to this address if the package is undeliverable.

This address appears on the upper left hand corner of the label.

Note: If the ShipFrom container is not present then this address will be used as the ShipFrom address. If this address is used as the ShipFrom the shipment will be rated from this origin address.

flattened_text: The Shipper Address object contains details for the address where a package should be returned if undeliverable. This address is used as the ShipFrom address if ShipFrom is not specified. It includes AddressLine, City, CountryCode, PostalCode, and StateProvinceCode fields. The AddressLine can have up to 3 occurrences, but only the first is printed on the label. Various character limits apply for different fields. The object is required and must include AddressLine, City, and CountryCode.

Name.description: Consignee's company name.  All other accounts must be either a daily pickup account or an occasional account.

AttentionName.description:
Contact name at the consignee's location.  Required for: UPS Next Day Air® Early service, and when ShipTo country or territory is different than ShipFrom country or territory.

Required if Invoice International form is requested.

TaxIdentificationNumber.description: Consignee's tax identification number. This element has been deprecated, replacement can be found in the GlobalTaxInformation container.

FaxNumber.description: Consignee's fax number.  If ShipTo country or territory is US 10 digits allowed, otherwise 1-15 digits allowed.

LocationID.description: Location ID is a unique identifier referring to a specific shipping/receiving location.  Location ID must be alphanumeric characters. All letters must be capitalized.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for shipping information to the recipient. It includes details like the recipient's address, contact name, email, fax number, company name, and location ID. Some fields have specific requirements, like character limits or mandatory presence. The tax identification number field is deprecated and should be replaced with information from the GlobalTaxInformation container.

Number.description:
Consignee's phone Number.  Required for: UPS Next Day Air® Early service, and when Ship To country or territory is different than the ShipFrom country or territory.

If ShipTo country or territory is US, PR, CA, and VI, the layout is:
area code, 7 digit PhoneNumber or
area code, 7 digit PhoneNumber, 4 digit extension number; number.

For other countries or territories, the layout is: country or territory code, area code, 7 digit number.

flattened_text: This object, "ShipTo_Phone," is a container for a phone number. It includes two properties: "Extension" for the consignee's phone extension and "Number" for the consignee's phone number. The "Number" property is required for specific UPS services and when the destination country differs from the origin country. The phone number format varies based on the destination country. The object is represented in XML as "Phone."

AddressLine.description: Address Line of the consignee. All three Address Lines will be printed on the label.

City.description: Consignee's city. 30 characters are accepted, but only 15 characters will be printed on the label.

StateProvinceCode.description:
Consignee's state or province code. Required for US or Canada.  If destination is US or CA, then the value must be a valid US State/ Canadian Province code.

If the country or territory is Ireland, the StateProvinceCode will contain the county.

PostalCode.description:
Consignee's postal code.  If the ShipTo country or territory is US or Puerto Rico, 5 or 9 digits are required.

If the ShipTo country or territory is CA, then the postal code is required and must be 6 alphanumeric characters whose format is A#A#A# where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit.

Otherwise optional. For all other countries or territories the postal code is optional and must be no more than 9 alphanumeric characters long.

CountryCode.description:
Consignee's country or territory code.  Must be a valid UPS Billing country or territory code.
For Return Shipment the country or territory code must meet the following conditions:
- At least two of the following country or territory codes are the same: ShipTo, ShipFrom, and Shipper.
- None of the following country or territory codes are the same and are a member of the EU: ShipTo, ShipFrom, and Shipper.
- If any of the two following country or territory codes: ShipTo/ ShipFrom/ Shipper are members in EU otherwise check if the shipper has Third country or territory Contract.

ResidentialAddressIndicator.description:
This field is a flag to indicate if the receiver is a residential location. 
True if ResidentialAddressIndicator tag exists.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored.

POBoxIndicator.description: This field is a flag to indicate if the receiver address has PO box indicator. True if POBoxIndicator tag exists; false otherwise.

flattened_text: The `ShipTo_Address` object contains details of the consignee's address for shipping labels. It includes the consignee's address lines, city, country code, PO box indicator, postal code, residential address indicator, and state/province code. Some fields have specific requirements based on the destination country or territory. The object is required to have AddressLine, City, and CountryCode fields.

Shipment_AlternateDeliveryAddress.description: AlternateDeliveryAddress Container.  Alternate Delivery Address (UPS Access Point Address) required if ShipmentIndicationType is 01 or 02.

flattened_text: This container is used for specifying an alternate delivery address (UPS Access Point Address) when the shipment indication type is 01 or 02. It includes fields for the address, attention name, retail location name, and UPS Access Point ID. The Attention Name, Address, and Name fields are required.

AddressLine.description: Address Line of the Retail Location.

StateProvinceCode.description:
Retail Location state or province code. Required for US or Canada.  If destination is US or CA, then the value must be a valid US State/Canadian Province code.

If the country or territory is Ireland, the StateProvinceCode will contain the county.

PostalCode.description: If the Alternate Delivery Address country or territory is US or Puerto Rico, 5 or 9 digits are required. The character - may be used to separate the first five digits and the last four digits. If the Alternate Delivery Address country or territory is CA, then the postal code is required and must be 6 alphanumeric characters whose format is A#A#A# where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit. Otherwise optional. For all other countries or territories the postal code is optional and must be no more than 9 alphanumeric characters long.

CountryCode.description: Retail Location country or territory code.

flattened_text: This schema defines an alternate delivery address for a retail location. It includes fields for the address line, city, country code, postal code, and state/province code. The postal code requirements vary based on the country or territory. The state/province code is required for the US and Canada, and for Ireland, it represents the county. The address line, city, country code are mandatory fields.

Name.description:
The ship from location's name or company name. 
35 characters are accepted, but for return Shipment only 30 characters will be printed on the label.  Required if ShipFrom tag is in the XML.

AttentionName.description:
The ship from Attention name. 
35 characters are accepted, but for return Shipment only 30 characters will be printed on the label.  Required if ShipFrom tag is in the XML and Invoice or CO International forms is requested. If not present, will default to the Shipper Attention Name.

TaxIdentificationNumber.description:
Company's Tax Identification Number at the pick up location.  Conditionally required if EEI form (International forms) is requested. 
Applies to EEI Form only. This element has been deprecated, replacement can be found in the GlobalTaxInformation container.

FaxNumber.description: The Ship from fax number.  If Ship from country or territory is US 10 digits allowed, otherwise 1-15 digits allowed.

Shipment_ShipFrom.description:
Ship From Container.  Required for return shipment. 

Required if pickup location is different from the shipper's address.

flattened_text: This section defines the Ship From details for a shipment. It is required for return shipments and when the pickup location differs from the shipper's address. Key properties include Address, Attention Name, Company Displayable Name, Fax Number, Name, Phone, Tax ID Type, Tax Identification Number (deprecated), and Vendor Info. The Address and Name fields are mandatory. The Attention Name and Name fields accept up to 35 characters, but only 30 characters will be printed on the label for return shipments. The Fax Number field has specific digit limits based on the country. The Tax Identification Number field is deprecated and replaced by the GlobalTaxInformation container for EEI forms.

Code.description:
Company's tax Identification type.  Valid values: EIN, DNS, and FGN. 
Applies to EEI form only.

Description.description: Description of TaxID submitted.  Applies to EEI form only.

ShipFrom_TaxIDType.description: Tax Identification Container.  Applies to EEI form only.

flattened_text: This object represents the tax identification information for shipping. It is used specifically for the EEI form. It includes the code for the company's tax identification type (EIN, DNS, or FGN) and a description of the submitted tax ID. The Code property is required.

TaxIDType_Code.description:
Company's tax Identification type.  Valid values: EIN, DNS, and FGN. 
Applies to EEI form only.

flattened_text: This field specifies the type of tax identification for a company. Valid values are EIN, DNS, and FGN. It is used specifically for the EEI form. The field must be a string with a length of 6 characters.

TaxIDType_Description.description: Description of TaxID submitted.  Applies to EEI form only.

flattened_text: This field describes the type of Tax ID submitted, specifically for the EEI form. It is a string with a maximum length of 35 characters and must be exactly 1 character long.

Number.description: The Ship from phone Number.

ShipFrom_Phone.description:
Container for Phone Number.  If ShipFrom country or territory is US, PR, CA, and VI, the layout is:
area code, 7 digit phone number or 
area code, 7 digit phone number, 4 digit extension number.

For other countries or territories, the layout is:
country or territory code, area code, 7 digit number. 

 If ShipFrom tag is in the XML and International forms is requested.

flattened_text: The `ShipFrom_Phone` object is used to store phone number information for the shipping address. The format varies based on the country or territory. For the US, PR, CA, and VI, it includes an area code, 7-digit phone number, and optional 4-digit extension. For other countries, it includes the country code, area code, and 7-digit number. The object includes properties for the phone number and extension. The phone number must be provided, while the extension is optional.

AddressLine.description: The Ship from street address including name and number (when applicable). 35 characters are accepted, but for return Shipment only 30 characters will be printed on the label.

City.description:
The Ship from city.

30 characters are accepted, but for return Shipment only 15 characters will be printed on the label.  Required if ShipFrom is supplied

StateProvinceCode.description:
Origin location's state or province code.  Required if ShipFrom is supplied, and ShipFrom country or territory is US.

If ShipFrom country or territory is US or CA, then the value must be a valid US State/ Canadian Province code. If the country or territory is Ireland, the StateProvinceCode will contain the county or territory.

PostalCode.description:
The ship from locations postal code.
9 characters are accepted.  Required if ShipFrom is supplied and the ShipFrom country or territory is the US and Puerto Rico.

For US and Puerto Rico, it must be valid 5 or 9 digit postal code. The character "-" may be used to separate the first five digits and the last four digits.

If the ShipFrom country or territory is CA, then the postal code must be 6 alphanumeric characters whose format is A#A#A# where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit.

For all other countries or territories the postal code is optional and must be no more than 9 alphanumeric characters long.

CountryCode.description:
Origin locations country or territory code.  Required if ShipFrom tag is supplied. For Return Shipment the country or territory code must meet the following conditions:

- At least two of the following country or territory codes are the same: ShipTo, ShipFrom, and Shipper.
- None of the following country or territory codes are the same and are a member of the EU: ShipTo, ShipFrom, and Shipper.
- If any of the two following country or territory codes: ShipTo/ShipFrom/ Shipper are members in EU otherwise check if the shipper has Third country or territory Contract.

ShipFrom_Address.description: Ship from Address Container.  The package will be originating from or being shipped from this address. The shipment will be rated from this origin address to the destination ship to address.

flattened_text: The `ShipFrom_Address` object represents the address where a package is being shipped from. It includes the street address, city, country code, postal code, and state/province code. The address details have specific length and formatting requirements based on the country or territory. The `AddressLine`, `City`, `CountryCode`, and `StateProvinceCode` fields are required. The object is structured as an XML element named `Address`.

VendorCollectIDTypeCode.description:
Code that identifies the type of Vendor Collect ID Number. Valid Values
- 0356 = IOSS
- 0357 = VOEC
- 0358 = HMRC

Vendor Collect ID Number type code will be printed on commercial invoice if present.

VendorCollectIDNumber.description:
Shipper's VAT Tax collection registration number to be entered by Shipper at time of shipment creation. Presence of this number as part of the shipment information implies the shipper has collected/paid the required VAT tax (outside of UPS/UPS systems). Vendor Colect ID Number will be printed on commercial invoice if present.

Sample Values:   'IMDEU1234567' (IOSS #),  'VOEC1234567' (VOEC #),  'GB1234567' (HMRC #)

Required if the shipment is subject to Vendor Collect ID collection

ConsigneeType.description: Consignee Type. 01 = Business  02 = Consumer NA = Not Applicable

flattened_text: The `ShipFrom_VendorInfo` object contains vendor information for a shipment. It includes fields for the consignee type, vendor's VAT tax collection registration number, and the type code for the vendor collect ID number. The vendor collect ID number and type code are required if the shipment is subject to vendor collect ID collection. Sample values for the vendor collect ID number include IOSS, VOEC, and HMRC. The information will be printed on the commercial invoice if provided.

SplitDutyVATIndicator.description: Split Duty VAT Indicator. The presence indicates the payer specified for Transportation Charges will pay transportation charges and any duties that apply to the shipment. The payer specified for Duties and Taxes will pay the VAT (Value-Added Tax) only.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored. The payment method for Transportation charges must be UPS account. The UPS account must be a daily pickup account or an occasional account.

Shipment_PaymentInformation.description: Payment information container for detailed shipment charges. The two shipment charges that are available for specification are Transportation charges and Duties and Taxes.  It is required for non-Ground Freight Pricing shipments only.

flattened_text: This component, "Shipment_PaymentInformation," holds payment details for specific shipment charges. It includes Transportation charges and Duties and Taxes. This information is mandatory for non-Ground Freight Pricing shipments. The component allows up to three shipment charges and specifies the payer for each type of charge. The payment method for Transportation charges must be a UPS account, which must be either a daily pickup account or an occasional account.

Type.description:
Valid values: 
01 = Transportation
02 = Duties and Taxes 03 = Broker of Choice  A shipment charge type of 01 = Transportation is required. 

A shipment charge type of 02 = Duties and Taxes is not required; however, this charge type is invalid for Qualified Domestic Shipments. 

A Qualified Domestic Shipment is any shipment in which one of the following applies: 

1) The origin and destination country or territory is the same.

2) US to PR shipment.

3) PR to US shipment.

4) The origin and destination country or territory are both European Union countries or territories and the GoodsNotInFreeCirculation indicator is not present.

5) The origin and destination IATA code is the same.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      03 = Broker of Choice

ConsigneeBilledIndicator.description:
Consignee Billing payment option indicator. The presence indicates consignee billing option is selected. The absence indicates one of the other payment options is selected.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored. This element or its sibling element, BillShipper, BillReceiver or BillThirdParty, must be present but no more than one can be present. This billing option is valid for a shipment charge type of Transportation only. Only applies to US/PR and PR/US shipment origins and destination.

This payment method allows you to bill the charges for a specified shipment to a consignee who has agreed to pay the charges. All shipping charges are billed to the consignees UPS account number including the following accessorials: Additional Handling, Delivery Area Surcharges, Delivery Change Requests, Early AM Premium, Early AM Out of Territory, Fuel Surcharge, Hazardous Material Surcharges, Large Package Surcharge, Over Max Limits, and Saturday Delivery.

Declared Value, Delivery Confirmation, On Call Pickup, Remote Area Surcharge, Saturday Pickup of Delivery fees are not passed to the consignee. These charges are billed to the shippers UPS account number.

PaymentInformation_ShipmentCharge.description: Shipment charge container.  If Duty and Tax charges are applicable to a shipment and a payer is not specified, the default payer of Duty and Tax charges is Bill to Receiver. There will be no default payer of Duty and Tax charges for DDU and DDP service.

flattened_text: This component defines the payment information for shipment charges. It specifies the default payer for Duty and Tax charges and the billing options for different parties involved in the shipment. The 'Type' property indicates the type of charge, such as Transportation or Duties and Taxes. The 'ConsigneeBilledIndicator' property signifies if the consignee is responsible for payment. The component outlines the valid values for 'Type' and the conditions under which certain charge types are required or invalid.

AccountNumber.description:
UPS account number.  Must be the same UPS account number as the one provided in Shipper/ShipperNumber. 

Either this element or one of the sibling elements CreditCard or AlternatePaymentMethod must be provided, but all of them may not be provided.

AlternatePaymentMethod.description:
Alternate Payment Method.

Valid value: 01= PayPal

Only valid for forward shipments. It is not valid for Return or Import Control shipments. 

This element or one of the sibling elements CreditCard or AccountNumber must be provided, but all of them may not be provided.   PayPal 01: Is only valid for forward shipments. It is not valid for Return or Import Control shipments. 

This element or one of the sibling elements CreditCard or AccountNumber must be provided, but all of them may not be provided.

ShipmentCharge_BillShipper.description: Container for the BillShipper billing option. The three payment methods that are available for the Bill Shipper billing option are alternate payment method, account number or credit card.  This element or its sibling element, BillReceiver, BillThirdParty or ConsigneeBilledIndicator, must be present but no more than one can be present.

flattened_text: The `ShipmentCharge_BillShipper` object is used for specifying billing options for the shipper. It includes fields for providing the UPS account number, alternate payment method (such as PayPal), or credit card details. Only one of these fields can be included. The UPS account number must match the one provided in the shipper details. The alternate payment method is only valid for forward shipments and has a specific value (01 for PayPal). Credit card details can be referenced from another schema.

Type.description:
Valid values:
- 01 = American Express
- 03 = Discover
- 04 = MasterCard
- 05 = Optima
- 06 = VISA
- 07 = Bravo
- 08 = Diners Club
- 13 = Dankort
- 14 = Hipercard
- 15 = JCB
- 17 = Postepay
- 18 = UnionPay/ExpressPay
- 19 = Visa Electron
- 20 = VPAY
- 21 = Carte Bleue

Number.description: Credit Card number.

ExpirationDate.description: Format is MMYYYY where MM is the 2 digit month and YYYY is the 4 digit year.  Valid month values are 01-12 and valid year values are Present Year - (Present Year + 10 years)

SecurityCode.description: Three or four digits that can be found either on top of credit card number or on the back of credit card. Number of digits varies for different type of credit card.  Valid values are 3 or 4 digits. It is required to provide the security code if credit card information is provided and when the ShipFrom countries or territories are other than the below mentioned countries or territories. Argentina, Bahamas, Costa Rica, Dominican Republic, Guatemala, Panama, Puerto Rico and Russia.

BillShipper_CreditCard.description:
Credit card information container.  Required if neither of the following is present: 

/ShipmentRequest/Shipment/PaymentInformation/ShipmentCharge/BillShipper/AccountNumber 
or 
/ShipmentRequest/Shipment/PaymentInformation/ShipmentCharge/BillShipper/AlternatePaymentMethod. 

Credit card payment is valid for shipments without return service only.

flattened_text: This component represents credit card information required for shipments without return service. It includes the card's address, expiration date, number, security code, and type. The expiration date format is MMYYYY, the number is 9-16 digits, and the security code is 3-4 digits. The type corresponds to different card networks. The security code is mandatory for certain countries.

AddressLine.description: Address Line 1 of the credit card billing address. Usually Street address information.

City.description: City of the credit card billing address.

StateProvinceCode.description: State or province code of the credit card billing address.

PostalCode.description: Credit card billing addressee postal code.

CountryCode.description: Credit card billing address country or territory code. Must be a valid UPS Billing country or territory code.

CreditCard_Address.description: Container to hold the Credit card Billing Address.  It is required to provide billing address if credit card information is provided and when the ShipFrom country or territory is the US, PR, and CA.

flattened_text: This container holds the billing address for a credit card transaction. It is mandatory to provide this information when submitting credit card details and when shipping from the US, Puerto Rico, or Canada. The container includes fields for address line, city, country code, postal code, and state/province code. The address line can have up to 3 lines of text, each up to 35 characters long. City, country code, postal code, and state/province code have specific length requirements. The fields for address line, city, and country code are required.

AccountNumber.description:
The UPS account number.  The account must be a valid UPS account number that is active. 

For US, PR and CA accounts, the account must be a daily pickup account, an occasional account, a customer B.I.N account, or a dropper shipper account. 

All other accounts must be either a daily pickup account, an occasional account, a drop shipper account, or a non-shipping account.

ShipmentCharge_BillReceiver.description: Container for the BillReceiver billing option.  This element or its sibling element, BillShipper, BillThirdParty or Consignee Billed, must be present but no more than one can be present. For a return shipment, Bill Receiver is invalid for Transportation charges.

flattened_text: This element, ShipmentCharge_BillReceiver, is used for the BillReceiver billing option in shipping. It contains the UPS account number and address information. Only one billing option can be present. The UPS account number must be valid and meet specific criteria based on the account type.

PostalCode.description:
The postal code for the UPS accounts pickup address. The pickup postal code was entered in the UPS system when the account was set-up.  The postal code must be the same as the UPS Bill Receiver account number pickup address postal code.

Required for United States and Canadian UPS accounts and/or if the UPS account pickup address has a postal code.
If the UPS accounts pickup country or territory is US or Puerto Rico, the postal code is 5 or 9 digits.

The character - may be used to separate the first five digits and the last four digits.

If the UPS accounts pickup country or territory is CA, the postal code is 6 alphanumeric characters whose format is A#A#A# where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit

BillReceiver_Address.description: Container for additional information for the bill receiver's UPS accounts address.

flattened_text: This section defines the `BillReceiver_Address` object, which contains additional information for the bill receiver's UPS account address. It includes a property `PostalCode` for the pickup address postal code. The postal code format varies based on the country or territory of the UPS account. For the US or Puerto Rico, it is 5 or 9 digits, while for Canada (CA), it is 6 alphanumeric characters in the format A#A#A#, where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit. The postal code must match the UPS Bill Receiver account number pickup address postal code.

AccountNumber.description:
The UPS account number of the third party shipper.  The account must be a valid UPS account number that is active. 

For US, PR and CA accounts, the account must be either a daily pickup account, an occasional account, or a customer B.I.N account, or a drop shipper account. 

All other accounts must be either a daily pickup account, an occasional account, a drop shipper account, or a non-shipping account.

CertifiedElectronicMail.description: Posta Elettronica Certificata (PEC) which is the recipient code for the customers certified electronic mail value.

InterchangeSystemCode.description: Sistema Di Interscambio(SDI) which is the recipient code for the customer's interchange value or Interchange System Code

ShipmentCharge_BillThirdParty.description: Container for the third party billing option.  This element or its sibling element, BillShipper, BillReceiver or Consignee Billed, must be present but no more than one can be present.

flattened_text: This element, ShipmentCharge_BillThirdParty, is used for third-party billing in shipping. It contains the UPS account number of the third party shipper, the recipient's certified electronic mail value, and the customer's interchange value. The UPS account number must be valid and active. The element must include the Address property.

PostalCode.description:
The postal code for the UPS accounts pickup address. The pickup postal code is the one that was entered in the UPS system when the account was set-up.  The postal code must be the same as the UPS Bill Third Party account number pickup address postal code.

Required for United States and Canadian UPS accounts and/or if the UPS account pickup address has a postal code.
If the UPS accounts pickup country or territory is US or Puerto Rico, the postal code is 5 or 9 digits.

The character - may be used to separate the first five digits and the last four digits.

If the UPS accounts pickup country or territory is CA, the postal code is 6 alphanumeric characters whose format is A#A#A# where A is an uppercase letter and # is a digit.

CountryCode.description: The country or territory code for the UPS accounts pickup address.

BillThirdParty_Address.description: Container for additional information for the third party UPS accounts address.

flattened_text: This component, "BillThirdParty_Address," holds extra details for third-party UPS account addresses. It includes properties for the country code and postal code of the UPS account's pickup address. The country code must be 2 characters long. The postal code varies based on the country: for the US or Puerto Rico, it's 5 or 9 digits with an optional hyphen; for Canada, it's 6 characters in the format A#A#A#, where A is a letter and # is a digit. The postal code is required for US and Canadian UPS accounts or if the account has a postal code.

AccountNumber.description: The UPS account number.  If the Ground Freight Pricing indicator and FreightShipmentInformation/DensityEligibleIndicator is present in the request, this account number must be validated to check if it is Ground Freight Pricing Density Based Rating enabled.

Shipment_FRSPaymentInformation.description: Container to hold the Payment information for the Ground Freight Pricing Shipments.  Required for Ground Freight Pricing Shipments only.

flattened_text: This container holds payment information for Ground Freight Pricing Shipments. It includes the UPS account number, which must be validated if Ground Freight Pricing Density Based Rating is indicated. The container also includes address and type information. The type and account number are required fields.

Code.description:
Valid codes:
- 01 = Prepaid
- 02 = FreightCollect
- 03 = ThirdParty

Description.description: Specifies the description for Ground Freight Pricing payment type.

FRSPaymentInformation_Type.description: Container to hold the Ground Freight Pricing payment type information.  It is required if the request has Ground Freight Pricing shipment indicator.

flattened_text: This component, FRSPaymentInformation_Type, is used to store payment type information for Ground Freight Pricing. It must be included if the request involves Ground Freight Pricing. It includes a Code field with valid options like Prepaid, FreightCollect, and ThirdParty, and a Description field for additional details. The Code field is required and must be a string of 1-2 characters, while the Description field can be up to 50 characters long.

PostalCode.description: The postal code for the Ground Freight Pricing payment information address.

CountryCode.description: The country or territory code for the Ground Freight Pricing payment information address.

FRSPaymentInformation_Address.description: Container to hold the information for the FreightCollect and PrepaidThirdParty Address.  Note: The Address is required only when the billing option is Freight collect or ThirdParty.

flattened_text: This container holds information for the address used in FreightCollect and PrepaidThirdParty billing options. The address includes the Country Code and Postal Code. The Country Code is a 2-character code, and the Postal Code can be up to 9 characters. The Address is required for Freight collect or ThirdParty billing.

DensityEligibleIndicator.description:
The presence of the tag indicates that the rate request is density based.
For Density Based Rating (DBR), the customer must have DBR Contract Service.

Shipment_FreightShipmentInformation.description: Container to hold Freight Shipment information.

flattened_text: This object, "Shipment_FreightShipmentInformation," is a container for holding information about freight shipments. It can only contain one instance. It includes properties like "DensityEligibleIndicator," which indicates if the rate request is density-based, and "FreightDensityInfo," which refers to additional freight density information. The object is named "FreightShipmentInformation" in XML.

AdjustedHeightIndicator.description: The presence of the AdjustedHeightIndicator indicates that allow the height reduction adjustment for density based rate request.

FreightShipmentInformation_FreightDensit.description: Freight Density Info container.  Required if DensityEligibleIndicator is present.

flattened_text: This component, FreightShipmentInformation_FreightDensityInfo, contains information about freight density. It is required when the DensityEligibleIndicator is present. It includes properties such as AdjustedHeight and HandlingUnits. AdjustedHeightIndicator allows for height reduction adjustments for density-based rate requests.

Value.description: Adjusted height value.

FreightDensityInfo_AdjustedHeight.description: Container for the adjusted height.  Required if AdjustedHeightIndicator is present.

flattened_text: This object, FreightDensityInfo_AdjustedHeight, is used to store information about adjusted height. It must be included if the AdjustedHeightIndicator is present. It contains two properties: UnitOfMeasurement and Value. The Value property is a string with a maximum length of 19 characters. Both UnitOfMeasurement and Value are required fields. The object is represented in XML as AdjustedHeight.

Code.description:
Code associated with Unit of Measurement for the Adjusted height.
Valid value: IN  Unit of measurement code for Adjusted height is validated only when Handling unit type is SKD = Skid or PLT = Pallet.

Description.description: Description for UnitOfMeasurement for the adjusted height.

AdjustedHeight_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Container for UnitOfMeasurement for the adjusted height.

flattened_text: This component defines the unit of measurement for the adjusted height. It includes a code (2 characters) and a description (up to 35 characters). The code is validated only for specific handling unit types. The code is required, and the component is represented in XML as "UnitOfMeasurement."

Quantity.description: Handling Unit Quantity for Density based rating.

FreightDensityInfo_HandlingUnits.description: Handling Unit for Density based rating container.

flattened_text: This object defines a handling unit for calculating freight density. It includes dimensions, quantity, and type of handling unit. Quantity must be 8 characters long. The object is required to have a type, quantity, and dimensions.

Code.description:
Handling Unit Code for Density based rating.  Valid values:
- SKD = Skid
- CBY = Carboy
- PLT = Pallet
- TOT = Totes
- LOO = Loose
- OTH = Other

Description.description: A description of the code for the Handling Unit type.

HandlingUnits_Type.description: Handling Unit Type for Density based rating.

flattened_text: This defines a Handling Unit Type for Density based rating. It includes a Code (e.g., SKD for Skid) and a Description of the Handling Unit type. The Code is limited to specific values like SKD, CBY, PLT, TOT, LOO, or OTH. The Description can be up to 35 characters long. The Handling Unit Type is required and can only have one instance.

Length.description: The length of the line item used to determine dimensional weight.

Width.description: The width of the line item used to determine dimensional weight.

Height.description: The height of the line item used to determine dimensional weight.

HandlingUnits_Dimensions.description: Dimension of the HandlingUnit container for density based pricing.

flattened_text: This object defines the dimensions of a handling unit container used for pricing based on density. It includes properties for height, length, width, and unit of measurement. The dimensions are used to calculate dimensional weight for shipping. The object requires values for unit of measurement, length, height, and width.

Code.description: Code for UnitOfMeasurement for the line item dimension. Valid value is IN

Description.description: Description for UnitOfMeasurement for the line item dimension.

flattened_text: This component defines a container for a unit of measurement used for handling units. It includes properties for a code (2 characters long) and a description (up to 35 characters long). The code must be 'IN'. The code property is required.

PromoCode.description: Promotion Code. A discount that is applied to the user.  Required if PromotionalDiscountInformation container is present.

PromoAliasCode.description: Promotion Alias code  Required if PromotionalDiscountInformation container is present.

Shipment_PromotionalDiscountInformation.description: PromotionalDiscountInformation container. This container contains discount information that the customer wants to request each time while placing a shipment.

flattened_text: This object, `Shipment_PromotionalDiscountInformation`, contains discount information that customers can request when placing a shipment. It includes properties for a Promotion Alias code and a Promotion Code, both required when using this container. The Promotion Alias code must be 20 characters long, and the Promotion Code must be 9 characters long.

Name.description:
Name of the person signing the declaration. 

Note: The name of person or department he/she is employed with, are both acceptable.

Title.description:
Title of the person signing the declaration.
Note: The title of the person or department he/she is employed with, are both acceptable.

Date.description: Date of signing the declaration form.  Valid format is YYYYMMDD.

ShipperDeclaration.description:
Valid values:
01 = Shipment level
02 = Package level                                           
  Valid only for the Shipper Declaration paper. If missing or invalid DGPaperImage will be returned at package level.

UploadOnlyIndicator.description: Dangerous Goods Paper Upload Only Indicator. DG Paper will not be returned in response if UploadOnlyIndicator present.

Shipment_DGSignatoryInfo.description: DGSignatoryInfo Container  DGPaperImage will be returned if DGSignatoryInfo container present

flattened_text: This object, `Shipment_DGSignatoryInfo`, contains information about the signatory of a declaration form for dangerous goods. It includes fields for the date of signing, name of the signatory, city, shipper declaration, title, and an indicator for uploading only. The `DGSignatoryInfo` container will return a `DGPaperImage` if present. The fields have specific character limits and formats. The `ShipperDeclaration` field has predefined values for different levels. If the `UploadOnlyIndicator` is present, the response will not include the dangerous goods paper.

NegotiatedRatesIndicator.description:
Negotiated Rates option indicator. If the indicator is present and the Shipper is authorized then Negotiated Rates should be returned in the response.  Negotiated Rates are of two types Account Based Rates (ABR) and Web Discount Rates. Negotiated Rates are only returned for qualified Shipper Account Numbers. 

Eligibility is determined using the combination of UserId and the Shipper's Shipper Account Number. If the user is qualified, both Published rates and Negotiated rates are returned to the user. If the UserId and Shipper Account 

Number are not qualified for Negotiated rates, a warning message is returned that indicates ineligibility and only the Published rates are returned in the response. As per discount eligibility of user, negotiated rates in the response may contain ABR or Web discount rates.

FRSShipmentIndicator.description: Ground Freight Pricing Rates option indicator. If the Ground Freight Pricing Shipment indicator is enabled and Shipper number is authorized then Ground Freight Pricing rates should be returned in the response.  The Shipper account number must be qualified to receive Ground Freight Pricing Density Based Shipment rates. Only the Shipper account number taken from /ShipmentRequest/Shipment/FRSPaymentInformation/AccountNumber is used when checking qualification for Ground Freight Pricing Density Based rates.

RateChartIndicator.description: RateChartIndicator, if present in request, response will contain RateChart element.

TPFCNegotiatedRatesIndicator.description:
This indicator applies for a third party (3P) / Freight collect (FC) shipment only. 

For 3P/FC shipment if the shipper wishes to request for the negotiated rates of the third party then this indicator should be included in the request. 

If authorized the 3P/FC negotiated rates will be applied to the shipment and rates will be returned in response.

UserLevelDiscountIndicator.description:
If this indicator is present user level discount will be applied to rates if applicable  Conditions checked:
This indicator should be present
Shipper number should not be present
User should be eligible for user level discount

flattened_text:
The `Shipment_ShipmentRatingOptions` object contains various indicators for different shipment rating options. 

1. `FRSShipmentIndicator`: Indicates if Ground Freight Pricing rates should be returned based on the Shipper account number.
2. `NegotiatedRatesIndicator`: Determines if Negotiated Rates (ABR or Web Discount Rates) should be returned for qualified Shipper Account Numbers.
3. `RateChartIndicator`: If present, the response will include the RateChart element.
4. `TPFCNegotiatedRatesIndicator`: Applies to third party (3P) / Freight collect (FC) shipments to request negotiated rates for third parties.
5. `UserLevelDiscountIndicator`: Applies user level discounts to rates if specific conditions are met.

BarCodeIndicator.description: If the indicator is present then the reference number's value will be bar coded on the label.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored. Only one shipment-level or package-level reference number can be bar coded per shipment. In order to barcode a reference number, its value must be no longer than 14 alphanumeric characters or 24 numeric characters and cannot contain spaces.

Code.description: Shipment Reference number type code. The code specifies the Reference name. Refer to the Reference Number Code table.  Valid if the origin/destination pair is not US/US or PR/PR and character should be alpha-numeric.

Value.description: Customer supplied reference number.  Valid if the origin/destination pair is not US/US or PR/PR

flattened_text: The Shipment Reference Number contains information about a reference number associated with a shipment. It includes a Bar Code Indicator to specify if the value will be barcoded, a Code to indicate the type of reference number, and a Value which is the customer-supplied reference number. The Value must be provided and can be up to 35 characters long. The Code must be a 2-character alphanumeric code. The Bar Code Indicator is optional and can only be used for one reference number per shipment.

Code.description:
Valid values:
- 01 = Next Day Air
- 02 = 2nd Day Air
- 03 = Ground
- 07 = Express
- 08 = Expedited
- 11 = UPS Standard
- 12 = 3 Day Select
- 13 = Next Day Air Saver
- 14 = UPS Next Day Air® Early
- 17 = UPS Worldwide Economy DDU
- 54 = Express Plus
- 59 = 2nd Day Air A.M.
- 65 = UPS Saver
- M2 = First Class Mail
- M3 = Priority Mail
- M4 = Expedited MaiI Innovations
- M5 = Priority Mail Innovations
- M6 = Economy Mail Innovations
- M7 = MaiI Innovations (MI) Returns
- 70 = UPS Access Point™ Economy
- 71 = UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday
- 72 = UPS Worldwide Economy DDP
- 74 = UPS Express®12:00
- 75 = UPS Heavy Goods
- 82 = UPS Today Standard
- 83 = UPS Today Dedicated Courier
- 84 = UPS Today Intercity
- 85 = UPS Today Express
- 86 = UPS Today Express Saver
- 96 = UPS Worldwide Express Freight.
- C6 = Roadie XD AM (Morning delivery)
- C7 = Roadie XD PM (Afternoon delivery)
- C8 = Roadie XD (Anytime delivery)

Note: Only service code 03 is used for Ground Freight Pricing shipments  The following Services are not available to return shipment: 13, 59, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86, C6, C7, C8

Description.description: Description of the service code. Examples are Next Day Air, Worldwide Express, and Ground.

flattened_text: The Shipment Service API defines UPS service types for shipping. It includes a service code with valid values like Next Day Air and Ground, each with a corresponding description. The service code is a string with a maximum length of 2 characters. The description is a string with a maximum length of 35 characters. Ground service (code 03) is used for Ground Freight Pricing shipments. Some services are not available for return shipments.

CurrencyCode.description: Invoice Line Total currency type.

MonetaryValue.description: Invoice Line Total amount for the entire shipment.  Valid values are from 1 to 99999999

Shipment_InvoiceLineTotal.description: Container to hold InvoiceLineTotal Information.  Required for forward shipments whose origin is the US and destination is Puerto Rico or Canada. Not available for any other shipments. FOR OTHER DESTINATIONS the InvoiceLineTotal in the International Forms Container must be used.

flattened_text: This container, "Shipment_InvoiceLineTotal," is used for forward shipments from the US to Puerto Rico or Canada. It contains information about the total invoice amount in a specific currency. The container includes properties for the currency code and the monetary value, with specific length and value constraints. Both the currency code and monetary value are required fields. This container is not applicable for shipments to other destinations, where a different container should be used.

Code.description:
Valid values:
- '01' - Hold for Pickup at UPS Access Point aka Direct to Retail (D2R)
- '02' - UPS Access Point™ Delivery aka Retail to Retail (R2R)  If '01' code is present indicates shipment will be send to Retail location where it is held to consignee to claim.

Description.description: Description for the code.

Shipment_ShipmentIndicationType.description: Container for Shipment Indication Type.  Required to indicate whether shipment is "Hold For Pickup At UPS Access Point" for use by approved shippers to identify a UPS Access Point location as an alternate delivery option during shipment preparation or "UPS Access Point™ Delivery", ship parcels directly to a UPS Access Point location for collection by the receiver.

flattened_text: This object, `Shipment_ShipmentIndicationType`, is used to specify if a shipment is for "Hold For Pickup At UPS Access Point" or "UPS Access Point Delivery". It contains a `Code` property with values '01' for Hold for Pickup and '02' for UPS Access Point Delivery, and a `Description` property for additional information. The `Code` property is required and has a maximum length of 2 characters.

SaturdayDeliveryIndicator.description: Saturday delivery indicator. The presence indicates Saturday delivery is requested and the absence indicates Saturday delivery is not requested.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored.

SaturdayPickupIndicator.description: Saturday pickup indicator. The presence indicates Saturday pickup is requested and the absence indicates Saturday pickup is not requested.  This is an empty tag, any value inside is ignored.

DeliverToAddresseeOnlyIndicator.description: Presence/Absence Indicator. Any value inside is ignored. DeliverToAddresseeOnlyIndicator is shipper specified restriction that requires the addressee to be the one who takes final delivery of the "Hold For PickUp at UPS Access Point" package. Presence of indicator means shipper restriction will apply to the shipment.  Only valid for Shipment Indication type "01 - Hold For PickUp at UPS Access Point".

DirectDeliveryOnlyIndicator.description: Presence/Absence Indicator. Any value inside is ignored. Direct Delivery Only (DDO) accessorial in a request would ensure that delivery is made only to the ship to address on the shipping label. This accessorial is not valid with Shipment Indication Type "01 - Hold For Pickup At UPS Access Point" and "02 - UPS Access Point™ Delivery".

ReturnOfDocumentIndicator.description: The flag indicates the ReturnOfDocument accessorial has been requested.  Valid for Poland to Poland forward shipment only.

ImportControlIndicator.description: Indicates that the Shipment is an ImportControl shipment.

CommercialInvoiceRemovalIndicator.description: CommercialInvoiceRemovalIndicator allows a shipper to dictate UPS to remove the Commercial Invoice from the user's shipment before the shipment is delivered to the ultimate consignee.

UPScarbonneutralIndicator.description: UPS carbon neutral indicator presence at shipment level is required to create carbon neutral Shipments.

ExchangeForwardIndicator.description: Exchange forward indicator presence at shipment level is required to create exchange forward Shipments.  In the label routing Instruction text will be defaulted to "EXCHANGE-LIKE ITEM ONLY".

HoldForPickupIndicator.description: Hold For Pickup indicator. The empty tag means indicator is present.  This accessorial is only valid for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday Shipment.

DropoffAtUPSFacilityIndicator.description: Drop off At UPS Facility indicator. The empty tag means indicator is present.  This accessorial is only valid for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday Shipment.

LiftGateForPickUpIndicator.description:
Lift Gate For Pick Up indicator. The empty tag means indicator is present.  Lift Gate for Pickup is not allowed with Drop Off At UPS Facility for a UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday shipment.
