When both Hold for Pickup and Drop Off At Facility are selected, neither of the Lift Gate accessorial (Pick Up or Delivery) are allowed for a UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday shipment. 

This accessorial is only valid for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday Shipment.

LiftGateForDeliveryIndicator.description:
Lift Gate For Delivery indicator. The empty tag means indicator is present.  Lift Gate for Delivery is not allowed with Hold For Pickup for a UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday shipment. 

When both Hold for Pickup and Drop Off At UPS Facility are selected, neither of the Lift Gate accessorial (Pick Up or Delivery) are allowed for a UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday shipment. 

This accessorial is only valid for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Midday Shipment.

SDLShipmentIndicator.description: The presence of the tag SDLShipmentIndicator indicates Shipment is SDL. SDLShipmentIndicator presence means EEI form/ EEI Filing option required.

EPRAReleaseCode.description: Package Release code allows the consignee or claimant to pick-up a package at a UPS Access Point™. The shipper must provide the Package Release Code to the consignee so that they can provide the code to the UPS Access Point personnel as another item for authentication before the package is released to them. Package Release Code is only valid with ShipmentIndicationType 01 - Hold for Pickup at UPS Access Point™.  The release code must be between length 4 and 6 and only contain numbers.

InsideDelivery.description:
Inside delivery accessory. Valid values:
01 - White Glove,
02 - Room of Choice,
03 - Installation,
04 - Over Threshold Fee.
Default is Room of Choice.  Shippers account needs to have a valid contract for Heavy Goods Service.

ItemDisposal.description: Presence/Absence indicator. True if present; false otherwise. Any value is ignored. If present, indicates that the customer would like items disposed.  Shippers account needs to have a valid contract for Heavy Goods Service.

flattened_text: This section defines various options for shipping services. It includes options like removing commercial invoices, specifying delivery restrictions, indicating special handling requirements, and requesting specific delivery or pickup days. Each option has specific rules and restrictions based on the type of shipment. Some options are only valid for certain types of shipments or require specific contracts with the shipping provider.

CODFundsCode.description: For valid values refer to: Rating and Shipping COD Supported Countries or Territories in the Appendix.

ShipmentServiceOptions_COD.description: COD container  Indicates COD is requested. Shipment COD is only available for EU origin countries or territories and for shippers account type Daily Pickup and Drop Shipping. Not available to shipment with return service.

flattened_text: The ShipmentServiceOptions_COD object represents the option to request Cash on Delivery (COD) for shipments. COD is available for EU origin countries or territories with Daily Pickup or Drop Shipping accounts. This option is not available for shipments with return service. The object includes properties for CODAmount and CODFundsCode, with specific requirements for CODFundsCode values.

CurrencyCode.description: COD amount currency code type.

MonetaryValue.description: COD Amount monetary value.

flattened_text: This component defines a COD (Cash on Delivery) amount, including the currency code and monetary value. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value is a 5-character string. Both properties are required.

CurrencyCode.description: Access Point COD Currency Code.

MonetaryValue.description: Access Point COD Monetary Value.

ShipmentServiceOptions_AccessPointCOD.description:
Access Point COD indicates COD is requested for a shipment.  Valid only for "01 - Hold For Pickup At UPS Access Point" Shipment Indication type. Shipment Access Point COD is valid only for countries or territories within E.U. 
Not valid with (Shipment) COD. 
Not available to shipment with return service.

flattened_text: This service option, "Access Point COD," allows requesting cash on delivery for a shipment. It is only valid for shipments held for pickup at a UPS Access Point within the E.U. This option cannot be used with regular COD or for shipments with return service. It requires specifying the currency code and monetary value for the COD.

NotificationCode.description:
The type of notification requested.

Note:
- QVN Exception notification and return notification are not applicable to GFP.
- QV In-transit and Return Notifications are only valid for ImportControl and Return shipment.
- QV In-transit Notification is allowed for return shipments only.
- QV Ship Notification is allowed for forward moving shipments only.

Valid values:
- 5 - QV In-transit Notification
- 6 - QV Ship Notification
- 7 - QV Exception Notification
- 8 - QV Delivery Notification
- 2 - Return Notification or Label Creation Notification
- 012 - Alternate Delivery Location Notification
- 013 - UAP Shipper Notification.

ShipmentServiceOptions_Notification.description: Container for the Quantum View Notification (QVN) is valid for all shipments including Return service, Import Control and Returns Flexible Access.  Valid return service types are: ERL, PRL, PNM, RS1, or RS3.   The shipment level notification is valid for forward and return international shipments as well as for domestic shipments (for US and PR).

flattened_text: The ShipmentServiceOptions_Notification object is used for Quantum View Notification (QVN) for various types of shipments, including returns and international shipments. It allows for different types of notifications such as in-transit, exception, delivery, and return notifications. The object includes properties for email, locale, notification code, text message, and voice message. The NotificationCode property specifies the type of notification requested, with specific valid values. The object is required to have NotificationCode and Email properties.

EMailAddress.description: Email address where the notification is sent.  Up to five email addresses are allowed for each type of Quantum View TM shipment notification. Up to two email address for return notification.

UndeliverableEMailAddress.description: The address where an undeliverable eMail message is sent if the eMail with the notification is undeliverable.  There can be only one UndeliverableEMailAddress for each shipment with Quantum View Shipment Notifications.

FromEMailAddress.description: The e-mail address specifies the Reply To E-mail address. The "From" field of the message header contains pkginfo@ups.com.  Valid for Return Notification only.

FromName.description: The name the email will appear to be from. Defaults to the Shipper Name.  The FromName must occur only once for each shipment with Quantum View Shipment Notifications.

Memo.description: User defined text that will be included in the eMail.  The Memo must occur only once for each shipment with Quantum View Shipment Notifications.

flattened_text: The Notification Email object contains information for sending email notifications related to Quantum View shipments. It includes fields for the recipient email address, reply-to email address, sender name, user-defined memo, and undeliverable email address. Each shipment notification can have up to five recipient email addresses and one each for the other fields. The object is required to have an email address and is represented in XML as "EMail."

PhoneNumber.description: Phone number for receiving Voice Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification.

Notification_VoiceMessage.description: VoiceMessage container is used for specifying phone number for receiving voice Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification.  Valid only for Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification. VoiceMessage phone number or TextMessage phone number or email address is required for ADL notification and UAP Shipper notification.

flattened_text: The `Notification_VoiceMessage` object is used to specify a phone number for receiving voice notifications for Alternate Delivery Location and UAP Shipper. It is required for these notifications. The `PhoneNumber` property within this object is a string with a maximum length of 15 characters.

PhoneNumber.description: Phone number for receiving Text Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification.

Notification_TextMessage.description: TextMessage container is used for specifying phone number for receiving text Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification.  Valid only for Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification. VoiceMessage phone number or TextMessage phone number or email address is required for ADL notification and UAP Shipper notification.

flattened_text: This object, "Notification_TextMessage," is used to specify a phone number for receiving text notifications for Alternate Delivery Location and UAP Shipper. It is required for these notifications. The phone number must be a string with a maximum length of 15 characters.

Language.description: Refer to Language/Dialect Combinations in the Appendix for valid pairs.

Dialect.description: Refer to Language/Dialect Combinations in the Appendix for valid pairs.

Notification_Locale.description: This container is used for providing Language and dialect details for Alternate Delivery Location notifications and UAP Shipper notifications.  Valid only for Alternate Delivery Location notification and UAP Shipper notification.

flattened_text: This container, "Notification Locale," is used to specify language and dialect details for notifications related to alternate delivery locations and UAP shippers. It contains properties for "Dialect" and "Language," with specific length requirements. Both properties are required.

LabelLinksIndicator.description: Indicates the Label and Receipt URLs are to be returned in the XML response.

ShipmentServiceOptions_LabelDelivery.description: Container for the Label Delivery accessorial. Note - LabelDelivery is not applicable for GFP and Mail Innovations Forward shipment.  Required for shipments with either Electronic Return Label Return Service or ImportControl Electronic LabelMethod type. Optional for shipments with Print Return Label Return Service or ImportControl Print LabelMethod type or Forward movement.  If this container is present for shipments with either Electronic Return Label Return Service or ImportControl Electronic LabelMethod type, either of the LabelLinksIndicator or EMail container should be provided. For shipments with Print Return Label Return Service or ImportControl Print LabelMethod type or Forward movement, only LabelLinksIndicator is valid option for LabelDelivery container.

flattened_text: This section defines the options for label delivery in the shipment service. It specifies that the Label Delivery feature is not available for certain types of shipments. It outlines the requirements for different label methods and indicates when specific containers should be provided. The options include providing an email address or indicating that label and receipt URLs should be returned in the XML response.

EMailAddress.description: The destination eMail address for the Label Delivery.

UndeliverableEMailAddress.description: The address where an undeliverable email message is sent if the Label Delivery email is undeliverable.  Defaults to FromEMailAddress.

FromEMailAddress.description: The e-mail address specifies the Reply To E-mail address. The "From" field of the message header contains pkginfo@ups.com.

FromName.description: The "FrontName" is the name from which notification will appear. Defaults to the "Shipper Name".

Memo.description: User defined text that will be included in the email.

Subject.description: The eMails subject. Defaults to the Label Delivery Notification plus the shipment ID. Defaults to text provided by UPS.

SubjectCode.description:
Specifies a reference code and reference number to display in the subject of the Label Delivery notification.

When the subject code is provided, the subject will contain the following: UPS Label Delivery, the reference code (the reference code will be mapped to the corresponding ANSI value) and the reference number.

The valid subject codes are:
- 01 - Shipment Reference Number 1,
- 02 - Shipment Reference Number 2,
- 03 - package Reference Number 1,
- 04 - package Reference Number 2,
- 05 - package Reference Number 3,
- 06 - package Reference Number 4,
- 07 - package Reference Number 5,
- 08 - Subject Text (Return Notification only).

If the subject code tag is not provided and the subject text is provided, the subject of the notification will be the subject text.

If the subject text is provided, and the subject code tag exists, then the subject code value must be 08. If Subject code is 08, subject text must exist. If a subject code is provided that refers to a nonexistent reference number, the subject will default to the shipment identification number.

flattened_text: The `LabelDelivery_EMail` object contains information for sending an email notification about label delivery. It includes fields for the recipient's email address, reply-to email address, sender name, custom message, email subject, reference code, and undeliverable email address. Some fields have default values. The `SubjectCode` field allows specifying a reference code and number to display in the email subject. The `UndeliverableEMailAddress` field determines where undeliverable email notifications are sent. The `EMailAddress` field is required.

FormType.description:
Indicates the name of the International Form requested.

Valid values:
- 01 - Invoice
- 03 - CO
- 04 - NAFTA CO
- 05 - Partial Invoice
- 06 - Packinglist
- 07 - Customer Generated Forms
- 08 – Air Freight Packing List
- 09 - CN22 Form
- 10 – UPS Premium Care Form
- 11 - EEI

For shipment with return service, 05 or 10 are the only valid values.

Note: 01 and 05 are mutually exclusive and 05 are only valid for return shipments only.

AdditionalDocumentIndicator.description:
Presence of the indicator means user will supply additional document, such as EEI, NAFTA_CO or CO.  This indicator should be set when the shipper intends to utilize UPS paperless invoice functionality AND the shipper has SELF-PREPARED other International Forms (EEI, CO, NAFTACO) to accompany the shipment. 
It is evaluated only when: 
1. Account is paperless enabled. 
2. Movement requires an invoice.
3. Destination country or territory accepts paperless invoice. 
4. Invoice data is supplied by the client and the data passes validation.

FormGroupIdName.description: Contains description text which identifies the group of International forms. This element does not appear on the forms.

InvoiceNumber.description: Commercial Invoice number assigned by the exporter.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice.

InvoiceDate.description: Date when the Invoice is created. Ideally this is the same as the ship date.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Required for Invoice form for forward shipments. For shipment with return service, the user input will be ignored, and the field will be blank on the invoice. Format is yyyyMMdd.

PurchaseOrderNumber.description: The customer's order reference number.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

TermsOfShipment.description:
Indicates the rights to the seller from the buyer. Also, it refers to Terms of Sale.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. 

Valid values: 
CFR: Cost and Freight 
CIF: Cost Insurance and Freight 
CIP: Carriage and Insurance Paid 
CPT: Carriage Paid To 
DAF: Delivered at Frontier 
DDP: Delivery Duty Paid 
DDU: Delivery Duty Unpaid 
DEQ: Delivered Ex Quay 
DES: Delivered Ex Ship 
EXW: Ex Works 
FAS: Free Alongside Ship 
FCA: Free Carrier 
FOB: Free On Board

ReasonForExport.description:
A reason to export the current international shipment.
Valid values: SALE, GIFT, SAMPLE, RETURN, REPAIR, INTERCOMPANYDATA, Any other reason.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and Optional for Partial Invoice. No validation.

Comments.description: Any extra information about the current shipment.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

DeclarationStatement.description: This is the legal explanation, used by Customs, for the delivering of this shipment. It must be identical to the set of declarations actually used by Customs. Examples of declarations that might be entered in this field are: I hereby certify that the goods covered by this shipment qualify as originating goods for purposes of preferential tariff treatment under the NAFTA. I hereby certify that the information on this invoice is true and correct and the contents and value of this shipment is as stated above.  EEA statement:  The exporter of the products covered by this document declares that except where otherwise clearly indicated these products are of EEA preferential origin.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. On the invoice for return shipment, the verbiage is as follows (user input is ignored): The exporter of the products covered by this document declares that except where otherwise clearly indicated these products are of EEA preferential origin

CurrencyCode.description: Currency code for all the monetary values of the Invoice form.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

ExportDate.description: The date the goods will be exiting the country or territory.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only. Required for CO and EEI forms. Format is yyyyMMdd.

ExportingCarrier.description:
The name of the carrier that is exporting the shipment. The vessels flag number should also be entered, if the carrier is a vessel.

If value is empty, it will be set to default value as 'UPS' for EEI forms.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only. Required for CO forms.

CarrierID.description: The four-character Standard Carrier Alpha Code (SCAC) for vessel, rail, and truck shipments. For air shipment, enter the two or three character International Air Transport Association (IATA) code.  Applies to EEI forms only. No Validations.

InBondCode.description: The two-character In Bond Code.  Applies to EEI forms only. Required for EEI forms. Valid values for EEI are: 70: Not in bond; 67: IE from a FTZ; 68: T&E from a FTZ.

EntryNumber.description: The Import Entry Number when the export transaction is used as proof of export for import transactions (examples: In Bond, Temporary Import Bond or Drawbacks).  Applies to EEI forms only. Conditionally Required for EEI forms when In bond code value is other than 70 (Not In Bond)

PointOfOrigin.description: Contains one of the following:  The two-digit U.S. Postal Service abbreviation for the state from which the goods were shipped to the port of export. The state that is the source for the good with the highest value. The state of consolidation. The Foreign Trade Zone number of the zone from where the exports are leaving.  If the goods were shipped from Puerto Rico, enter PR.  Applies to EEI forms only. Required for EEI.

PointOfOriginType.description: Valid values are : S (for state postal code abbreviation) , F : FTZ Identifier  Applies EEI forms only. Required for EEI form.

ModeOfTransport.description: Mode of transport by which the goods are exported. Valid values: Air, AirContainerized, Auto, FixedTransportInstallations, Mail, PassengerHandcarried, Pedestrian, Rail, Rail, Containerized, RoadOther, SeaBarge, SeaContainerized, SeaNoncontainerized, Truck, TruckContainerized.  Applies to EEI forms only.  Required for EEI.  Only allowed values can be entered. Only 10 Characters can appear on the form. Anything greater than 10 characters will be truncated on the form.

PortOfExport.description: Should be one of the following-Overland: The U.S. Customs port where the carrier crosses the U.S. border, Vessel and Air: The U.S. Customs port where the goods are loaded on the carrier to be exported from the U.S., Postal: The U.S. Postal Office from where the goods are mailed.  Applies to EEI forms only. No validation is performed.

PortOfUnloading.description: The country or territory and the port where the goods will be unloaded from the exporting carrier. For vessel and air shipments only.  Applies to EEI forms only. No validation is performed.

LoadingPier.description: Pier where goods are loaded. For vessel shipments only.  Applies to EEI forms only. No validation is performed.

PartiesToTransaction.description:
Information about parties to transaction. Use Related, if the parties to the transaction are related. A related party is an export from a U.S. businessperson or business to a foreign business or from a U.S. business to a foreign person or business where the person has at least 10 percent of the voting shares of the business during the fiscal year. If unincorporated, then an equivalent interest in the business.  Applies to EEI forms only.

Valid values:
- R - Related
- N - Non-related.

Parties to transaction is required if EEIFilingOption Code is 3 and if valid UPSFiled POA Code present in request.

Default will be set to N - Non-related if invalid code present with length of one.

RoutedExportTransactionIndicator.description: If Present, indicates that it is a routed export transaction. A routed export transaction is one, where the foreign principal party in interest authorizes a U.S. forwarding (or other) agent to export the merchandise outside the U.S.  Applies to EEI forms only.

ContainerizedIndicator.description: If present indicates that the goods are containerized. This applies to vessel shipments only.  Applies to EEI forms only.

OverridePaperlessIndicator.description: The application will automatically provide a copy of the invoice or NAFTA/CO with each response regardless of whether the user has enabled Paperless account. The user now has the option to print or ignore the copy provided.

ShipperMemo.description: Text for the shipper to add additional information.  Forward shipment only.

HazardousMaterialsIndicator.description: This is an empty tag. Presence of the indicator for EEI form means shipment contains hazardous material.

flattened_text: This section defines the data structure for international forms in a shipment service. It includes details like additional document indicators, carrier information, currency codes, declaration statements, and more. The required fields are FormType and Product. The data structure is organized as an object named InternationalForms.

DocumentID.description: DocumentID represents a document uploaded to Forms History.

InternationalForms_UserCreatedForm.description: Data container for DocumentID(s).  Required if Form Type is 07.

flattened_text: This data container is used for storing DocumentID(s) related to user-created forms. It is required when the form type is 07. The DocumentID represents a document uploaded to the Forms History and must be a string of maximum length 26 characters. The container is an object named UserCreatedForm.

ShipmentDate.description: Shipment Date associated with UPS Premium Care Shipment.   Valid Format: yyyyMMdd

PageSize.description:
Size of UPS Premium Care Form.  Valid values: 
01 = A4 Size
02 = Letter Size

PrintType.description:
Format of UPS Premium Care Form.  Valid values: 
01 = PNG
02 = PDF

NumOfCopies.description: Number of Copies of UPS Premium Care Form.  Valid value is 02.

InternationalForms_UPSPremiumCareForm.description: UPS Premium Care Form is required if UPS Premium Care Indicator is present on a package.  Valid only for Canada to Canada movements.

flattened_text: The UPS Premium Care Form is needed when a package has the UPS Premium Care Indicator and is only valid for shipments within Canada. This form includes fields for the language, number of copies (must be 2), page size (A4 or Letter), print type (PNG or PDF), and shipment date (format: yyyyMMdd). All fields are required.

Language.description:
Languages for UPS Premium Care Form. Two languages are required for UPS Premium Care Form.   Valid values: 
eng = US English
fra = Canadian French

UPSPremiumCareForm_LanguageForUPSPremium.description: Container to hold languages in which UPS Premium Care Form is required.

flattened_text: This object holds the languages required for the UPS Premium Care Form. Two languages are needed, with valid values being US English (eng) and Canadian French (fra). The object is an array with a maximum length of 2, and the language field is required.

LabelSize.description:
Provide the valid values: 
6 = 4X6
1 = 8.5X11
  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

PrintsPerPage.description: Number of label per page. Currently 1 per page is supported.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

LabelPrintType.description:
Valid Values are pdf, png, gif, zpl, star, epl2 and spl.
  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22Type.description:
Valid values: 
1 = GIFT
2 = DOCUMENTS
3 = COMMERCIAL SAMPLE
4 = OTHER  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22OtherDescription.description: Required if CN22Type is OTHER.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

FoldHereText.description: String will replace default "Fold Here" text displayed on the label.

InternationalForms_CN22Form.description: Container for the CN22 form.  Required if the customer wants to use the UPS generated CN22.

flattened_text: The `InternationalForms_CN22Form` object is a container for the CN22 form used in shipping. It includes properties like CN22 content, description, type, fold text, label print type, label size, and prints per page. Some properties are required based on the form type. The object can only have a maximum of 1 instance. The required properties include LabelPrintType, CN22Type, LabelSize, PrintsPerPage, and CN22Content.

CN22ContentQuantity.description: Total number of items associated with this content.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22ContentDescription.description:
Detailed description of the content.

If the combined MI package and CN22 label is requested, only the first 30 characters will appear on the combined label.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22ContentTotalValue.description: Total value of the items associated with this content.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22ContentCurrencyCode.description: Currently only USD is supported.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

CN22ContentCountryOfOrigin.description: Country or Territory of Origin from where the CN22 contents originated.

CN22ContentTariffNumber.description: The tariff number associated with the CN22 contents.

CN22Form_CN22Content.description:
Container for CN22 content.  Required if the CN22 form container is present. 
Note: The maximum number of goods printed on the CN22 form when a combined MI package and CN22 form label is requested is 30.

flattened_text: The `CN22Form_CN22Content` object is a container for CN22 form content. It must be included if the CN22 form container is present. Key properties include the country of origin, currency code (currently only USD is supported), description, quantity, tariff number, total value, and weight of the items. Note that when a combined MI package and CN22 label is requested, only the first 30 characters of the description will appear on the label. The maximum number of goods printed on the CN22 form is 30. The object is required to have currency code, total value, description, weight, and quantity.

Weight.description: Total weight of the content. Pounds and Ounces are allowed up to 2 decimals.  Required if the CN22 form container is present.

flattened_text: This object represents the weight of CN22 content. It includes the unit of measurement and the total weight of the content, which must be in pounds and ounces with up to 2 decimals. The weight is required if the CN22 form container is present.

Code.description: Required if weight is provided, valid values are lbs. and ozs.  Required if weight is provided.

Description.description: Short description for UnitOfMeasurement.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for the weight of CN22 content. It includes properties for the unit code (lbs. or ozs.) and a short description. The unit code is required if weight is provided. The description is limited to 50 characters. The unit of measurement is represented as an object in XML with the name "UnitOfMeasurement."

Code.description:
Required for EEI Form.  Applicable for EEI form.
Valid values: 
1 - Shipper filed,
2 - AES Direct, 
3 - UPS filed.

EMailAddress.description: Email Address where the notification is sent. Valid for UPS filed (option 3), Shipper filed (option 1- A , 1-C)  Applicable for EEI form.

Description.description: Optional Description of Filing Code.  Applicable for EEI form.

InternationalForms_EEIFilingOption.description: EEI Filing option.  Applicable for EEI form and is required.

flattened_text: This component defines options for filing an EEI form. It includes a code (1, 2, or 3) indicating the filing method, a brief description, an email address for notifications (for certain methods), and references to specific filing options for shippers and UPS. The code is required, and the description is optional. The maximum lengths for the description and email address are specified.

EEIFilingOption_UPSFiled.description: Indicates the EEI UPS Filed option. (option 3)  Applicable for EEI form.

flattened_text: This section defines the EEI Filing Option for UPS Filed, which is option 3 on the EEI form. It includes the property POA, which references the UPS Filed Power of Attorney schema. The POA property is required and the object is named UPSFiled.

Code.description: Indicates the EEI UPS Filed POA filing option.  Applicable for EEI form. Valid values are 1- One Time POA; 2- Blanket POA.

Description.description: Description for POA Code.  Applicable for EEI form.

UPSFiled_POA.description: Container for POA.  Applicable for EEI form.

flattened_text: This object, UPSFiled_POA, is used for the Power of Attorney (POA) information required for the EEI form. It can only have one instance. It includes two properties: Code (with values 1 or 2 for different POA types) and Description. The Code property is a string with a maximum length of 1 character, while the Description property is a string with a maximum length of 20 characters. The Code property is mandatory.

Code.description: Indicates the EEI Shipper sub option.  Applicable for EEI form and is required. Valid value is: A- requires the ITN; B- requires the Exemption Legend; C- requires the post departure filing citation.

Description.description: Description of ShipperFiled Code.  Applicable for EEI form.

PreDepartureITNNumber.description: Input for Shipper Filed option A and AES Direct. The format is available from AESDirect website.  Valid and Required for Shipper Filed option A. EEI form only.

EEIShipmentReferenceNumber.description: Shipment Reference Number for use during interaction with AES. Valid for EEI form for Shipper Filed option 'C' and AES Direct Filed.

EEIFilingOption_ShipperFiled.description: Indicates the EEI Shipper Filed option or AES Direct. (Option 1 or 2).  Applicable for EEI form.

flattened_text: This section defines options for filing EEI (Electronic Export Information) in shipping documents. It includes codes for different filing methods (A, B, C), a description for each code, a shipment reference number, exemption legends, and ITN numbers. These details are required for EEI forms and AES Direct filings.

InternationalForms_Contacts.description: Holds the contact information of various parties.  Applicable for EEI and NAFTA CO only. Required for NAFTA CO and EEI. Ultimate consignee contact information is required for EEI.  Producer contact information is required for NAFTA CO

flattened_text: This section, "InternationalForms_Contacts," stores contact details for different parties. It is used for EEI and NAFTA CO forms. Required for NAFTA CO and EEI forms. EEI form needs Ultimate Consignee contact info. NAFTA CO form needs Producer contact info. Contains properties for Forward Agent, Intermediate Consignee, Producer, Sold To, and Ultimate Consignee.

CompanyName.description: Company Name or the Individual name of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

TaxIdentificationNumber.description:
Tax ID of the Forwarding agent.
Valid Values: (Below values are applicable for EEIFilingOption Code =3)
94-308351500 
13-168669100  
  Applicable for EEI form only.

Contacts_ForwardAgent.description: The forwarding agent is the company or person acting as agent in the trans-shipping of freight to the destination country or territory.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: This component defines the forwarding agent for trans-shipping freight to a destination country. It includes the agent's address, company name or individual name, and tax identification number. This information is required for the EEI form.

AddressLine.description: Address line of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

City.description: City of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

StateProvinceCode.description: State of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

Town.description: Town of the Forwarding Agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

PostalCode.description: Postal code of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only. Required for certain countries or territories. The length of the postal code depends on the country or territory code

CountryCode.description: Country or Territory code of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

ForwardAgent_Address.description: Address information of the Forwarding agent.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: This object represents the address information of a Forwarding agent for the EEI form. It includes AddressLine, City, CountryCode, PostalCode, StateProvinceCode, and Town. AddressLine is an array of up to 3 strings with a max length of 35 characters each. City, CountryCode, PostalCode, StateProvinceCode, and Town are strings with specific length constraints. PostalCode length varies based on the country code. AddressLine, City, and CountryCode are required fields.

CompanyName.description: Company Name or the Individual name of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

Contacts_UltimateConsignee.description: The ultimate consignee is the person or company who receives the goods for end-use or the person or company listed on the export license. This is the end-user of the goods.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: The "Contacts_UltimateConsignee" object represents the ultimate consignee, who is the recipient of goods for end-use or as listed on the export license. This is the end-user of the goods and is applicable for the EEI form. It includes properties such as Address and CompanyName (maximum 35 characters), and UltimateConsigneeType. CompanyName and Address are required fields.

AddressLine.description: Address line of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

City.description: City of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

StateProvinceCode.description: State of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only. Required for certain countries or territories. The length of the postal code depends on the country or territory code

Town.description: Town of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

PostalCode.description: Postal code of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only. Required for certain countries or territories. The length of the postal code depends on the country or territory code.

CountryCode.description: Country or Territory code of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

UltimateConsignee_Address.description: Address information of the Ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: The "UltimateConsignee_Address" object contains address details for the ultimate consignee, specifically for the EEI form. It includes AddressLine, City, CountryCode, PostalCode, StateProvinceCode, and Town fields. Some fields have specific length requirements. AddressLine is an array of up to 3 strings with a max length of 35 characters each. CountryCode is a 2-character string. PostalCode and StateProvinceCode have varying length requirements based on the country or territory code. Certain fields are required.

Code.description:
Ultimate Consignee Type Code.   Applicable for EEI form only.

Valid values:  
D =  Direct Consumer 
G = Government Entity
R = Reseller
O = Other/Unknown

Description.description: Ultimate Consignee Type Description.  Applicable for EEI form only.

UltimateConsignee_UltimateConsigneeType.description: Container for providing UltimateConsignee Type.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: This section defines the UltimateConsigneeType object, used in the EEI form. It includes properties for Code (with valid values: D, G, R, O) and Description. The Code property is a single character, while the Description property can be up to 20 characters long. The Code property is required.

CompanyName.description: Company Name or the Individual name of the Intermediate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

Contacts_IntermediateConsignee.description: The intermediate consignee is the person or company in the importing country or territory that makes final delivery to the ultimate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: This component defines the intermediate consignee for the EEI form. The intermediate consignee is the entity in the importing country that delivers goods to the final recipient. It includes properties for the address and company name of the intermediate consignee. The company name must be a string with a maximum length of 35 characters. Both the company name and address are required fields.

AddressLine.description: Address line of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

City.description: City of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

StateProvinceCode.description: State of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only. Required for certain countries or territories.

Town.description: Town of the Intermediate consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

PostalCode.description: Postal code of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only. Required for certain countries or territories. The length of the postal code depends on the country or territory code.

CountryCode.description: Country or Territory code of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

IntermediateConsignee_Address.description: Address information of the Intermediate Consignee.  Applicable for EEI form only.

flattened_text: This section defines the address details of the Intermediate Consignee for the EEI form. It includes Address Line, City, Country Code, Postal Code, State/Province Code, and Town. Certain fields are required based on the country or territory. The address information is structured as an object named "Address" in the XML.

Option.description:
The text associated with the code will be printed in the producer section instead of producer contact information. 
Use attached List if more than one producer's good is included on the Certificate, attach a list of additional producers, including the legal name, address (including country or territory), and legal tax identification number, cross-referenced to the goods described in the Description of Goods field.  Applies to NAFTA CO.  
Valid values: 
01 - AVAILABLE TO CUSTOMS UPON REQUEST
02 - SAME AS EXPORTER
03 - ATTACHED LIST
04 - UNKNOWN

CompanyName.description: Company Name or the Individual name of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO.  Only applicable when producer option is empty or not present. Conditionally required for: NAFTA CO, when Producer option is not specified.

TaxIdentificationNumber.description: Tax ID of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO. Only applicable when producer option is empty or not present

AttentionName.description: Contact name at the Producer location.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

EMailAddress.description: Producer email address.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

Contacts_Producer.description:
Information of the producer. The NAFTA Certificate of Origin must be completed, signed, and dated by the exporter. 
When the Certificate is completed by the producer for use by the exporter, it must be completed, signed, and dated by the producer. The date must be the date the Certificate was completed and signed.  Applies to NAFTA CO.  Required for NAFTA CO forms.

flattened_text: This section defines the information needed for the producer in the context of the NAFTA Certificate of Origin. It includes details like the producer's address, contact name, company name, email address, tax identification number, and phone number. There is also an option to include a specific text code instead of the producer's contact information. The producer's information is crucial for completing the NAFTA CO form accurately.

AddressLine.description: Address line of the Producer.

City.description: City of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO. Conditionally required for: NAFTA CO, when Producer option is not specified.

StateProvinceCode.description: State of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO. Required for certain countries or territories.

PostalCode.description: Postal code of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO. Required for certain countries or territories. The length of the postal code depends on the country or territory code.

CountryCode.description: Country or Territory code of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

Producer_Address.description: Address information of the Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO. Only applicable if producer option is empty or not present. Conditionally required for: NAFTA CO, when Producer option is not specified.

flattened_text: This section defines the address information of the Producer for NAFTA CO. It includes details like AddressLine, City, CountryCode, PostalCode, StateProvinceCode, and Town. Certain fields are required based on specific conditions. The address information is structured as an object with XML representation named Address.

Number.description: The locations phone number of the Producer. Applies to NAFTA CO.

Extension.description: The locations phone extension of the Producer. Applies to NAFTA CO.

Producer_Phone.description: Phone number information of Producer.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

flattened_text: This data structure defines the phone number information for a producer, specifically for NAFTA CO. It includes properties for the phone extension and phone number, with specific length constraints. The phone number is required, and the structure is represented as an object in XML with the name "Phone."

TaxIdentificationNumber.description: SoldTo Tax Identification Number. This element has been deprecated, replacement can be found in the GlobalTaxInformation container.

Option.description: The text associated with the code will be printed in the sold to section of the NAFTA CO form.  The values indicate the following: 01 – Unknown.  Applies to NAFTA CO form. Possible Values are 01 and 02.

Contacts_SoldTo.description: SoldTo Container. The Sold To party's country code must be the same as the Ship To party's country code with the exception of Canada and satellite countries.  Applies to Invoice and NAFTA CO Forms. Required if Invoice or NAFTA CO (International Form) is requested.

flattened_text: The `Contacts_SoldTo` object represents the information of the party to whom goods are sold. It includes details like account number, address, contact name, email, company name, and phone number. The `TaxIdentificationNumber` field is deprecated and should be replaced with information from the `GlobalTaxInformation` container. This object is required when requesting an invoice or NAFTA CO form for international shipments.

Number.description: Sold To contacts phone number.

flattened_text: This data structure represents a phone contact for a customer. It includes an extension (up to 4 characters) and a phone number (up to 15 characters). The phone number is required.

AddressLine.description: SoldTo location's street address.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

StateProvinceCode.description: SoldTo location's state or province code.  Required for certain countries or territories.

PostalCode.description: SoldTo location's postal code.

CountryCode.description: SoldTo location's country or territory code.

SoldTo_Address.description: Sold To Address Container.  Applies to NAFTA CO.

flattened_text: This data structure represents the address of the customer who made the purchase. It includes fields for the street address, city, country code, postal code, state/province code, and town. The address must include the street address, city, and country code. Other fields are optional. The address is structured as an object named "Address" in the system.

Description.description: Description of the product.  Applies to all International Forms. Optional for Partial Invoice. Must be present at least once and can occur for a maximum of 3 times.

CommodityCode.description: 6-to-15-alphanumeric commodity code. Customs uses this code to determine what duties should be assessed on the commodity.  Applies to Invoice, Partial Invoice and NAFTA CO. Required for NAFTA CO and optional for Partial Invoice. Should be at least 6 alphanumeric. For NAFTA CO: For each good described in Description of Goods field, identify the H.S. tariff classification to six digits. If the good is subject to a specific rule of origin in Annex 401 that requires eight digits, identify to eight digits, using the H.S. tariff classification of the country or territory into whose territory the good is imported.

PartNumber.description: The part number or reference number for the product contained in the invoice line, as indicated on the customs invoice.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice.

OriginCountryCode.description: The country or territory in which the good was manufactured, produced or grown. For detailed information on country or territory of origin, certificate of origin, rules of origin, and any related matters, please refer to the U.S. Customs and Border Protection Web site at www.customs.gov or contact your country or territory's Customs authority.

JointProductionIndicator.description: If present, JNT will be used as the origin of country or territory code on the NAFTA form and the Product/Origincountry or territoryCode tag will be ignored.  Applies to NAFTA CO only.

NetCostCode.description:
For each good described in the Description of Goods field, where the good is subject to a regional value content (RVC) requirement, indicate NC if the RVC is calculated according to the net cost method; otherwise, indicate NO. If the RVC is calculated over a period of time then indicate "NC with begin/end date" by passing code "ND"  Applies to NAFTA CO only. Required for NAFTA CO.  Valid values:
- NC
- ND
- NO

PreferenceCriteria.description:
Indicates the criterion (A through F) for each good described in the Description of Goods field if applicable. 

The rules of origin are contained in Chapter Four and Annex 401. 

Additional rules are described in Annex 703.2 (certain agricultural goods), Annex 300-B, Appendix 6 (certain textile goods) and Annex 308.1 (certain automatic data processing goods and their parts).  Applies to NAFTA CO only.

ProducerInfo.description:
Indicate the following:  Yes - If shipper is the producer of the good. If not, state 02, 03, and 04 depending on whether this certificate was based upon:  
No [1] - Knowledge of whether the good qualifies as an originating good. 
No [2] - Reliance on the producers written representation (other than a Certificate of Origin) that the good qualifies as an originating good. 
No [3] - A completed and signed Certificate for the good voluntarily provided to the exporter by the producer.  Applicable for NAFTA CO and is required. Valid values: Yes, No [1], No [2], and No [3].

MarksAndNumbers.description: Any special marks, codes, and numbers that may appear on package.  Applies to CO Only.

NumberOfPackagesPerCommodity.description: The total number of packages, cartons, or containers for the commodity.  Applicable for CO and is required. Should be numeric. Valid characters are 0 -9.

VehicleID.description: Includes the following information for used self-propelled vehicles as defined in Customs regulations 19 CFR 192.1: The unique Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) in the proper format. Or The Product Identification Number (PIN) for those used self-propelled vehicles for which there are no VINs.  Or the Vehicle Title Number.  Applies to EEI forms only.

ExportType.description: Code indicating Domestic: Exports that have been produced, manufactured, or grown in the United States or Puerto Rico. This includes imported merchandise which has been enhanced in value or changed from the form in which imported by further manufacture or processing in the United States or Puerto Rico. Foreign: Merchandise that has entered the United States and is being exported again in the same condition as when imported.   Applies to EEI forms only. Required for EEI form.  Valid values:  D: Domestic; F: Foreign.

SEDTotalValue.description:
This amount will always be USD.  Applies to EEI forms only. Required for EEI form. Valid characters are 0-9 and \'.\' (Decimal point). Limit to 2 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 15 including \'.\' and can hold up to 2 decimal places.

Note: This value is calculated based on the Product/Unit/Value and /Product/Unit/Number (Number of Units * Price per Unit). If the total value is incorrect it will be replaced by the actual calculated total value.

TaxesPaid.description: Invoice Commodity Level Tax Collected Code for each shipment commodity line.Taxes paid Indicator is only applicable for shipments to Singapore. [TaxesPaid = 0 - No on Report], [TaxesPaid = 1 -Yes on Report], [TaxesPaid = empty - null on Report], [If TaxesPaid is not passed in input request = null on Report]

InternationalForms_Product.description:
Contains the commodity/product information.  Applies to EEI, Invoice, Partial Invoice, CO and NAFTA CO. When any International form is requested, at least one Product must be present. 

Maximum number of products allowed for different forms are:

50: Package Packing List

100: Commercial Invoice, NAFTA, CO, EEI

1000: Air Freight packing list

Note: For Partial Invoice this container is optional.

flattened_text: The `InternationalForms_Product` object contains information about a product or commodity for various international forms like EEI, Invoice, CO, and NAFTA CO. It includes details such as commodity code, description, export type, origin country, part number, and more. Some fields are required for specific forms, while others are optional. For example, the commodity code is required for NAFTA CO, and the description must be present at least once but can occur up to three times. The object is structured as an object with multiple properties, each serving a specific purpose in international trade documentation.

Number.description: Total quantity of each commodity to be shipped, measured in the units specified in the Unit of Measure field.  Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Must be numeric. Valid characters are 0-9.

Value.description: Monetary amount used to specify the worth or price of the commodity. Amount should be greater than zero.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice form. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Amount should be greater than zero.  Valid characters are 0-9 and. (Decimal point). Limit to 6 digits after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 19 including '.' and can hold up to 6 decimal places.(#####.######, ######.#####, #######.####, ########.###, #########.##,##########.#,############). The value of this product  and the other products should be such that the invoice line total which is the sum of ( number*values) of all products should not exceed 9999999999999999.99

Product_Unit.description: Container tag for the Unit information of each product. (also called as commodity)  Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice.

flattened_text: Each product has a unit information section for invoices. It includes the quantity, unit of measurement, and value of the product. The quantity must be numeric and the value must be a monetary amount greater than zero. The value can have up to 6 decimal places. The total invoice line amount should not exceed 9999999999999999.99. The unit information is required for invoices and optional for partial invoices.

Code.description:
Code for the Unit of measurement of the commodity units.  Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice.

Refer to Product Unit of Measure Codes in the Appendix for valid values.

Description.description: The Unit of Measure if OTH (Other) is entered as the UnitOfMeasurement code.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms.  Conditionally Required for the Invoice and Partial Invoice form if OTH is entered as the units UnitOfMeasurement Code.

Unit_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Container tag for the Unit of measurement for the commodity.  Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for a commodity in an invoice. It includes a code for the unit of measurement and a description. The code must be a valid product unit of measure code. The description is required if "OTH" (Other) is selected as the unit of measurement.

BeginDate.description: If the RVC is calculated over a period of time, it should be identified by the begin date (yyyyMMdd) of that period. (Reference: Articles 402.1, 402.5).  Applies to NAFTA CO only. Format is yyyyMMdd.

EndDate.description: If the RVC is calculated over a period of time, it should be identified by the End date (yyyyMMdd) of that period. (Reference: Articles 402.1, 402.5).  Applies to NAFTA CO only. Format is yyyyMMdd.

Product_NetCostDateRange.description: Date Range for regional value content (RVC).  Applies to NAFTA CO only.

flattened_text: This data structure defines a date range for regional value content (RVC) specific to NAFTA CO. It includes BeginDate and EndDate properties in the format yyyyMMdd. These dates mark the period over which RVC is calculated. EndDate and BeginDate are required fields.

Weight.description: Weight of Product.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only. Valid characters are 0-9 and '.' (Decimal point). Limit to 1 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 5 including '.' and can hold up to 1 decimal place.

Product_ProductWeight.description: The shipping weight, including containers, for each commodity with a separate Harmonized Tariff Code / Schedule B Number. This weight does not include carrier equipment.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only. Required for CO and EEI forms.

flattened_text: This schema defines the structure for specifying the weight of a product for shipping purposes on certain forms. It includes the unit of measurement and the weight of the product. The weight should be a numeric value with up to one decimal place and a maximum length of 5 characters. Both the unit of measurement and weight are required fields.

Code.description:
Code for unit of Measurement of weight.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only.  Valid values:
- KGS
- LBS

Description.description: Description of the Unit of Measure.

ProductWeight_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Container tag for the Unit of Measurement of weight.  Applies to CO and EEI forms only.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for product weight on CO and EEI forms. It includes a code (KGS or LBS) and a description. The code must be 3 characters or less, and the description must be 20 characters or less. The code is required.

Number.description: A unique 10-digit commodity classification code for the item being exported. (To classify a commodity access the following Web page: http://www.census.gov/foreign-trade/schedules/b/#search).  Applies to EEI forms only. Has to be 10 characters.

Quantity.description: The count of how many Schedule B units of the current good are in the shipment (EEI only). For example, if the Schedule B unit of measure is dozens and eight dozen, is being shipped, indicate 8 in this field.  Applies to EEI forms only. Conditionally required for EEI forms if ScheduleB UnitOfMeasurement is not X. Should be Numeric. Valid characters are 0 -9.

Product_ScheduleB.description: Container tag for the schedule B information of a commodity.  Applies to EEI forms only. Required for EEI form

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for Schedule B information in EEI forms. It includes fields for a 10-digit commodity classification code, quantity of units being exported, and the unit of measurement. The commodity code must be 10 characters long. Quantity should be a numeric value between 1 and 10 characters. The unit of measurement is a reference to another schema. The commodity code and unit of measurement are required fields.

Code.description:
The unit of measure indicated on the Export License. Enter an X if there is no unit of measure in the Schedule B Unit field.  Applies to EEI forms only. Required for the EEI form.

Refer to ScheduleB Unit of Measure Codes in the Appendix for valid values.

Description.description: Description of the Unit of Measure.

ScheduleB_UnitOfMeasurement.description: The unit of measure indicated on the Export License.  Applies to EEI forms only.

flattened_text: This object defines the unit of measurement used in an Export License for EEI forms. It includes a code and a description of the unit of measure. The code must be a maximum of 3 characters and is required. The description must be a maximum of 20 characters.

FormType.description: Indicates the name of the International form requested to NOT have product information.  Possible Values are 04 – NAFTA CO.  Please note that if this is used and you DO NOT have the corresponding form type requested this will be IGNORED.

Product_ExcludeFromForm.description: Container tag for determining whether or not to exclude product information from a particular form.  If this container is not present we assume that the DEFAULT is selected which is "none" and all products will appear on all forms.

flattened_text: This configuration defines a container tag called "Product_ExcludeFromForm" used to specify whether to exclude product information from a specific form. If this tag is not present, the default setting is "none," meaning all products will be included on all forms. The container allows specifying the form type (e.g., 04 - NAFTA CO) for which product information should be excluded. If the specified form type is not available, the exclusion will be ignored. The container allows only one instance and requires specifying the FormType. The XML element name for this configuration is "ExcludeFromForm."

Product_PackingListInfo.description: Data Container holding package related information.  Required for packaging list, Air Freight Packing list and multi-piece Economy shipments.

flattened_text: This data container, Product_PackingListInfo, holds package-related information needed for packaging lists, air freight packing lists, and multi-piece economy shipments. It includes an array of up to 20 items referencing PackingListInfo_PackageAssociated. The PackageAssociated property is required.

PackageNumber.description: Package number the product should be allocated to ont he packing list.  Required for packaging list and Air Freight Packing list.

ProductAmount.description: Amount of Product associated with a package.  Required for packaging list and Air Freight Packing list.

PackingListInfo_PackageAssociated.description:
Data Container holding package/product related information that will break up the product into each package on the packing list.  Total product amount must equal the product unit value above. Required for packaging list and Air Freight Packing list.                                                      Packaging list max allowed : 20
Air Freight Packaging list max allowed: 200

flattened_text:
This data container holds information about packages or products listed on a packing list. It breaks down the product into individual packages. The total product amount must match the product unit value. It is required for both packaging lists and air freight packing lists. The maximum allowed entries for a packaging list is 20, and for an air freight packaging list is 200. 

The container includes fields for Package Number (required), Product Amount (required), and Product Note.

ExportInformation.description: Required for EEI form id it is a SDL product. Valid values: LC, LV, SS,MS, GS, DP, HR, UG, IC, SC, DD, HH, SR, TE,TL, IS, CR, GP, RJ, TP, IP, IR, DB, CH, RS, OS  Applies to EEI form only. Required if EEIFilingOption code 3 specified for EEI form.

Product_EEIInformation.description: Required for EEI form.  Applies to EEI form only.

flattened_text: This object, `Product_EEIInformation`, is required for the EEI form and only applies to that form. It includes `DDTCInformation`, `ExportInformation`, and `License` properties. The `ExportInformation` property is required for SDL products and must have a specific format. The object is limited to one instance and is named `EEIInformation` in XML.

Number.description:
Represents any one of the following values: export license number, exception code, CFR citation, KPC Number, ACM Number.  Applies to EEI form only.

Refer to EEI License Types and Exemptions in the Appendix  for valid values and formats.

Code.description:
The standard license code published by US government. 
Refer to EEI License Codes in the Appendix for valid values.  Applies to EEI form only. It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3. It is optionally required for all other filing types; however, it is used to categorize each product as SDL or non-SDL.  It is also used to identify which piece of information is applicable.

LicenseLineValue.description:
The export monetary amount allowed per license. Required for a licensable product when the EEI form is selected.
Format: Whole numbers only.  Applies to EEI form only. Required if EEIFilingOption code 1A (only for SDL shipments) or 3.

ECCNNumber.description: Product ECCN Number issued by BIS (Bureau of Industry and Security). If the license number is a commerce license, ECCN must be provided. The format is #A### or EAR99  Applies to EEI forms only. It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3. ECCN is required one of the following License Exception Codes is entered: CIV, CTP, ENC, GBS, KMI, LVS, TSR

EEIInformation_License.description: Licence information for SDL commodity.  Applies to EEI form only.

flattened_text: This section defines license information for SDL commodity in the EEI form. It includes fields for the standard license code, ECCN number, export monetary amount allowed per license, and various identifying numbers. The license code categorizes products as SDL or non-SDL and is used for information categorization. The ECCN number is required for commerce licenses, and the export monetary amount is required for licensable products on the EEI form. The section specifies valid values and formats for each field.

ITARExemptionNumber.description:
The specific citation (exemption number) under the International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) from the Code of Federal Register (see 22 CFR 120-130) that exempts the shipment from the requirements for a license or other written authorization from the Directorate of Trade Controls (DDTC). 
Refer to EEI License Codes in the Appendix for valid values.  Applies to EEI Form only. This field is applicable for EEIFiling option 1A and 3.

USMLCategoryCode.description: Digit numeric code (e.g. 01-18, 20 or 21). Indicates the U.S. Munitions List (USML) category article, service or related technical data as it applies to the article reported.  Applies to EEI form only. It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3.

EligiblePartyIndicator.description: Presence/Absent indicator. Certification by the U.S. exporter that the exporter is an eligible party to participate in the defense trade.

RegistrationNumber.description: It is a unique registration code assigned to the registrant. The DDTC registration code consist of a letter prefix, M (assigned to a manufacturer and/or exporter) or K (assigned to a broker), followed by four or five digits (e.g. K-1234 or M12345).  It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3.

Quantity.description: Export Quantity.  Applies to EEI form only. It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3. Only positive integer value is valid.

SignificantMilitaryEquipmentIndicator.description: Presence/ Absence Indicator.  Applies to EEI form only.

ACMNumber.description: Approved Community Member Number (ACM). It is required to be provided along with ITARExemptionNumber for some License code (SGB and SAU). The ACM# for the United Kingdom (License code SGB) must begin with UK followed by 9 numbers.  The ACM# for Australia (License Code SAU) must begin with DTT followed by 8 numbers.  Applies to EEI form only.  It is required for EEIFilingOption code 1A and 3.

EEIInformation_DDTCInformation.description: Department of State/ Directorate of Defense Trade Control Information. This element is a container for additional information that is applicable to SDL products. It will only be evaluated if the provided license code is an SDL code.  Applies to EEI Form only.

flattened_text: This element contains additional information for SDL products related to the Department of State/ Directorate of Defense Trade Control. It includes details like Approved Community Member Number, Eligible Party Indicator, ITAR Exemption Number, Export Quantity, Registration Number, Significant Military Equipment Indicator, USML Category Code, and Unit of Measurement. These details are required for specific EEI filing options. The element is part of the EEI Form and is evaluated only for SDL license codes.

Code.description: Required for EEI form. Unit of measurement code. The two or three (3) alpha unit of measurement for the article being shipped. For example: BAG/BG - bags  Applies to EEI form only.  It is required for EEIFilingOption code 1A and 3.

Description.description: Description for Unit of Measurement.  Applies to EEI form only.

DDTCInformation_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Container for unit of measurement.  Applies to EEI form only. It is required for EEIFilingOption code 3.

flattened_text: This section defines the unit of measurement for the EEI form. It is mandatory for EEIFilingOption code 3. The container includes a code (e.g., BAG/BG for bags) and a description. The code is required for EEIFilingOption codes 1A and 3.

MonetaryValue.description: The discount to be subtracted from the sum of the total value on the invoice.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Valid characters are 0-9 and '.'  (Decimal point). Limit to 2 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 15 including '.' and can hold up to 2 decimal places. This value should be greater than or equal to zero or less than or equal to the value of all goods listed on the invoice.

InternationalForms_Discount.description: Container tag that holds the discount.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

flattened_text: The `InternationalForms_Discount` object represents a discount that can be applied to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms. It contains a `MonetaryValue` property, which specifies the amount to be subtracted from the total value on the invoice. The `MonetaryValue` should only contain numbers and a decimal point, with a limit of 2 decimal places and a maximum length of 15 characters. This value must be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to the total value of goods on the invoice. The `MonetaryValue` property is required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice forms.

MonetaryValue.description: Cost to transport the shipment.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Valid characters are 0-9 and '.'  (Decimal point). Limit to 2 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 15 including '.' and can hold up to 2 decimal places.

InternationalForms_FreightCharges.description: Container tag that holds the Freight Charges.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

flattened_text: This section defines the "Freight Charges" for international forms related to invoices. It specifies the cost of shipping the goods, which is mandatory for invoices and optional for partial invoices. The value must be a string with a maximum length of 15 characters, including up to 2 decimal places. The field name in the XML is "FreightCharges."

MonetaryValue.description: The amount the shipper or receiver pays to cover the cost of replacing the shipment if it is lost or damaged.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Valid characters are 0-9 and '.'  (Decimal point). Limit to 2 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 15 including '.' and can hold up to 2 decimal places.

InternationalForms_InsuranceCharges.description: Container tag that holds the Insurance Charges.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

flattened_text: This section, "InternationalForms_InsuranceCharges," is a container for Insurance Charges on Invoice and Partial Invoice forms. It includes a property called "MonetaryValue," which represents the amount paid to cover lost or damaged shipments. This field is required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice forms. The value must be numeric with up to 2 decimal places and a maximum length of 15 characters.

MonetaryValue.description: The Monetary value of Other Charges.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Invoice forms and optional for Partial Invoice. Valid characters are 0-9 and '.' (Decimal point). Limit to 2 digit after the decimal. The maximum length of the field is 15 including '.' and can hold up to 2 decimal places.

Description.description: Description of what the other charges are for.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only. Required for Complete Invoice and Optional for Partial Invoice forms.

InternationalForms_OtherCharges.description: Container tag that holds the information of amount that covers additional charges not already listed on the invoice.  Applies to Invoice and Partial Invoice forms only.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for handling additional charges not listed on an invoice. It includes fields for describing the charges and specifying their monetary value. The description must be up to 10 characters long, while the monetary value can have up to 15 characters with a maximum of 2 decimal places. These fields are required for complete invoices and optional for partial invoices.

BeginDate.description: Begin date of the blanket period. It is the date upon which the Certificate becomes applicable to the good covered by the blanket Certificate (it may be prior to the date of signing this Certificate).  Applies to NAFTA CO form only. Required for NAFTA CO. Format is yyyyMMdd. This is not valid for a paperless shipment.

EndDate.description: End Date of the blanket period. It is the date upon which the blanket period expires.  Applies to NAFTA CO form only. Required for NAFTA CO. Format is yyyyMMdd.  This is not valid for a paperless shipment.

InternationalForms_BlanketPeriod.description: This field should be entered if the  NAFTA Certificate covers multiple shipments of identical goods as described in the Description of Goods field that are imported into a NAFTA country or territory for a specified period of up to one year (the blanket period). The importation of a good for which preferential treatment is claimed based on this certificate must occur between these dates.  Applies to NAFTA CO form only. Required for NAFTA CO.  This is not valid for a paperless shipment.

flattened_text: The InternationalForms_BlanketPeriod field is used for NAFTA Certificates that cover multiple shipments of identical goods over a specified period, up to one year. This field specifies the start and end dates of this blanket period. It is required for NAFTA CO forms and not valid for paperless shipments. The BeginDate is the start date of the period, and the EndDate is the end date. Both dates must be in the format yyyyMMdd.

DCISType.description:
Type of delivery confirmation.  Valid values: 
1 - Delivery Confirmation Signature Required
2 - Delivery Confirmation Adult Signature Required. Valid for forward shipments only.

ShipmentServiceOptions_DeliveryConfirmat.description:
Delivery Confirmation container.   Valid for forward shipments only.

Refer to Delivery Confirmation Origin-Destination Pairs in the Appendix for a list of valid values.

flattened_text: This section defines the options for delivery confirmation in a shipment. It includes fields for the DCIS number and the type of delivery confirmation required. The valid values for the DCISType field are 1 for Delivery Confirmation Signature Required and 2 for Delivery Confirmation Adult Signature Required. The maximum length for both fields is 1 character.

Code.description:
Valid LabelMethod types are:
01 = ImportControl Print and Mail
02 = ImportControl One-Attempt
03 = ImportControl Three-Attempt
04 = ImportControl Electronic Label
05 = ImportControl Print Label

Description.description: LabelMethod description.

ShipmentServiceOptions_LabelMethod.description: Type of ImportControl Label. This container is applicable only for ImportControl shipments.  This container is applicable only for ImportControl shipments.

flattened_text: This object defines the different types of label methods available for ImportControl shipments. The "Code" property specifies the label method type using a two-digit code, and the "Description" property provides a brief description of the label method. The valid label method types include ImportControl Print and Mail, One-Attempt, Three-Attempt, Electronic Label, and Print Label. The object is required to have a "Code" property and can have a maximum of one instance.

ShipmentServiceOptions_PreAlertNotificat.description: This container is used for providing Pre-Alert Notifications to the consignee for UPS Exchange movements and Pack & Collect shipments.

flattened_text: This container, ShipmentServiceOptions_PreAlertNotification, is used to send Pre-Alert Notifications to the recipient for UPS Exchange movements and Pack & Collect shipments. It includes EMailMessage, Locale, TextMessage, and VoiceMessage properties. The Locale property is required.

UndeliverableEMailAddress.description: This is used for notification when EMailAddress for PreAlertNotification is undeliverable.

PreAlertNotification_EMailMessage.description: This container is used for Populating EMailMessage details for PreAlertNotification.

flattened_text: This container, PreAlertNotification_EMailMessage, is used to store details for sending email notifications about PreAlertNotification. It includes properties for the recipient's email address and an alternate email address for undeliverable notifications. The recipient's email address is required and can be up to 50 characters long.

PhoneNumber.description:
Phone number for receiving Voice PreAlertNotification.  Valid values are 0 – 9.

If the country or territory of the message recipient is US, PR, CA, and VI, the layout is:

1, area code, 7 digit phone number or

1, area code, 7 digit phone number, 4 digit extension number.

For other countries or territories, the layout is country or territory code, area code, 7 digit number.

PreAlertNotification_VoiceMessage.description: VoiceMessage container is used for specifying phone number for receiving voice PreAlertNotification.

flattened_text: This object, PreAlertNotification_VoiceMessage, is used to specify a phone number for receiving voice PreAlertNotifications. It contains a property, PhoneNumber, where you can input the phone number. The phone number must be between 1 and 15 characters long and can only contain numbers 0-9. The format of the phone number varies based on the country or territory of the recipient. The PhoneNumber property is required for this object.

PhoneNumber.description:
Phone number for receiving Voice PreAlertNotification.  Valid values are 0 – 9.

If the country or territory of the message recipient is US, PR, CA, and VI, the layout is:

1, area code, 7 digit phone number or

1, area code, 7 digit phone number, 4 digit extension number.

For other countries or territories, the layout is country or territory code, area code, 7 digit number.

PreAlertNotification_TextMessage.description: TextMessage container is used for specifying phone number for receiving text preAlertNotification.

flattened_text: This object, PreAlertNotification_TextMessage, is used to specify a phone number for receiving text pre-alert notifications. It contains a property, PhoneNumber, where you can input a valid phone number to receive these notifications. The phone number format varies based on the country or territory of the recipient. The PhoneNumber property is required and can be a maximum of 15 characters long.

Language.description: Refer to Language/Dialect Combinations in the Appendix for valid pairs.

Dialect.description: Refer to Language/Dialect Combinations in the Appendix for valid pairs.

PreAlertNotification_Locale.description: This container is used for providing Language and dialect details for PreAlertNotification.

flattened_text: The `PreAlertNotification_Locale` container is used to specify language and dialect details for PreAlertNotification. It includes properties for `Dialect` and `Language`, with specific length requirements. Both properties are required. The container is represented as an object in XML with the name `Locale`.

DiagnosticSpecimensIndicator.description: This field is a flag to indicate if the package has Biological substances. True if present; false otherwise.  Shippers account needs to have a valid contract for Biological Substances. Lane check will happen based on postal code/ city.

AlcoholicBeveragesIndicator.description: Presence/Absence Indicator. True if present; false otherwise. Any value is ignored. If present, indicates that the package contains Alcoholic Beverages  Shippers account needs to have a valid contract for Alcohol.

PerishablesIndicator.description: Presence/Absence Indicator. True if present; false otherwise. Any value is ignored. If present, indicates that the package contains Perishable items.  Shippers account needs to have a valid contract for Perishables.
