ShipmentRequest_LabelSpecification.description: Container used to define the properties required by the user to print and/or display the UPS shipping label.  Required for shipment without return service or shipments with PRL return service. Required for Electronic Return Label or Electronic Import Control Label shipments with SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707.

flattened_text: The `ShipmentRequest_LabelSpecification` defines the properties needed to print UPS shipping labels. It specifies the language character set, browser user agent string, label image format, and label stock size. The label image format and label stock size are required fields. The character set defaults to English and the user agent defaults to Mozilla/4.5 if not specified.

Code.description: Label print method code determines the format in which Labels are to be generated. For EPL2 formatted Labels use EPL, for SPL formatted Labels use SPL, for ZPL formatted Labels use ZPL and for image formats use GIF.  For shipments without return service the valid value is GIF, ZPL, EPL and SPL. For shipments with PRL return service, the valid values are EPL, ZPL, SPL and GIF. For UPS Premier Silver shipment only ZPL is supported.

Description.description: Description of the label image format code.

flattened_text: This component defines the format for label images. It includes properties for the code and description of the label image format. The code specifies how labels are generated, with options like EPL, SPL, ZPL, and GIF. The description provides additional details about the format code. The code must be a string with a maximum length of 4 characters, and the description must be a string with a maximum length of 35 characters. The code property is required, and the format is represented as an object named LabelImageFormat in XML.

Height.description: Height of the label image. For IN, use whole inches.  For EPL2, ZPL and SPL Labels. Only valid values are 6 or 8. Note: Label Image will only scale up to 4 X 6, even when requesting 4 X 8.

Width.description: Width of the label image. For IN, use whole inches.  For EPL2, ZPL and SPL Labels. Valid value is 4. Note: Label Image will only scale up to 4 X 6, even when requesting 4 X 8.

LabelSpecification_LabelStockSize.description: Container for the EPL2, ZPL or SPL label size.  Valid for EPL2, ZPL and SPL Labels.

flattened_text: This section defines the label size specifications for EPL2, ZPL, or SPL labels. It includes properties for the height and width of the label image, with specific valid values for each. The label image will scale up to a maximum size of 4 X 6, even if a larger size is requested. Both height and width are required properties in this object.

Code.description: For Exchange Forward Shipment, by default Label will have Exchange Routing instruction Text as EXCHANGE-LIKE ITEM ONLY. If code value is: 01- EXCHANGE-LIKE ITEM ONLY, 02- EXCHANGE-DRIVER INSTRUCTIONS INSIDE.

Description.description: Description of the label Instruction code.

flattened_text: This object, LabelSpecification_Instruction, is a container for routing instructions. It includes properties for Code and Description. The Code property specifies routing instructions for exchange forward shipments, with specific code values indicating different instructions. The Description property provides a description of the instruction code. The Code property is required and must be a string of length 2, while the Description property is optional and must be a string of length 1 to 35.

ShipmentRequest_ReceiptSpecification.description: Container used to allow the user to choose to print a thermal receipt.

flattened_text: This object, "ShipmentRequest_ReceiptSpecification," lets users select to print a thermal receipt. It includes the property "ImageFormat" and requires this property to be specified. The object is used for specifying receipt details in XML format.

Code.description: Print code that determines the receipt format. Valid Codes are: EPL, SPL, ZPL and HTML.

Description.description: Description of the receipt format code.

flattened_text: This specification defines an ImageFormat container for receipt formats. It includes properties for a code (EPL, SPL, ZPL, or HTML) and a description of the code. The code must be 3 characters long, and the description must be between 1 and 35 characters. The code property is required.
This defines a "ShipmentResponse" object that includes a "Response" and "ShipmentResults" property. Both properties are required. The object is used to represent a response related to a shipment.

Alert.description:
Alert Container.  There can be zero to many alert containers with code and description.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This response container, `ShipmentResponse_Response`, includes information about a shipment response. It contains three main properties: `Alert`, `ResponseStatus`, and `TransactionReference`. The `Alert` property can have multiple alert containers with codes and descriptions. For versions equal to or greater than v2403, `Alert` will always be returned as an array. For older versions, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one. The `ResponseStatus` property is required in the response.

Code.description: Identifies the success or failure of the transaction. 1 = Successful

Description.description: Describes Response Status Code. Returns text of Success.

flattened_text: This defines a response status object with two properties: Code (identifies success/failure) and Description (describes status). Code is a 1-character string indicating success (1) or failure. Description is a string up to 35 characters. Both properties are required.

Code.description: Warning code returned by the system.

Description.description: Warning messages returned by the system.

Response_Alert.description: Alert Container. There can be zero to many alert containers with code and description.

flattened_text: This defines an "Alert" object that can contain a warning code and message from the system. Each alert can have one code (up to 10 characters) and one description (up to 150 characters). Both code and description are required fields.

CustomerContext.description: The CustomerContext Information which will be echoed during response.

flattened_text: This defines a response object called "TransactionReference" that contains CustomerContext information. The CustomerContext field can be up to 512 characters long and will be included in the response.

Disclaimer.description:
Disclaimer would be used to provide more information to shipper regarding the processed shipment. This would be used to notify shipper about possible taxes and duties that might have been added or might apply to the shipment. This field would be returned only if TaxInformationIndicator is present in a request.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

RatingMethod.description:
RatingMethod is to indicate whether the Shipment was rated as shipment level or package level. This information will be returned only if RatingMethodRequestedIndicator is present in the request.  Valid values:
01 = Shipment level
02 = Package level

BillableWeightCalculationMethod.description:
BillableWeightCalculationMethod is to indicate whether the billable weight calculation method utilized was - the package level or shipment level. This information will be returned only if RatingMethodRequestedIndicator is present in the request.  Valid values:
01 = Shipment Billable Weight
02 = Package Billable Weight

ShipmentIdentificationNumber.description: Returned UPS shipment ID number.1Z Number of the first package in the shipment.

MIDualReturnShipmentKey.description:
MIDualReturnShipmentKey is unique key required to process Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipment. 

The unique identifier (key) would be returned in response of first phase of Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipments. 

This unique identifier (key) would be part of request for second phase of Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipments and would be played back in response for second phase of Mail Innovations Dual Return Shipment.  If the shipment is a Package return shipment, the package tracking number will be concatenated with the system time (in the format YYYY-MM-DDHH.MM.SS.NNN) and followed by service code. 

If the shipment is an MI Returns shipment, the Mail Manifest ID (MMI) will be concatenated with the system time.

BarCodeImage.description: Bar Code Image will be returned as Base 64 encoded graphic image. Bar Code Image will be returned if BarCodeImageIndicator or BarCodeAndLabelIndicator is present.

PackageResults.description:
Returned Package Information.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ControlLogReceipt.description:
Container for the High Value reports when forward shipments have declared value between $999 and $50,000 USD. \nTwo copies of high value report needs to be pointed out.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2409, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2409, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

LabelURL.description:
URL will point to a page wherein label, receipt and other documents, if applicable, such as HighValueReport, CustomsInvoice and ImportControl instructions can be requested. LabelURL is returned only if the LabelLinksIndicator is requested for following shipments:
Print/Electronic ImportControl shipment
Print/Electronic Return shipment. 
Forward shipment except for Mail Innovations Forward.

LocalLanguageLabelURL.description:
URL will point to a page wherein label, receipt and other documents, if applicable, such as HighValueReport, CustomsInvoice and ImportControl instructions can be requested. LocalLanguageLabelURL is returned only if the LabelLinksIndicator is requested for following shipments:
Print/Electronic ImportControl shipment
Print/Electronic Return shipment. 
Forward shipment except for Mail Innovations Forward.  Not returned if LabelLinksIndicator is requested with Locale element.

ReceiptURL.description:
URL will point to a page wherein label, receipt and other documents, if applicable, such as HighValueReport, CustomsInvoice and ImportControl instructions can be requested. ReceiptURL is returned only if the LabelLinksIndicator is requested for following shipments:
Print/Electronic ImportControl shipment
Print/Electronic Return shipment.

LocalLanguageReceiptURL.description:
URL will point to a page wherein label, receipt and other documents, if applicable, such as HighValueReport, CustomsInvoice and ImportControl instructions can be requested. LocalLanguageReceiptURL is returned only if the LabelLinksIndicator is requested for following shipments:
Print/Electronic ImportControl shipment
Print/Electronic Return shipment.   Not returned if LabelLinksIndicator is requested with Locale element.

DGPaperImage.description:
Dangerous Good Paper Image in pdf format. One multipage PDF document will be returned that will contain all required Dangrous Goods shipping paper copies for all Dangerous Goods packages. Only returned when DGSignatoryInfo is present.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

MasterCartonID.description: Master Carton ID. MasterCartonID will be return if MasterCartonIndicator is present in request.

flattened_text: This response contains various details about a shipment, such as bar code image, billable weight calculation method, high value reports, and shipment charges. It includes information like the shipment ID number, master carton ID, and package results. Some elements are returned based on specific indicators in the request, like tax information or label links. The response structure is in an object format named ShipmentResults.

Code.description: Code representing type of Disclaimer.   Refer to Disclaimer Codes and Messages in the Appendix for various disclaimers that would be possible for a given shipment.

Description.description:
Disclaimer description.   This field would be returned only if TaxInformationIndicator is present in a request.

Refer to Disclaimer Codes and Messages in the Appendix for various disclaimers that would be possible for a given shipment.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure of a "ShipmentResults_Disclaimer" object. It includes properties for "Code" and "Description," which provide information about the type of disclaimer associated with a shipment. The "Code" property is a 2-character string representing the disclaimer type, while the "Description" property gives a brief description of the disclaimer. The "Description" field is only returned if the "TaxInformationIndicator" is present in a request. The object is required to have a "Code" property and is represented in XML as "Disclaimer."

RateChart.description:
Rate Type with which Shipment is rated. Possible RateChart values for different regions will be:
US 48 origin:
- 1 – Daily Rates
- 3 – Standard List Rates
- 4 – Retail Rates.

Alaska/Hawaii origin:
- 1 – Daily Rates
- 3 – Standard List Rates
- 4 – Retail Rates.

All Other origins:
- 1 – Rates
- 5 - Regional Rates
- 6 - General List Rates.

3 and 4 do not apply.

ItemizedCharges.description:
Itemized Charges are returned only when the Subversion element is present and greater than or equal to 1601.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

TaxCharges.description:
TaxCharges container are returned only when TaxInformationIndicator is present in request and when Negotiated Rates are not applicable. TaxCharges container contains Tax information for a given shipment.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ShipmentResults_ShipmentCharges.description: Shipment charges Container. Shipment charges info.

flattened_text: This component defines the structure for shipment charges information. It includes details like base service charges, itemized charges (if applicable), rate chart information, service options charges, tax charges, total charges, and transportation charges. The itemized charges and tax charges are returned based on specific conditions. Certain values are specified for rate charts based on different regions. The component is required to include total charges, service options charges, and transportation charges.

CurrencyCode.description: BaseServiceCharge currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Base Service Charge value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

ShipmentCharges_BaseServiceCharge.description:
Base Service Charge container.
Transportation charge = BaseServiceCharge + Fuel charge  Returned only if Subversion >=1701.

flattened_text: This object represents the base service charge for a shipment. It includes the currency code and value amount. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the value amount ranges from 0 to 99999999999999.99. This information is returned only for specific versions of the service.

CurrencyCode.description: Transportation charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Transportation and surcharges value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This object represents transportation charges for a shipment. It includes the currency code and the monetary value of the charges. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value must be between 0 and 99999999999999.99. Both the currency code and monetary value are required fields.

Code.description: Identification code for itemized charge.

Description.description: Description of Itemized Charge that had been charged.

CurrencyCode.description: Itemized Charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Itemized Charges value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This section defines the structure of itemized charges for a shipment. Each itemized charge includes a code, currency code, description, monetary value, and sub-type. The code is a 3-character identification code, currency code is a 3-character currency code, description is up to 50 characters, and monetary value is a valid amount between 0 and 99999999999999.99. Currency code, monetary value, and code are required fields.

CurrencyCode.description: Accessorial charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Accessorial charges value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for service option charges in a shipment. It includes properties for the currency code and monetary value of the charges. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value must be between 0 and 99999999999999.99. Both properties are required.

Type.description: Tax Type code. The code represents the type of Tax applied to a shipment.   Refer to Tax Type Values/Abbreviations in the Appendix for valid values.

MonetaryValue.description: Tax Monetary Value represent the Tax amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This section defines the structure of tax charges for a shipment. It includes properties for the monetary value of the tax and the type of tax applied. The monetary value must be between 0 and 99999999999999.99. The type is a code representing the type of tax, with specific values listed in the documentation. Both the type and monetary value are required fields.

CurrencyCode.description: Total charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Total charges value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99.

flattened_text: This object represents the total charges for a shipment. It includes the currency code and the value amount. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the value amount can range from 0 to 99999999999999.99. Both the currency code and value amount are required fields.

CurrencyCode.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes monetary value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

ShipmentCharges_TotalChargesWithTaxes.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes container would be returned only if TaxInformationIndicator is present in request and when Negotiated Rates are not applicable. TotalChargesWithTaxes contains total charges including total taxes applied to a shipment.

flattened_text: This object, `ShipmentCharges_TotalChargesWithTaxes`, is returned when taxes are included in a shipment and negotiated rates are not used. It includes the total charges and taxes for the shipment. It consists of `CurrencyCode` (3-character currency code) and `MonetaryValue` (monetary amount up to 99999999999999.99). Both fields are required.

ItemizedCharges.description:
Itemized Charges are returned only when the Subversion element is present and greater than or equal to 1601.

Negotiated itemized charges are only returned for certain contract-only shipments as well as Worldwide Express Freight, Ground Freight Pricing, and Hazmat movements.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

TaxCharges.description:
TaxCharges container are returned only when TaxInformationIndicator is present in request. TaxCharges container contains Tax information for a given shipment.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ShipmentResults_NegotiatedRateCharges.description: Negotiated Rates Charge Container.  For tiered rates and promotional discounts, if a particular shipment based on zone, origin, destination or even shipment size doesn't qualify for the existing discount then no negotiated rates container will be returned. Published rates will be the applicable rate.

flattened_text: The `ShipmentResults_NegotiatedRateCharges` object contains negotiated rates charges for shipments. It includes itemized charges, rate modifiers, tax charges, total charges, and total charges with taxes. Itemized charges are returned for specific shipments and certain service types. Tax charges are included if tax information is provided. The object structure may vary based on the API version used.

Code.description: Identification code for itemized charge.

Description.description: Description of Itemized Charge that had been charged.

CurrencyCode.description: Itemized Charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Itemized Charges value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for itemized charges in negotiated rate charges. Each itemized charge includes a code, currency code, description, monetary value, and subtype. The code is a 3-character identifier, currency code is a 3-character currency code, description is up to 50 characters, monetary value ranges from 0 to 99999999999999.99, and subtype is up to 50 characters. Currency code, monetary value, and code are required fields.

Type.description: Tax Type code. The code represents the type of Tax applied to a shipment.   Refer to Tax Type Values/Abbreviations in the Appendix for valid values.

MonetaryValue.description: Tax Monetary Value represent the Tax amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for representing negotiated rate charges and tax charges in an object format. It includes properties for Tax Monetary Value and Tax Type code, with specific constraints on their length and valid values. The Tax Type code indicates the type of tax applied to a shipment. Both Tax Type and Monetary Value are required fields. The object is named TaxCharges in XML.

CurrencyCode.description: Total charges currency code.

MonetaryValue.description: Total charges monetary value.  Valid values are from 0 to 9999999999999999.99

NegotiatedRateCharges_TotalCharge.description: Total charges container. Account Based Rates info. Total charges are only returned for ABR eligible shipper account/UserId combinations when the user includes the NegotiatedRatesIndicator in the request.

flattened_text: This object, `NegotiatedRateCharges_TotalCharge`, contains information about total charges for Account Based Rates. It includes the currency code (`CurrencyCode`) and the monetary value (`MonetaryValue`). The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value ranges from 0 to 9999999999999999.99. This information is returned only for specific user accounts that are eligible for Account Based Rates and when the `NegotiatedRatesIndicator` is included in the request.

ModifierType.description:
Rate Modifier Type .
Example- "ORM"  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

ModifierDesc.description:
Rate Modifier Description .
Example- "Origin Modifier"  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

Amount.description:
Amount .
Example- "-1.00","0.25"

It contains positive or negative values.  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

NegotiatedRateCharges_RateModifier.description: Container for returned Rate Modifier information.  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for Rate Modifier information in the Negotiated Rate Charges. It includes the Amount (positive or negative values), Modifier Description, and Modifier Type. These properties are applicable for SubVersion 2407 or higher and only for oAuth shipments. The Amount is a string with a length of 16 characters, Modifier Description is a string with a length of 50 characters, and Modifier Type is a string with a length of 3 characters. All three properties are required.

CurrencyCode.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes monetary value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 9999999999999999.99

NegotiatedRateCharges_TotalChargesWithTa.description: TotalChargesWithTaxes container would be returned only if TaxInformationIndicator is present in request. TotalChargesWithTaxes contains total charges including total taxes applied to a shipment.

flattened_text: This object, `NegotiatedRateCharges_TotalChargesWithTaxes`, is returned when tax information is requested. It includes the total charges and taxes for a shipment. It has two properties: `CurrencyCode` for the currency type and `MonetaryValue` for the amount. Both properties are required. The `CurrencyCode` is a 3-character string, and `MonetaryValue` accepts values from 0 to 9999999999999999.99.

HandlingUnits.description:
Handling Unit for Density based rating container.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ShipmentResults_FRSShipmentData.description: Ground Freight Pricing Shipment data container. Ground Freight Pricing shipment data is only guaranteed to be returned for Ground Freight Pricing shipments only.

flattened_text: This data container holds information for Ground Freight Pricing shipments. It includes Freight Density Rate, Handling Units, and Transportation Charges. Handling Units may be returned as an array depending on the API version used. Transportation Charges are required.

DiscountPercentage.description: It indicates the shipment level discount percentage for transportation charges.

FRSShipmentData_TransportationCharges.description: Transportation charges container. Ground Freight Pricing transportation charges. These are only returned for Ground Freight Pricing enabled shipper account number when the user includes the FRSShipmentIndicator in the request.

flattened_text: This container holds transportation charges for ground freight pricing. It is included in the response when the user requests it with a specific indicator. It includes discount amount, discount percentage, gross charge, and net charge. The discount percentage is a string with a length of 1 to 5 characters. The container is required to have all these properties.

CurrencyCode.description: Gross charges currency code.

MonetaryValue.description: Gross charges monetary value.  Valid values are from 0 to 9999999999999999.99

TransportationCharges_GrossCharge.description: Gross Charges container. It indicates the shipment level gross Ground Freight Pricing transportation charges.

flattened_text: This section defines the "TransportationCharges_GrossCharge" object, which represents the gross transportation charges for a shipment. It includes the currency code and monetary value of the charges. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value must be between 0 and 9999999999999999.99. Both the currency code and monetary value are required fields.

CurrencyCode.description: Discount Amount currency code.

MonetaryValue.description: Discount amount monetary value.  Valid values are from 0 to 9999999999999999.99

TransportationCharges_DiscountAmount.description: Discount Amount container. It indicates the shipment level Ground Freight Pricing discount amount for transportation charges

flattened_text: This data structure represents a discount amount for ground freight transportation charges at the shipment level. It includes the currency code and monetary value of the discount. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value ranges from 0 to 9999999999999999.99. Both the currency code and monetary value are required fields.

CurrencyCode.description: Net Charge currency code.

MonetaryValue.description: Net charges monetary value.  Valid values are from 0 to 9999999999999999.99

TransportationCharges_NetCharge.description: Net Charges container. It indicates the shipment level net Ground Freight Pricing transportation charges.

flattened_text: This component, "TransportationCharges_NetCharge," represents the net charges for ground freight pricing at the shipment level. It includes the currency code and monetary value of the charges. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value ranges from 0 to 9999999999999999.99. Both the currency code and monetary value are required fields in this object.

Density.description: Density is returned if the Shipper is eligible for Density based rate.   Valid values are 0 to 999.9

TotalCubicFeet.description: Total Cubic feet is returned if the Shipper is eligible for Density based rate.   Valid values are 0 to 99999.999

FRSShipmentData_FreightDensityRate.description: FreightDensityRate container for Density based rating.

flattened_text: This data structure, "FRSShipmentData_FreightDensityRate," is used for calculating freight rates based on density. It includes properties for "Density" and "Total Cubic Feet," with specific value ranges. Both properties are required.

Quantity.description: Handling Unit Quantity for Density based rating.

flattened_text: This object defines data for a single handling unit in a Freight Rate Shopping System (FRS). It includes properties for adjusted height, dimensions, quantity, and type of handling unit. The quantity is a string with a maximum length of 8 characters and is required for density-based rating. The type, quantity, and dimensions are mandatory fields. The object is represented in XML as "HandlingUnits."

Value.description: Adjusted Height value for the handling unit.  Height Adjustment is done only when Handling unit type is SKD = Skid or PLT = Pallet.

HandlingUnits_AdjustedHeight.description: Container to hold Adjusted Height information.

flattened_text: This container, HandlingUnits_AdjustedHeight, stores information about Adjusted Height. It includes the unit of measurement and the adjusted height value for handling units like Skid or Pallet. The adjusted height value is a string with a maximum length of 19 characters. The container is required to have UnitOfMeasurement and Value properties.

Weight.description: Billing weight. Higher of the actual shipment weight versus the shipment dimensional weight.  When using a negotiated divisor different from the published UPS divisor (139 for inches and 5,000 for cm), the weight returned is based on the published divisor. Rates, however, are based on the negotiated divisor.

flattened_text: This object represents the billing weight of a shipment. It includes the unit of measurement and the billing weight value, which is calculated based on the higher of the actual weight or dimensional weight of the shipment. The weight value is determined using a specific divisor, and rates are based on a negotiated divisor if different. The object is required to have both the unit of measurement and weight properties.

Code.description: Code of the billing weight measurement units. Values are: KGS or LBS.

Description.description: Description of the billing weight measurement units.

BillingWeight_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Billing weight unit of measurement code. The unit of measurement used in Shipment request is returned.

flattened_text: This component defines the unit of measurement for billing weight in a shipment request. It includes a code (either KGS or LBS) and a description. The code must be 3 characters long, and the description must be between 1 and 35 characters. The component is required in the request and is represented in XML as UnitOfMeasurement.

TrackingNumber.description:
Package 1Z number.  
For Mail Innovations shipments, please use the USPSPICNumber when tracking packages (a non-1Z number Mail Manifest Id is returned).

RateModifier.description:
Returned Package Information.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

USPSPICNumber.description: USPSPICNumber is USPS Package Identification; it should be used for tracking Mail Innovations shipments.

CN22Number.description:
USPS defined CN22 ID number format varies based on destination country or territory. 
Not applicable as of Jan 2015. 
Mail Innovations shipments US to VI, PR, and GU are not considered international.

Accessorial.description:
The container for Accessorial indicators. This information would be returned only for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Mid-day service request with Dry Ice or Oversize Pallet and SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707. This is valid only for UPS Worldwide Express Freight and UPS Worldwide Express Freight Mid-day service.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ItemizedCharges.description:
Itemized Charges are returned only when the subversion element is present and greater than or equal to 1607. Package level itemized charges are only returned for US domestic movements.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text:
This component, `ShipmentResults_PackageResults`, contains various details related to a shipment package. It includes information such as accessorial indicators, base service charge, CN22 number, itemized charges, negotiated charges, rate modifier, service options charges, shipping label, shipping receipt, simple rate, tracking number, and USPS PIC number. 

Some key points to note:
- Accessorial indicators are specific to certain UPS services.
- CN22 number format varies based on the destination country.
- Itemized charges are only provided for certain movements.
- Tracking number is a 1Z number, and for Mail Innovations shipments, use the USPSPICNumber for tracking.
- The component is required to have a TrackingNumber field.
- The component is represented as an object in XML with the name `PackageResults`.

CurrencyCode.description: BaseServiceCharge currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description: Base Service Charge value amount.  Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

PackageResults_BaseServiceCharge.description:
Base Service Charge container.
Transportation charge = BaseServiceCharge + Fuel charge  Returned only if Subversion >=1701.

flattened_text: This object, `PackageResults_BaseServiceCharge`, represents the base service charge for a shipment. It includes the currency code and value amount. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the value amount ranges from 0 to 99999999999999.99. This information is returned only for certain versions of the service.

CurrencyCode.description: Package accessorial charges currency code type. The currency code used in the Shipment request is returned.

MonetaryValue.description:
Package accessorial charges value amount.

Valid values are from 0 to 99999999999999.99

PackageResults_ServiceOptionsCharges.description: Shipment charges info. Shipment charges are only guaranteed to be returned for shipments whose origin country or territory is US or Puerto Rico.

flattened_text: This data structure represents shipment charges information. It specifies the currency code and value of accessorial charges for a package. The currency code is a 3-character string, and the monetary value must be between 0 and 99999999999999.99. This information is guaranteed for shipments originating from the US or Puerto Rico.

GraphicImagePart.description:
Base 64 encoded graphic image. Applicable only for Mail Innovations CN22 Combination Forward Label with more than 3 commodities.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

InternationalSignatureGraphicImage.description: Base 64 encoded graphic image of the Warsaw text and signature box. EPL2, ZPL and SPL labels. The image will be returned for non-US based shipments. One image will be given per shipment and it will be in the first PackageResults container.

HTMLImage.description: Base 64 encoded html browser image rendering software. This is only returned for gif and png image formats.

PDF417.description: PDF-417 is a two-dimensional barcode, which can store up to about 1,800 printable ASCII characters or 1,100 binary characters per symbol. The symbol is rectangular. The image is Base 64 encoded and returned if the LabelImageFormat code is GIF. Shipment with PRL return service only.

PackageResults_ShippingLabel.description:
The container for UPS shipping label. Returned for following shipments -
Forward shipments,
Shipments with PRL returns service, 
Electronic Return Label or Electronic Import Control Label shipments with SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707. Shipping label wont be returned if BarCodeImageIndicator is present.

flattened_text: The `PackageResults_ShippingLabel` object contains information about UPS shipping labels. It is returned for various types of shipments, including forward shipments and those with specific services. The object includes properties such as GraphicImage (base 64 encoded graphic image), HTMLImage (base 64 encoded html browser image), and PDF417 (two-dimensional barcode). Some properties are specific to certain label formats or shipment types. The object is required to have GraphicImage and ImageFormat properties.

Code.description: Label image code that the labels are generated. Valid values: EPL = EPL2 SPL = SPL ZPL = ZPL GIF = gif images PNG = PNG images. Only EPL, SPL, ZPL and GIF are currently supported. For multi piece COD shipments, the label image format for the first package will always be a GIF for any form of label requested.

Description.description: Description of the image format.

flattened_text: This defines the Shipping Label Image Format, specifying the code for label generation (EPL, SPL, ZPL, GIF), and a description of the format. The code must be 3 characters long, and the description up to 35 characters. The label for the first package in multi-piece COD shipments will always be a GIF.

GraphicImage.description:
Base 64 encoded receipt in HTML format.

The receipt image is only returned for the first 5 packages.

PackageResults_ShippingReceipt.description:
Supported for following shipments -
PRL shipments,
Electronic Return Label or Electronic Import Control Label shipments with SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707.

flattened_text: This object, `PackageResults_ShippingReceipt`, is used for specific types of shipments like PRL and certain Electronic Return Label shipments. It includes a base64 encoded HTML receipt image for the first 5 packages. The object requires `GraphicImage` and `ImageFormat` properties and is represented in XML as `ShippingReceipt`.

Code.description:
Code representing the format in which a receipt is delivered. Valid values:
- HTML = HTML format

Description.description: Description of the image format code.

flattened_text: This object defines the format of an image for a shipping receipt. It includes a code (e.g., HTML) and a description of the code. The code must be a string of 1 to 4 characters, and the description must be a string of 1 to 35 characters. The code is required.

Code.description: Code for Accessorial Indicator.

Description.description: Description for Accessorial Indicator.

flattened_text: This data structure defines the Accessorial package results. It includes a code and description for the accessorial indicator. The code is a 3-character string, and the description is up to 50 characters long. The code is required.

Code.description: Simple Rate Package Size Valid values: XS -  Extra Small S -  Small M -  Medium L - Large XL - Extra Large

PackageResults_SimpleRate.description: SimpleRate will be returned if Simple Rate  present in request

flattened_text: The `PackageResults_SimpleRate` object represents a simple rate package size that can be returned in the response. It includes a `Code` property with valid values of XS, S, M, L, and XL. The `Code` property is required and must be a string of length 2.

Code.description:
Code that indicates the type of form.  Valid values:
- 01 - All Requested International Forms.

Description.description: Description that indicates the type of form.  Possible Values: All Requested International Forms.

FormGroupId.description: Unique Id for later retrieval of saved version of the completed international forms.

FormGroupIdName.description: Contains description text which identifies the group of International forms. This element is part of both request and response. This element does not appear on the forms.

PackageResults_Form.description:
Container tag for the International forms image.  Currently this container would be returned for UPS Premium Care shipments. Form is returned for following shipments -
Forward shipments,
Shipments with PRL ReturnService,
Electronic Return Label or Electronic Import Control Label shipments with SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707. CN22 data for Worlwide economy services will be returned within the PDF417 barcode of the label.

flattened_text: The `PackageResults_Form` object is a container for international forms images related to specific UPS Premium Care shipments. It includes information about the type of form, a unique ID for saved forms, and a description of the form group. The form's image is referenced in a separate schema. This object is limited to a maximum of one instance. The form's code, description, form group ID, and form group ID name have specific character length restrictions and valid value options. The CN22 data for Worldwide economy services is included in the PDF417 barcode of the label.

ShipmentResults_Form_Image.description: Container tag for the International forms image.

flattened_text: This object represents an International forms image for shipment results. It includes a base 64 encoded image and the image format. The image is required and can only have one format.

Form_Image.description: Container tag for the International forms image.

flattened_text: This object represents an International forms image. It contains a base 64 encoded image and its format. The image is required, and only one image is allowed. The object is named "Image" in XML.

Code.description:
Code representing the format in which the High Value Report is generated.

Valid values:
- PDF = pdf.

Description.description: Description of the High Value Report image format code.

HighValueReport_Image_ImageFormat.description: Container for the High Value Report image format information for Import Control Shipments.

flattened_text: This section defines the image format for High Value Report in Import Control Shipments. It includes a code (3 characters) and a description (up to 35 characters). The valid code values are PDF. The code is required, and only one image format is allowed.

Code.description:
Format code of the generated COD Turn In Page.

- HTML = HTML format.

Only HTML format is supported for COD Turn In Page.

Description.description: Description of the form image format code.

CODTurnInPage_Image_ImageFormat.description: The container for format of COD Turn In Page.

flattened_text: This component defines the format of a COD Turn In Page image. It includes a format code (e.g., HTML) and a description of the format. Only HTML format is supported for COD Turn In Page images.

Code.description:
Code representing the format in which the forms are generated. Valid values:
- PDF = pdf

Description.description: Description of the form image format code.

ShipmentResults_Image_ImageFormat.description: Container tag for the International forms image format information.

flattened_text: This section defines the format for international forms images in a shipment result. It includes a code (e.g., PDF) and a description of the format. The code must be a 3-character string, and the description must be up to 35 characters long. The code is required.

Code.description: Code representing the format in which the forms are generated. Valid values: PDF = pdf, PNG = png

Description.description: Description of the form image format code.

Image_ImageFormat.description: Container tag for the International forms image format information.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for storing information about international forms image formats. It includes properties for a code representing the format (PDF or PNG) and a description of the format. The code must be a 3-character string, and the description must be up to 35 characters long. The code property is required.

Code.description: Identification code for itemized charge.

Description.description: Description of Itemized Charge that had been charged.

CurrencyCode.description: The IATA currency code associated with the Itemized Charge costs for the shipment.

MonetaryValue.description: Itemized Charges value amount.

flattened_text: This data structure defines itemized charges for a package, including a code, currency code, description, monetary value, and sub-type. The code is a 3-character identification code, the currency code is a 3-character IATA currency code, and the description is up to 50 characters long. The monetary value is a string up to 19 characters long. The sub-type is a string up to 50 characters long. The CurrencyCode, MonetaryValue, and Code fields are required.

ItemizedCharges.description:
Negotiated Itemized Accessorial and SurCharges.

Negotiated itemized charges are only returned for certain contract-only shipments as well as Worldwide Express Freight, Ground Freight Pricing, and Hazmat movements. Negotiated Itemized Accessorial and Sur Charges are returned only when the subversion element is present and greater than or equal to 1607.

Package level itemized charges are only returned for US domestic movements

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2403, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using versions < v2403, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

PackageResults_NegotiatedCharges.description:
Negotiated Rates Charge Container.  These charges are returned when:
1) Subversion is greater than or equal to 1607
2) If negotiated rates were requested for GFP shipments and account number is eligible to receive negotiated rates.

flattened_text: This container holds negotiated rates charges for shipments meeting specific criteria. It includes negotiated itemized accessorial and surcharges for certain types of shipments. The element will be returned as an array for versions >= v2403 and as a single object for versions < v2403 if there is only one.

Code.description: Identification code for itemized charge.

Description.description: Description of Itemized Charge that had been charged.

CurrencyCode.description: The IATA currency code associated with the Itemized Charge costs for the shipment.

MonetaryValue.description: Itemized Charges value amount.

flattened_text: This data structure defines itemized charges for a shipment. It includes properties such as a unique identification code, currency code, description, value amount, and sub-type. The identification code, currency code, and value amount are required fields. The maximum length for the description, monetary value, and sub-type is specified.

ModifierType.description:
Rate Modifier Type .
Example- "ORM"  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

ModifierDesc.description:
Rate Modifier Description .
Example- "Origin Modifier"  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

Amount.description:
Amount .
Example- "-1.00","0.25"

It contains positive or negative values.  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

NegotiatedCharges_RateModifier.description: Container for returned Rate Modifier information.  Applies if SubVersion is 2407 or greater and supports only for oAuth shipments.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for Rate Modifier information related to negotiated charges. It is applicable for SubVersion 2407 or higher and only for oAuth shipments. The container includes three properties: Amount (positive or negative values), ModifierDesc (description of the rate modifier), and ModifierType (type of rate modifier). All three properties are required and have specific length constraints. The overall structure is represented as an object named RateModifier in XML format.

ModifierType.description: Rate Modifier Type. Example: "ORM". Applies only if SubVersion is 2205 or greater.

ModifierDesc.description: Rate Modifier Description. Example: "Origin Modifier". Applies only if SubVersion is 2205 or greater.

Amount.description: Amount. Example: "-1.00","0.25". It contains positive or negative values. Applies only if SubVersion is 2205 or greater.

PackageResults_RateModifier.description: Container for returned Rate Modifier information. Applies only if SubVersion is 2205 or greater.

flattened_text: This container holds information about Rate Modifiers, which are adjustments to rates. It includes the Amount (positive or negative values), Modifier Description, and Modifier Type. This applies if the SubVersion is 2205 or higher. The required fields are ModifierType, ModifierDesc, CurrencyCode, and Amount.

GraphicImage.description: Base 64 encoded html, EPL2, ZPL or SPL image.

flattened_text: This object represents the control log receipt for shipment results. It includes a base64 encoded image in formats like html, EPL2, ZPL, or SPL. The object requires both the graphic image and the image format to be included.

Code for the type of Graphic Image for the High Value Report.

Valid values:
- EPL = EPL2 (when user requests label in EPL2 format)
- SPL = SPL (when user requests label in SPL format)

flattened_text: This object, ControlLogReceipt_ImageFormat, is used to specify the format of a High Value report image. It contains two properties: Code, which indicates the type of graphic image format (EPL, SPL, ZPL, or HTML), and Description, which provides a brief description of the format code. The Code property is required and must be a string with a maximum length of 4 characters. The Description property is optional and can be up to 35 characters long.

Code.description:
Code that indicates the type of form.

Valid values: 01 - All Requested International Forms.

FormGroupIdName.description: Contains description text which identifies the group of International forms. This element is part of both request and response. This element does not appear on the forms.

ShipmentResults_Form.description:
Container tag for the International forms image.   Form is returned for following shipments -
Forward shipments,
Shipments with PRL ReturnService,
Electronic Return Label or Electronic Import Control Label shipments with SubVersion greater than or equal to 1707.

flattened_text: The `ShipmentResults_Form` object is a container for international forms images related to various types of shipments. It includes a code indicating the form type, a description of the form, a unique ID for retrieving saved forms, and a description of the form group. The object can only contain one form image. The form code can be '01' for all requested international forms. The `Image` property references the schema for the form image.

ShipmentResults_CODTurnInPage.description: The container of the COD Turn In Page.

flattened_text: This object represents the COD Turn In Page for shipment results. It contains an Image property that references the CODTurnInPage_Image schema. The Image property is required and there can be a maximum of one COD Turn In Page in the container.

ShipmentResults_HighValueReport.description: Container for the High Value Report generated for ImportControl or Return shipments with high package declared value.

flattened_text: This object, "ShipmentResults_HighValueReport," holds the High Value Report for shipments with high declared values. It includes an "Image" property that references the schema for the report's image. The object is required to have an image and is represented in XML as "HighValueReport."

GraphicImage.description: Base 64 encoded High Value Report image.

HighValueReport_Image.description: Container tag for the High Value Report image.

flattened_text: This defines a container for the High Value Report image. It includes a base64 encoded image and references the image format. The image and format are required properties within this object.

This object is a wrapper for a void shipment request. It contains one property, VoidShipmentRequest, which refers to the schema defining the void shipment request. The VoidShipmentRequest property is required and the object is represented in XML as VoidShipmentRequest.
This response wrapper contains information about voiding a shipment. It includes the VoidShipmentResponse schema and is required in the response. The maximum number of responses is 1.
This is a container for voiding a shipment request. It includes a request and details about the shipment to be voided. Both the request and shipment details are required.

RequestOption.description: Optional processing. No options  Not used. Left for future uses

flattened_text: This YAML defines a request for voiding a shipment. It includes an optional processing option for future use and a transaction reference. The request is represented as an object named VoidShipmentRequest_Request in XML format.

CustomerContext.description: The CustomerContext Information which will be echoed during response.

VoidRequest_TransactionReference.description: TransactionReference identifies transactions between client and server.

flattened_text: This object, VoidRequest_TransactionReference, is used to identify transactions between a client and server. It includes a property called CustomerContext, which holds information echoed in the response. The CustomerContext is a string with a maximum length of 512 characters.

ShippingHistoryUserKey.description: Unique key to tag shipments in shipping history. It could be MyUPS registration Number or any unique identifier.

ShipmentIdentificationNumber.description: The shipment's identification number  Alpha-numeric. Must pass 1Z rules. Must be upper case.
