OAuth2.description:
Find your Client ID and Secret on your app info page.
1. Select \"Try It\"
2. In the Security section enter your Client ID and Secret.
3. Select \"Request Token\"
4. Enter any additional information in the Body and Parameters sections.
5. Select \"Send\" to execute your API request

flattened_text:
To use OAuth2 for authentication, find your Client ID and Secret on your app info page. Follow these steps:

1. Select "Try It".
2. Enter your Client ID and Secret in the Security section.
3. Click "Request Token".
4. Add any extra information in the Body and Parameters sections.
5. Click "Send" to run your API request.

OAuth2 uses client credentials and the token URL is at https://wwwcie.ups.com/security/v1/oauth/token. The authentication method is client_secret_basic.

This component, LOCATORRequestWrapper, is an object that wraps a LocatorRequest. It can only contain one LocatorRequest and is required to have this property. The XML element name for this object is LocatorRequest.

This response wrapper contains a single property called LocatorResponse, which refers to the LocatorResponse schema. The LocatorResponse property is required and the wrapper is of type object. The XML element name for this wrapper is LocatorResponse.

LocationID.description: Location ID is the identification number of the UPS affiliated location.

AllowAllConfidenceLevels.description: Indicator to allow confidence level in search.

SearchOptionCode.description:
Valid values: 
01-Proximity Search Details
02-Address Search Details
03-Proximity Search Summary
04-Address Search Summary
05-Freight Will Call Search. 
Either OptionType 03 or 04 is required.

FreightIndicator.description: FreightIndicator. Required for Freight Location Search.

flattened_text: The `LocatorRequest` object is used to request location information from UPS. It includes properties like `AllowAllConfidenceLevels`, `FreightIndicator`, `LocationID`, `LocationSearchCriteria`, `OriginAddress`, `Request`, `SearchOptionCode`, `ServiceGeoUnit`, `SortCriteria`, `Translate`, and `UnitOfMeasurement`. Some properties are required, such as `Request`, `OriginAddress`, and `Translate`. The `SearchOptionCode` property specifies the type of search to perform. The `LocationID` property is an array of location identification numbers.

RequestAction.description:
Indicates the action to be taken by the XML service. 
The only valid value is 'Locator'.

flattened_text: This API request is for locating a specific item. It includes a RequestAction field with the value 'Locator' to specify the action. The TransactionReference field refers to another schema for additional details. The request is in XML format and must include the RequestAction field.

CustomerContext.description: The client uses CustomerContext to synchronize request/response pairs. The client establishes CustomerContext, which can contain any information client want, as long as it is valid XML; it is echoed back by the server

Request_TransactionReference.description: TransactionReference identifies transactions between client and server.

flattened_text: This object, Request_TransactionReference, is used to identify transactions between a client and server. It includes a property called CustomerContext, which the client can use to synchronize request/response pairs. The CustomerContext can contain any valid XML information and will be echoed back by the server. The maximum length of the TransactionReference is 512 characters.

MaximumListSize.description:
If present, indicates the maximum number of locations the client wishes to receive in an address candidate response where the provided origin information is insufficient to accurately establish location. 

Valid values: 1-50, default 10

flattened_text: This component, `LocatorRequest_OriginAddress`, holds details about the origin address. It includes fields for the address key format and geocode. The `MaximumListSize` field specifies the maximum number of locations the client wants in the response when the origin information is not precise enough. Valid values range from 1 to 50, with a default of 10. The `AddressKeyFormat` field is required.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the origin address or the center point of the area code.

Longitude.description: The longitude of the origin address or the center point of the area code.

OriginAddress_Geocode.description: Geocode is the latitude and longitude of the origin address.

flattened_text: This data structure represents the geocode (latitude and longitude) of the origin address. It includes properties for Latitude and Longitude, each with a maximum length of 15 characters. Both Latitude and Longitude are required fields. The data is structured as an object named Geocode.

ConsigneeName.description: Name. Not relevant for this tool

AddressLine.description: Address Line Information. The user may submit street level address information or provide Intersection information.

PoliticalDivision3.description: Barrio or other sub-division of City

PostcodePrimaryLow.description: Main postal code. Required if the user does not submit the City, State/Province address combination.

PostcodeExtendedLow.description: 4 Digit postal code extension. Valid for US only.

CountryCode.description: Two-character country or territory abbreviation

SingleLineAddress.description:
Single line search information. Can contain values of origin address in a single line. Will override other origin address information.

Conditionally Required for Non-Postal Code Countries. Applicable Country Ireland (IE)

SingleLineAddress used for the lookup

SingleLineAddress (Format - CSV) (\"Values:\" + postalCode + city + state + address + landmark	+ phoneNumber)

OriginAddress_AddressKeyFormat.description:
Contains all of the basic information about the origin such as: Address Lines, City, State/Province, Postal Code and Country or Territory Code. 
The element CountryCode is required.

flattened_text: This object, "OriginAddress_AddressKeyFormat," contains essential information about the origin address, including address lines, city, state/province, postal code, and country code. It includes fields for address details like street information, country abbreviation, state, city, and postal code extensions. Some fields are required, such as country code, state, address line, and primary postal code. The object is structured to capture key origin address data for various locations.

Locale.description:
Locale is the 5 digit combination of 2 character language code and 2 character country or territory code separated by an underscore ('_') character. Will be used to determine what language the response will be sent in. 
Default value is: en_US. 
Examples are: fr_CA, es_MX.

LocatorRequest_Translate.description: Contains the locale information for the request.

flattened_text: This object, `LocatorRequest_Translate`, contains locale information for a request. It includes a property called `Locale`, which is a 5-digit combination of a 2-character language code and a 2-character country or territory code separated by an underscore. The default value is `en_US`, and examples include `fr_CA` and `es_MX`. The `Locale` property will determine the language of the response.

Code.description:
Valid values are:

- MI-Miles
- KM-Kilometers

LocatorRequest_UnitOfMeasurement.description: Distance unit of measurement. This is required for location requests (request option 1).

flattened_text: This object defines the unit of measurement for distance in location requests. The valid values are "MI-Miles" and "KM-Kilometers". The "Code" property is required.

MaximumListSize.description: If present, indicates the maximum number of locations the client wishes to receive in response; ranges from 1 to 50 with a default value of 5.

SearchRadius.description:
Defines the maximum radius the user wishes to search for a UPS location. If the user does not specify, the default value is 100 miles. Whole numbers only. 

Valid values are:
5-100 for UnitOfMeasure MI
5-150 for UnitOfMesaure KM

BrexitFilter.description: Brexit Filter. Applicable for country code GB; Pass the PostalCode for the address in the location search if Brexit functionality is desired. UAPs with postal code starts with BT returned when brexit filter starts with BT, else UAPs returned with non BT postal code. Applicable for UAP and Proximal building search.

LocatorRequest_LocationSearchCriteria.description:
The Location search criteria container allows the user to further define the basis to which they wish to receive the UPS locations. 
Only relevant when the user requests a Location search (request option 1).

flattened_text: The `LocatorRequest_LocationSearchCriteria` object defines criteria for searching UPS locations. It includes options like Access Point search, Brexit filter for UK addresses, maximum list size, search radius, and service search. Users can specify search parameters like postal code, search radius, and maximum number of locations to receive. The default search radius is 100 miles. The object is used when requesting UPS location search.

LocationSearchCriteria_SearchOption.description:
SearchOption contains the information that forms the basis of the location search, It contains the criteria for search by Locations, Retail Locations, Additional Services, or Program Types.

There should be one container for each type of search the user may wish to do. The user can specify either search by Locations or Retail Locations, but not both.

If this container is missing, the default search would be for The UPS Store, UPS Center, UPS Drop Box, and Authorized Shipping Outlet location types.

flattened_text: This component, LocationSearchCriteria_SearchOption, defines the criteria for location searches. It includes options for searching by Locations, Retail Locations, Additional Services, or Program Types. Users can specify one type of search at a time. If not specified, the default search includes The UPS Store, UPS Center, UPS Drop Box, and Authorized Shipping Outlet locations. The component includes OptionCode, OptionType, and Relation properties, with OptionCode and OptionType being required.

Code.description:
Code for Option type valid values are:

- 01-Location
- 02-Retail Location
- 03-Additional Services
- 04-Program Type
- 05-Service Level Option.
- 06-End Point Service Offering

SearchOption_OptionType.description:
OptionType is a container that indicates the type of search for locations. There are 5 types of search. They are search by: Location, Retail Location, Additional Services, Program Type, and a Service Level Option. 
If search criteria by Location or Retail Location is not provided the default search of The UPS Store, UPS Center, UPS Drop Box, and Authorized Shipping Outlet location types will be performed.

flattened_text: The `SearchOption_OptionType` object defines the type of search for locations, with options including Location, Retail Location, Additional Services, Program Type, and Service Level Option. If the search criteria for Location or Retail Location is not provided, the default search will include The UPS Store, UPS Center, UPS Drop Box, and Authorized Shipping Outlet locations. The `Code` property specifies the valid values for the search type.

Code.description:
These codes vary by country. It is strongly recommended that clients contact UPS to retrieve the primary search indicator and the valid Location Types and Service Level Options for each country or territory.

Refer to Location Search Option Codes in the Appendix for additional information.

SearchOption_OptionCode.description:
Option code contains the information of a particular Location, Retail Location, Additional Service, Program Type or End Point Service Offering depending on the option type. 
The SearchOptions can contain one or more OptionCodes which forms the criteria for the location search.

flattened_text: The `SearchOption_OptionCode` object represents a specific code related to a location, retail location, additional service, program type, or endpoint service offering. This code is used as a criteria for location searches. The `Code` property within this object contains country-specific codes and is limited to a maximum length of 10 characters. It is recommended to contact UPS for primary search indicators and valid location types and service level options for each country.

Code.description:
Applicable for Additional Services and Program Types.

Valid values:

- 01 - And (Default)
- 02 - Or

SearchOption_Relation.description:
The relation container will contain the relation parameter (And/Or) that has to be used among multiple option codes in the location search. 

This is only applicable to option type Additional Services and Program Types. If this container is not present for Additional Services and Program Types, the default relation of And is used.

flattened_text: The `SearchOption_Relation` object defines how to combine multiple option codes in a location search for Additional Services and Program Types. It specifies whether to use "And" or "Or" as the relation parameter. If not specified, the default is "And." The `Code` property contains the valid values: "01" for "And" (default) and "02" for "Or."

Time.description: Scheduled Local Drop-off Time. Format: HHMM

LocationSearchCriteria_ServiceSearch.description: Allows for users to further define the search criteria. Refer to the rules specified in Service Search section.

flattened_text: This criteria allows users to refine their search for services. Users can specify a service code, service option code, and scheduled drop-off time. The drop-off time should be in HHMM format. Only one criteria can be selected.

Code.description:
Code indicating the different services. Valid values are:
01-Ground.
02-Air.
03-Express
04-Standard
05-International (Only avialable July 17)

ServiceSearch_ServiceCode.description:
Container that contains the service information such as Ground/Air.
Required if the customer provides ServiceSearch Time.

flattened_text: This object, `ServiceSearch_ServiceCode`, holds service information like Ground or Air. It must be provided if the customer gives a ServiceSearch Time. The `Code` property indicates different services with values like Ground, Air, Express, Standard, and International (available only on July 17). The `Code` property is a string with a length of 2 characters.

Code.description:
Code that defines the optional service.

Valid values:
- 01 - Saturday pickup.

Only valid for air service.

ServiceSearch_ServiceOptionCode.description: Container for the optional service information such as Saturday Pick up.

flattened_text: This object, `ServiceSearch_ServiceOptionCode`, holds optional service details like Saturday pickup. It includes a `Code` property that defines the optional service, with a maximum length of 2 characters. The valid value for `Code` is '01' for Saturday pickup, applicable only for air service. The `Code` property is required and the object is named `ServiceOptionCode` in XML.

FreightWillCallRequestType.description:
Valid values are: 
1 - Postal Code
2 - Delivery SLIC
3 - Delivery City/State.
1: Freight Will Call Search based on Postal Code, this search is valid for Postal code countries. 2: Freight Will Call Search based on SLIC. 3: Freight Will Call Search based on City and/or State. This Search is valid for non-postal code Countries

OriginOrDestination.description:
OriginOrDestination is required for FreightWillCallRequestType 1 and type 3 . Valid values:
01-Origin facilities
02-Destination facilities.

FormatPostalCode.description:
FormatPostalCode would be required in the request when FreightWillCallRequestType is 1. Valid values are:
NFR-No format requested
FR-format requested
FS-format and search
NVR-No validation requested.

DayOfWeekCode.description:
Day Of week Code. Valid Values are 1 to 7. 
1-Sunday
2-Monday 
3-Tuesday 
4-Wednesday
5-Thursday
6-Friday
7-Saturday.

LocationSearchCriteria_FreightWillCallSe.description: Freight Will Call Search Container. Required if SearchOption is '05-Freight Will Call Search'

flattened_text: This container is used for searching freight will call information. It includes criteria like the day of the week, facility address, postal code format, request type, and origin/destination. The search options are based on postal code, delivery SLIC, or city/state. The container is required for specific search options and must include the freight request type, origin/destination, postal code format, and facility address.

SLIC.description: Facility SLIC. Required for Freight Will call search if FreightWillCallRequestType is 2.

AddressLine.description: Address line

City.description: City. Required for Freight Will call search if FreightWillCallRequestType is 3.

PostalCodePrimaryLow.description: Postal code. Required for Freight Will call search if FreightWillCallRequestType is 1.

PostalCodeExtendedLow.description: 4 Digit postal code extension. Valid for US only.

State.description: State. Required if FrieghtWillCallRequestType is 3 if State is available.

CountryCode.description: Country or territory code.

flattened_text: This data structure represents a facility address for a freight will call search. It includes fields for address line, city, country code, postal codes, SLIC, and state. Depending on the type of freight will call request, certain fields are required. The address line can have up to 2 strings of maximum 64 characters each. The country code must be provided. The structure is represented as an object named FacilityAddress in XML.

PublicAccessPointID.description: The Public Access Point ID to use for UPS Access Point Search. Once this parameter is present , address or geocode search is ignored. It cannot be combined with AccountNumber search parameter.

AccessPointStatus.description:
Status of UPS Access Point. Valid values are: 
01-Active-available
07-Active-unavailable.

AccountNumber.description: The account number to use for UPS Access Point Search in the country or territory. Used to locate a private network for the account. Once this parameter is present any access point address or geocode search is ignored. It cannot be combined with PublicAccessPointID search parameter.

ExactMatchIndicator.description: Presence of this tag represents that "AccessPointSearchByAddress" service is requested. The value of this tag is ignored.

ExistIndicator.description: Presence of this tag represents that "AccessPointAvailability" service is requested. The value of this tag is ignored.

LocationSearchCriteria_AccessPointSearch.description: Applicable for request option 64 only. This contains inclusion and exclusion criteria for address search. It also contains Account Number and Access Point Public ID search elements.

flattened_text: This object, `LocationSearchCriteria_AccessPointSearch`, is used for a specific request option. It includes criteria for address search, Account Number, and Access Point Public ID search elements. The object has properties like AccessPointStatus, AccountNumber, ExactMatchIndicator, ExcludeFromResult, ExistIndicator, IncludeCriteria, and PublicAccessPointID. These properties define various aspects of the UPS Access Point search, such as status, account number, and search indicators.

AccessPointSearch_IncludeCriteria.description: This contains elements to refine (include) UPS Access point address or geocode Search.

flattened_text: The `AccessPointSearch_IncludeCriteria` object is used to refine UPS Access Point address or geocode searches. It includes elements like Merchant Account Number List, Search Filter, and Service Offering List. Only one instance of this object is allowed.

MerchantAccountNumber.description: Account number to be used for a private network access point search where a UPS access point candidate list is obtained in search by address or geocode search.

IncludeCriteria_MerchantAccountNumberLis.description: This contains the list of Merchant Account numbers to be used for finding private network access points.

flattened_text: This object, `IncludeCriteria_MerchantAccountNumberList`, is used to specify a list of Merchant Account numbers for finding private network access points. It allows for providing one account number for searching UPS access points based on address or geocode. The account number must be a string between 6 and 10 characters.

DCRIndicator.description: DCR/DCO Availability indicator for UPS Access Point. Either this indicator is present or not present. Presence indicates a search for access points with DCR. Any data in the element is ignored.

ShippingAvailabilityIndicator.description: Shipping Availability indicator for UPS Access Point. Either this indicator is present or not present. Presence indicates a search of access points with shipping availability. Any data in it is ignored.

ShipperPreparationDelay.description: Value for the number of days to check for shipping availability from the current day. When this value is present, ShippingAvailabilityIndicator is implied implicitly.

ClickAndCollectSortWithDistance.description: This contains the distance (in given UnitOfMeasurement) wherin to sort the click and collect access point locations above other access point locations when a UPS Access Point candidate list is obtained in search by address or geocode search.

IncludeCriteria_SearchFilter.description: Container to hold one or more search criteria for UPS Access Points that allow DCR, Shipping and ClickAndCollect access. Only applicable when the UPS access point candidate list is obtained in search by address or geocode search.

flattened_text: This container holds search criteria for UPS Access Points that allow DCR, Shipping, and ClickAndCollect access. It is used when obtaining a list of UPS access points through address or geocode search. The container includes criteria for sorting ClickAndCollect locations by distance, indicating DCR availability, specifying a preparation delay for shipping availability, and indicating shipping availability. The container can only hold one set of criteria.

IncludeCriteria_ServiceOfferingList.description: Container to hold end point service offering List for UPS Access point. Applicable only when a UPS Access Point candidate list is obtained in search by address or geocode search.

flattened_text: This container holds a list of service offerings for UPS Access Point. It is used when retrieving a list of UPS Access Point candidates through address or geocode search. The container can only include one service offering. The main property is "ServiceOffering," which is an array of service offerings.

Code.description:
The valid values are: 
001-Direct To Retail
002-Not In One ADL
003-Click and Collect
004-Retail to Retail
005-Pickup
006-Drop Off
007-PUDO
008-Early Pickup Delivery Time
009-Accept prepaid drop offs
010-DCO DCR intercept accepted 
011-Accepts Payments 
012-Pay At Store
013-Accepts Restricted Articles

Description.description: Description of the service offering. Text will be displayed in the locale requested.

flattened_text: This API defines a service offering with a unique code and description. The code must be a 3-character string from a predefined list. The description provides details about the service offering and is limited to 35 characters. Both code and description are required fields.

BusinessClassificationCode.description: This contains the business classification code to exclude from UPS Access Point Search by address or geocode. Multiple codes can are possible in separate elements. Please refer to Appendix D for detailed business codes.

BusinessName.description: This contains the business name to exclude from UPS Access Point Search by address or geocode. Partial names are accepted.

Radius.description: Public Access points within Radius (in specified Unit of Measure) of any included private access points will be excluded from the results. Valid only if at least one IncludeCriteria/MerchantAccountNumber is provided.

AccessPointSearch_ExcludeFromResult.description: This contains elements to exclude from UPS Access Point address or geocode search.

flattened_text: This object, `AccessPointSearch_ExcludeFromResult`, is used to specify elements to exclude from a UPS Access Point address or geocode search. It includes properties such as `BusinessClassificationCode` for excluding specific business classification codes, `BusinessName` for excluding specific business names, `PostalCodeList` for referencing a list of postal codes to exclude, and `Radius` for excluding public access points within a specified radius of private access points. The object can only contain a maximum of one exclusion criteria.

ExcludeFromResult_PostalCodeList.description: Container to hold a list of postal codes to exclude from the access point address or geocode search.

flattened_text: This container holds a list of postal codes that should be excluded from address or geocode searches. It can only contain one postal code. The required property is "PostalCode," which is an array of postal codes. The XML name for this object is "PostalCodeList."

PostalCodeList_PostalCode.description: Container to hold the postal code .

flattened_text: This data structure represents a postal code, which can include a primary and secondary postal code. The primary postal code is required and can be up to 10 characters long. The secondary postal code is optional and can also be up to 10 characters long. The structure is named "PostalCode" in XML format.

DayOfWeekCode.description:
Day Of week Code.
Valid values:
1-Sunday
2-Monday
3-Tuesday
4-Wednesday
5-Thursday
6-Friday
7-Saturday

LocationSearchCriteria_OpenTimeCriteria.description: Container to hold open times of the Location.

flattened_text: This object, LocationSearchCriteria_OpenTimeCriteria, holds information about the open times of a location. It includes the day of the week (using numeric codes from 1 to 7, representing Sunday to Saturday), the opening time (in HHMM format), and the closing time (also in HHMM format).

SortType.description:
For different sort type. Valid values:
01-Closest Location
02-Deadline for Drop-off by Air/Express
03-Deadline for Drop-off by Ground/Standard
04-Latest Close Time
05-Earliest Open Time.

flattened_text: This component defines the sorting criteria for locating a specific item. It includes a property called SortType, which specifies the type of sorting to be applied. The valid values for SortType range from closest location to earliest open time. The SortType property is a string with a length between 1 and 2 characters.

ServiceCode.description:
Service Code. Required if ServiceGeoUnit Container present. 
Valid value is '096' .

GeoPoliticalUnit.description:
GeoPoliticalUnit. Required if ServiceGeoUnit container present.
Valid value is '002' .

LocatorRequest_ServiceGeoUnit.description: ServiceGeoUnit Container. Required to search for the freight facility information

flattened_text: This object, `LocatorRequest_ServiceGeoUnit`, is used to search for freight facility information. It contains two properties: `GeoPoliticalUnit` and `ServiceCode`. Both properties are required and have specific valid values. The `GeoPoliticalUnit` must be '002' and the `ServiceCode` must be '096'.

AllowAllConfidenceLevels.description:
Confidence level.
Valid values: True or False

flattened_text: The `LocatorResponse` object contains information about a location search response. It includes properties for allowing all confidence levels, geocode details, response data, and search results. The object requires the `Response`, `AllowAllConfidenceLevels`, and `SearchResults` properties. The object is represented in XML as `LocatorResponse`.

ResponseStatusCode.description:
Identifies the success or failure of the interchange. 
1-Success
0-Failure

flattened_text: This component, `LocatorResponse_Response`, is a container for a response. It includes properties such as `Error`, `ResponseStatusCode`, `ResponseStatusDescription`, and `TransactionReference`. The `ResponseStatusCode` indicates success or failure (1 for success, 0 for failure), while `ResponseStatusDescription` provides a description of the status code. The component is required to have `ResponseStatusCode` and is represented as an object in XML with the name `Response`.

CustomerContext.description: Customer provided data. If this data is present in the request, it is echoed back to the customer.

XpciVersion.description:
Identifies the version of the message. 
Current version is 1.0014

Response_TransactionReference.description: Container for customer provided data and the XPCI Version.

flattened_text: This response object, "TransactionReference," contains customer-provided data and the XPCI Version. It includes two properties: CustomerContext (up to 512 characters) and XpciVersion (exactly 6 characters, currently version 1.0014). The object is limited to a single instance.

ErrorSeverity.description:
Describes the severity of the error. 
For additional information, refer to Locator Error Codes in the Appendix.

ErrorCode.description:
A numeric value that describes the error. Each tool defines a range of error codes. 
For additional information, refer to Locator Error Codes in the Appendix.

MinimumRetrySeconds.description:
Number of seconds to wait until retry. 

This field is populated on special conditions of the Transient Error only, as defined by the service.

A number between 1 and 86400 (24 hours)

ErrorLocation.description:
Identifies the element in error.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ErrorDigest.description:
The contents of the element in error.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Response_Error.description: If an error is encountered during the interchange, the Response contains an error. If the error is present, then the ErrorSeverity and ErrorCode are required.

flattened_text: When an error occurs during data exchange, the response will include details about the error. The error must include severity and a specific error code. The error code is a numeric value that varies by tool. The error description provides additional context. The error location identifies the element causing the issue. The error severity indicates the seriousness of the error. In some cases, a minimum retry time may be provided for transient errors. The error details are structured in an object format named "Error" in the response.

ErrorLocationElementName.description: The Xpath name of the element in error. This is a valid Xpath pointing to an element in the request document.

ErrorLocationAttributeName.description: The name of the attribute in error. This is the name of the attribute contained by the Error Location element.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure of an error location object, which contains information about the attribute and Xpath element causing an error. The object includes properties for the attribute name and Xpath element name, with specific character length constraints. The object is named "ErrorLocation" and is used to identify the location of errors in a request document.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the origin address, center point of the exchange, center point of the postal code, or center point of the city.

Longitude.description: The longitude of the origin address, center point of the exchange, center point of the postal code, or center point of the city.

LocatorResponse_Geocode.description: Geocode is the latitude and longitude of the origin address. The Geocode is provided in the first successful response. Required to be returned when the origin address or phone number is submitted in the request.Will not be returned when the  requestoption =64

flattened_text: The LocatorResponse_Geocode object contains the latitude and longitude of the origin address. It is returned in the first successful response when the origin address or phone number is provided in the request. This information is not returned when the request option is set to 64. The object includes the Latitude and Longitude properties, both of type string. Both Latitude and Longitude are required fields.

GeocodeCandidate.description:
If the origin address provided in the location request document does not have a match, a list of candidate addresses, geocodes and optionally a landmark will be returned.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

Disclaimer.description:
Disclaimer. In the event the user requested Ground and Air service types and the maximum UPS locations list size has not been met, the list of locations will continue with locations that provide either ground or air within the search radius. 

The disclaimer will note this deviation from the requested search criteria. The disclaimer is also the location where the user will receive information regarding a one-time pickup option if the first location is greater than 20 miles from the origin.

DropLocation.description:
When a location request is submitted with a valid origin address, UPS locations will be returned.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

AvailableLocationAttributes.description:
This container contains the information about the currently existing Retail Locations or Additional Services or Program types.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

ActiveAvailableAccessPointIndicator.description:
Indicates whether the country or territory has AccessPoints or not. 

This tag is populated in the Response only if tag "ExistIndicator" was present in the Locator request.

flattened_text:
The `LocatorResponse_SearchResults` object contains search results for locations. It includes information about available access points, location attributes, disclaimers, drop locations, and geocode candidates. 

- `ActiveAvailableAccessPointIndicator`: Indicates if the country has access points.
- `AvailableLocationAttributes`: Contains details about existing locations or services.
- `Disclaimer`: Provides information about location deviations and pickup options.
- `DropLocation`: Lists UPS locations based on the origin address.
- `GeocodeCandidate`: Lists candidate addresses if no match is found for the origin address. 

For versions >= v2, elements are returned as arrays. The XML name for this object is `SearchResults`.

LandmarkName.description: If a Landmark code was provided in the request, a candidate list of Landmark Names will be returned along with the corresponding address and Geocode.

flattened_text: This API defines the structure for a single geocoding search result. It includes the address key format, geocode information, and landmark name if provided. The landmark name has a maximum length of 50 characters. The geocode and address key format are required fields.

ConsigneeName.description: Name. Not relevant for candidate list.

AddressLine.description: Address Line Information. The address level or Intersection information must be returned if provided in the request. The AddressLine will be a combination of up to 3 separate address lines, each separated by a new line character.

PoliticalDivision3.description: Subdivision within a City. e.g., a Barrio.

PostcodeExtendedLow.description: 4 Digit postal code extension. Valid for US only.

CountryCode.description: A country or territory code. Valid values for candidates to be returned are: US-United States (meaning US 50)

GeocodeCandidate_AddressKeyFormat.description: Contains all of the basic information about candidate address.

flattened_text: The `GeocodeCandidate_AddressKeyFormat` object contains basic information about a candidate address. It includes details such as address line, consignee name, country code, state/province, city, subdivision within a city, postal code extension, and postal code. Some fields are required, such as state, address line, postal code, city, and country code. The object is represented in XML as `AddressKeyFormat`.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the origin address, center point of the exchange, center point of the postal code, or center point of the city.

Longitude.description: The longitude of the origin address, center point of the exchange, center point of the postal code, or center point of the city.

GeocodeCandidate_Geocode.description: Geocode is the latitude and longitude of the origin candidate.

flattened_text: This data structure represents a geocode candidate, which includes latitude and longitude coordinates for a specific location. It contains properties for latitude and longitude, both required fields. The latitude and longitude values represent the center point of the origin address, exchange, postal code, or city.

LocationID.description: The location ID that corresponds to the UPS location. Do not expose the Location ID.

OriginOrDestination.description:
OriginOrDestination will returned for FreightWillCallRequestType 1 Postal based and 3 City and/or State based search. 

OriginOrDestination will be 01 for origin facilities and 02 for Destination facilities

PhoneNumber.description:
The UPS locations Phone number. A phone number of the location will be returned.

10 digits allowed for US, otherwise 1..15 digits allowed.

The phone number will be returned as a string.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

FaxNumber.description:
The UPS location's Fax number. A fax number of the location will be returned when available. 
10 digits allowed for US, otherwise 1..15 digits allowed.
The fax number will be returned as string.

EMailAddress.description: Email address of the UPS location. Returned when available.

LocationAttribute.description:
OptionType is a container that indicates the type of the location attribute.

There are 4 types of attributes.

They are: Location, Retail Location, Additional Services and Program Type.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

SpecialInstructions.description:
Walking directions.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

LatestGroundDropOffTime.description:
The latest ground time the users can Drop-off the package at the location to be picked up. The time information is based on the time at the UPS location.

When a user specifies a Drop-off Time and Ground as the Service Type, the locations that have latest Drop-off times equal to or later than the specified Drop-off time and service type are returned.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

LatestAirDropOffTime.description:
The latest airtime the users can Drop-off the package at the location to be picked up. The time information is based on the time at the UPS location.

When a user specifies a Drop-off Time and Air as the Service Type, the locations that have latest Drop-off times equal to or later than the specified Drop-off time and service type are returned.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

AdditionalChargeIndicator.description: Presence or Absence Indicator. If present, Indicates if the UPS location would have an additional charge. ASO locations will require an additional charge.

StandardHoursOfOperation.description: The standard hours of operation of the drop location will be returned when available. The location's time may differ because of holidays.

NonStandardHoursOfOperation.description: The non-standard hours of operation of the drop location. The location's time may differ because of holidays, weekends, or other factors that are beyond the locations control. Seven days preceding a given holiday the Non Standard Hours Of Operation will be returned along with the standard hours of operation if available.

WillCallHoursOfOperation.description: The will call hours of operation of the drop location will be returned when available. The location's time may differ because of holidays.

Number.description: The center number of the drop location if it is The UPS store.

HomePageURL.description: The home page URL of the drop location if it is The UPS store.

Comments.description: Comments returned about the location. Text will be displayed in English or the locale given in the request. If Country Code is FR, and locale passed in the request is "fr_FR" then text will be displayed in French language, else comment will be displayed in English language.

Disclaimer.description:
Textual disclaimer about the drop location.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

LocalizedInstruction.description:
LocalizedInstruction container. Applicable for SearchOptionCode 01, 02, 03.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

PromotionInformation.description:
Container to hold any promotion text for the location. Text will be displayed in English or the locale given in the request.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

DisplayPhoneNumberIndicator.description:
Valid Values: 
0-Do not display phone number
1-Display phone number. 
This indicator will be returned only for the contact type Telephone number. This indicator is used by the clients to determine whether to display the telephone number to the end user.

PromotionalLinkURL.description: Promotional link URL for specific location.

FeaturedRank.description:
Feature Ranking values:
Null or blank - Location is not featured. 
1 - Featured Location ranked number 1.
2 - Featured Location ranked number 2.

WillCallLocationIndicator.description:
Will Call Location Indicator values:
- Y – Signifies a Will Call location that serves the customers address.
- N - Signifies it is not a Will Call location.

Will Call locations are only returned with a \"Y\" indicator if the request included EnhancedSearchOption code 10.

flattened_text: This component defines the structure of search results for drop locations. It includes information like access point details, additional charges, comments, disclaimer, phone number display indicator, operating hours, and more. Some fields are returned as arrays based on the API version used. Certain fields are required, such as geocode, timezone, location ID, and phone number. The component is named "DropLocation" and is of type object.

PhraseID.description:
Contains the name of the IVR file that relates to this drop location. The file is an audio recording of information related to the location.
ONLY FOR IVR.

TextToSpeechIndicator.description:
Indicates to the response recipient that the information has changed, and a new audio file should be produced. 
ONLY FOR IVR.

DropLocation_IVR.description:
Integrated Voice Response information. 
ONLY FOR IVR.

flattened_text: This object, "DropLocation_IVR," contains information for Integrated Voice Response (IVR) systems. It includes properties for the IVR file name (PhraseID) and an indicator for text-to-speech changes (TextToSpeechIndicator). The PhraseID property is limited to 30 characters and is required. The TextToSpeechIndicator property signals when new audio files should be generated.

Latitude.description: The latitude of the location address or the center point of the area code.

Longitude.description: The longitude of the location address or the center point of the area code.

DropLocation_Geocode.description: Geocode is the latitude and longitude of the location address. The Geocode for the location address will be returned when Location is requested in the Request Option.

flattened_text: The `DropLocation_Geocode` object represents the latitude and longitude of a location address. It includes properties for Latitude and Longitude, which are required fields. When requesting location information, the geocode for the address will be returned.

ConsigneeName.description: Name. (Also includes the building name)Return if available.

AddressLine.description: Address Line Information of the UPS location The address level or Intersection information. Only two address lines will be returned. The second line may contain such information as the building name, the suite, and room.

PoliticalDivision3.description: Subdivision within a City. e.g., a Barrio.

PostcodeExtendedLow.description: 4 Digit postal code extension. Valid for US only.

CountryCode.description: A country or territory code. Valid values to be returned are: US-United States (meaning US 50).

DropLocation_AddressKeyFormat.description: Contains all of the basic information about a location, Consignee Name, Building Name, Address Lines, City, State/Province, Postal Code and Country or Terriotry Code.

flattened_text: The `DropLocation_AddressKeyFormat` object contains essential details about a location, including the consignee name, building name, address lines, city, state/province, postal code, and country code. It includes properties like AddressLine, ConsigneeName, CountryCode, PoliticalDivision1, PoliticalDivision2, PoliticalDivision3, PostcodeExtendedLow, and PostcodePrimaryLow. Some properties are required, such as PoliticalDivision1, AddressLine, PostcodePrimaryLow, PoliticalDivision2, and CountryCode. The object is represented as an XML element named `AddressKeyFormat`.

OptionCode.description:
Option code is a container that contains the information of a particular type of Location or retail location or additional service or program type that the drop location contains.

If the OptionType is Location or Retail Location Type there will be one code since each location has only one location type or retail location type.

If the Option type is additional services or program types there can be one or more option codes.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

DropLocation_LocationAttribute.description: LocationAttribute is a container that contains the information about the location's Location Type, Retail Location Type, Additional Services, or Program Type.

flattened_text: The `DropLocation_LocationAttribute` object contains information about the location's type, retail location type, additional services, or program type. It includes properties for `OptionCode` and `OptionType`. The `OptionCode` property holds codes for different types of locations or services. For versions >= v3, `OptionCode` is always returned as an array. In versions v1 and v2, it is returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one. The `OptionType` property refers to the type of option. Both `OptionCode` and `OptionType` are required fields.

Code.description:
Code for Option type. Valid values:
- 01 - Location
- 02 - Retail Location
- 03 - Additional Services
- 04 - Program Type

Description.description: Description for Option type such as Location, RetailLocation, AdditionalServices and ProgramType.

flattened_text: This defines the `LocationAttribute_OptionType` object with two properties: `Code` and `Description`. The `Code` property specifies the type of option (e.g., Location, Retail Location) with a maximum length of 1 character. The `Description` property provides a brief description of the option type with a maximum length of 50 characters. Both properties are required. The object is named `OptionType` in XML.

Category.description:
Only applicabe for OptionType = 03 (Additional Services). Valid values:
- 06 - Non transportation
- 07 - Transportation

Code.description: These codes vary by country or territory. It is strongly recommended that clients contact UPS to retrieve the primary search indicator and the valid Location Types and Service Level Options for each country. Refer to Location Search Option Codes in the Appendix for additional information.

Description.description:
Description is only applicable for Location and Retail Location. The description for Program types and additional service is not provided with Location detail.

It is only provided when the request is for 8, 24, 40, 56-All available additional services or 16, 24, 48, 56-all available Program types.

Name.description: Name will indicate the name of any Additional Services/ Program Types depending on the option code. Text will be displayed in the locale selected.

flattened_text: This section defines the attributes for an option code related to location. It includes properties like category, code, description, name, and transportation pickup schedule. The category specifies if the option is for transportation or non-transportation services. The code varies by country and clients are advised to contact UPS for details. Description and name provide additional information about the location or retail location. The transportation pickup schedule is referenced from another schema. The description and code are required fields.

PickUp.description:
PickUp container contains details of day of week and corresponding pickup times for that service.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

OptionCode_TransportationPickUpSchedule.description: TransportationPickUpSchedule container contains details of Latest Drop Off time/Pickup Time for the transportation services (Ground/Air/Standard/Express/International) of the location.

flattened_text: This object, `OptionCode_TransportationPickUpSchedule`, contains details about the latest drop-off or pickup times for transportation services at a specific location. The `PickUp` property within this object includes information about the day of the week and corresponding pickup times. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, `PickUp` will always be returned as an array. For version v1 requests, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

DayOfWeek.description:
Day of week.
- 1 - Sunday
- 2 - Monday
- 3 - Tuesday
- 4 - Wednesday
- 5 - Thursday
- 6 - Friday
- 7 - Saturday.

flattened_text: This schema defines a transportation pick-up schedule, including the day of the week for the pick-up and details about the pick-up. The day of the week is represented as a string with a maximum length of 1 character. The pick-up details reference another schema called "PickUp_PickUpDetails." Both the day of the week and pick-up details are required fields. The XML element for this object is named "PickUp."

PickUpTime.description: Pickup time of transportation service for a location in military format (HHMM) e.g. 0930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

NoPickUpIndicator.description: Presence or Absence Indicator. If present, Indicates that there is no pickup time for the day.

PickUp_PickUpDetails.description: PickUpDetails container contains either pickup time or NoPickupIndicator. Either PickUpTime or NoPickupIndicator

flattened_text: The `PickUp_PickUpDetails` object contains either a pickup time in military format (e.g., 0930) or a `NoPickUpIndicator` to indicate no pickup for the day. The `NoPickUpIndicator` property is a string that shows absence or presence, while the `PickUpTime` property is a string representing the pickup time. The `PickUpTime` should be exactly 4 characters long. The object is required to have the `NoPickUpIndicator` property and can have a maximum of 1 instance.

Value.description: The straight line distance from the origin to the UPS location. Distance value may include one decimal and followed by one decimal place.

DropLocation_Distance.description: Container for the straight line distance from the origin to the UPS location.

flattened_text: This object represents the straight line distance from the origin to a UPS location. It includes the unit of measurement and the distance value, which can have one decimal place. The object is required to have both the unit of measurement and the distance value.

Code.description:
The distance unit of measurement code. The unit of measurement used in the search request is returned. 

Valid values: MI-Miles or KM-Kilometers

Description.description: May return the description of the unit of measure specified in the request.

Distance_UnitOfMeasurement.description: The unit of measurement the user will see for the distance is based on the user input provided in the search request.

flattened_text: This component defines the unit of measurement for distance displayed to users based on their search input. It includes a code (e.g., MI for Miles, KM for Kilometers) and an optional description. The code is required, and the description is limited to 5-10 characters.

Segment.description: Walking directions, last 50 feet. **NOTE:** For versions >= v3, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1 and v2, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This schema defines a property called "DropLocation_SpecialInstructions" with a maximum of 1 instance. It includes a "Segment" property that provides walking directions for the last 50 feet of a route. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v3, "Segment" will always be returned as an array. For versions v1 and v2, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

CommentType.description:
Container for CommentType Code and Text.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

DropLocation_AdditionalComments.description: Container for Additional Comments about Location.Text will be displayed in the Locale requested.

flattened_text: This object, `DropLocation_AdditionalComments`, holds additional comments about a location. The text is displayed in the requested language. It includes a `CommentType` property that contains a code and text. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, `CommentType` will always be returned as an array. For version v1, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

Code.description: Comment code is 01 for AccessPoint LCO pickup time comment.

Text.description: Access point LCO pickup time comment

flattened_text: This defines a data structure for additional comments, including a comment code and text for an AccessPoint LCO pickup time comment. The comment code is limited to 2 characters, and the text is limited to 255 characters. Both the text and code are required fields.

StandardHours.description:
StandardHours Container.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This component defines the operating hours for a drop location. It includes a property called StandardHours, which may be returned as an array depending on the API version used. The StandardHours property contains details about the operating hours, such as opening and closing times.

HoursType.description:
Hours Type. 

Valid values: 
10-Regular Operating Hours 
11-Will Call Hours
12-Same Day Will Call Hours
14-Customer PickUp
50-Drop Off Hours 
51-Prep Hours

DayOfWeek.description:
Container for the Day of Week.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This component defines the standard operating hours for a service. It includes the day of the week and the type of hours (e.g., regular operating hours, will call hours). The day of the week is returned as an array in versions >= v2 and as a single object in version = v1. The hours type is a string with specific valid values. The component is required to include both the day of the week and the hours type.

OpenHours.description: Open time of a location in military format (HHMM) e.g. 930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

CloseHours.description: Close time of a location in military format (HHMM) e.g. 930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

LatestDropOffHours.description: LatestDropOffHours for Hour Type 50. Latest Drop Off time of a location in military format (HHMM) e.g. 930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

PrepHours.description: PrepHours for Hour Type 51. Prep Hours of a location in military format (HHMM) e.g. 930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

ClosedIndicator.description: Presence absence Indicator. Indicator present means location is closed.

Open24HoursIndicator.description: Presence/ Absence Indicator. Presence denotes  for the given day, if the location is open 24 hours. Absence denotes the location is not open for 24 hours on the given day.

flattened_text: This data structure defines the standard hours for a location on a specific day of the week. It includes information such as the opening and closing times, whether the location is closed, open 24 hours, or has specific drop-off and preparation hours. The day of the week is specified using numbers (1 for Sunday, 2 for Monday, and so on). The format for time is military time (HHMM), except for midnight which is represented as 0.

Last50ftInstruction.description: Holds the additional instructions. Text will be displayed in English or the locale given in the request. The max length of the additional instruction text is 750 characters.

flattened_text:
This component, `DropLocation_LocalizedInstruction`, contains two properties: `Last50ftInstruction` and `Locale`. 

`Last50ftInstruction` holds additional instructions in either English or the specified locale, with a maximum length of 750 characters. 

`Locale` specifies the language locale with a maximum length of 5 characters. 

Both `Locale` and `Last50ftInstruction` are required fields.

Locale.description: Locale (language/ dialect) for the promotion code.

Promotion.description: Promotion text for the given location.

flattened_text: This object, "DropLocation_PromotionInformation," contains information about a promotion at a specific location. It includes properties for "Locale" (language/dialect of the promotion code) and "Promotion" (text for the promotion). The "Locale" property is a string with a length of 5 characters, and the "Promotion" property is a string with a length between 1 and 100 characters. Both properties are required. The object is represented in XML as "PromotionInformation."

HubSortCode.description: Holds the value of the hub sort code or airport code

FreightSortFacilityCode.description: Holds the value of the facility location code.

DropLocation_SortCode.description: This container is only for Freight Will call Search.

flattened_text: This container, "DropLocation_SortCode," is used specifically for Freight Will Call Search. It can contain only one set of data. It includes two properties: "FreightSortFacilityCode" for the facility location code (3 characters long) and "HubSortCode" for the hub sort code or airport code (2 characters long). The container is represented as an object in XML with the name "SortCode."

ServiceOffering.description:
Container for Service offering code.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

DropLocation_ServiceOfferingList.description: Container to hold the list of service offerings at the end point.

flattened_text: This object, `DropLocation_ServiceOfferingList`, contains a list of service offerings available at the endpoint. It can hold a maximum of one service offering. The `ServiceOffering` property is a container for service offering codes. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, this property will always be returned as an array. For requests using version v1, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

PublicAccessPointID.description: The Public Access Point ID associated with UPS access point.

ImageURL.description: Image URL associated with UPS access point.

FacilitySLIC.description: Holds the value of facility SLIC of Access Point Location. Not implemented currently. For future use.

DropLocation_AccessPointInformation.description: Container for UPS Access Point specific parameters.

flattened_text: This object, "DropLocation_AccessPointInformation," contains specific parameters related to UPS Access Points. It includes properties such as AccessPointStatus, Availability, BusinessClassificationList, FacilitySLIC, ImageURL, PrivateNetworkList, and PublicAccessPointID. Each property has its own description and constraints. The object is defined as an XML element named "AccessPointInformation."

BusinessClassification.description:
Container to hold Business classification of UPS access point.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

AccessPointInformation_BusinessClassific.description: Container to hold list for business classification.

flattened_text: This component, `AccessPointInformation_BusinessClassificationList`, is a container that stores business classification information for UPS access points. It can hold a maximum of one item. The `BusinessClassification` property within this container holds the business classification data. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, this property will always be returned as an array. For version v1 requests, it will be returned as an array if there are multiple objects, and as a single object if there is only one.

Code.description: Business Classification code of UPS Access Point. Please refer to appendix D for a list of business classification.

Description.description: Description of business classification.

flattened_text: This API defines a business classification for UPS Access Point locations. It includes a code (up to 3 characters) and a description (up to 35 characters). The code is required and must be unique. The description provides details about the classification.

Code.description:
Valid status values are: 
01-Active-available
06-Suspended
07-Active-unavailable
08-Terminated

Description.description: Description of status code.

flattened_text: This object, AccessPointInformation_AccessPointStatus, represents the status of a UPS AccessPoint. It includes a status code (Code) with specific values and a description of the status (Description). The status code is a 2-character string, and the description is limited to 35 characters. Both properties are required.

PrivateNetwork.description:
Container to hold the private network details.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

AccessPointInformation_PrivateNetworkLis.description: Container to hold the list of private networks.

flattened_text: This component, `AccessPointInformation_PrivateNetworkList`, is used to store information about private networks. It can hold a maximum of one private network. The `PrivateNetwork` property contains details about the private network. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, this property will always be returned as an array. For requests using version v1, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

This API defines a Private Network with two properties: NetworkDescription and NetworkID. NetworkDescription is a string with a maximum length of 50 characters, and NetworkID is a string with a maximum length of 10 characters. Both properties are required. The API allows for only one Private Network to be created.

AccessPointInformation_Availability.description: Container to hold the status of shipping or DRC/DCO availability of a UPS Access Point.

flattened_text: This container holds the status of UPS Access Point availability for shipping or DRC/DCO. It includes properties for DRC availability and shipping availability. The container is limited to holding one instance.

AvailableIndicator.description: Presence or absence indicator. Presence means the location is available for shipping.

flattened_text: This component defines the status of shipping availability. It includes an indicator to show if a location is available for shipping and a reference to reasons for unavailability.

Code.description:
Code for shipping unavailability. Code for DCR/DCO unavailability.

Valid values:
- 01 - Temporarily Unavailable
- 02 - Location Full
- 03 - Unavailable
- 04 - Weather

Description.description: Description for shipping unavailability.

ShippingAvailability_UnavailableReason.description: Container to hold shipping unavailable reason.

flattened_text: This object, ShippingAvailability_UnavailableReason, is used to store reasons for shipping unavailability. It contains two properties: Code (a 2-character code representing the reason) and Description (a text description of the reason). The Code property has specific valid values like Temporarily Unavailable and Weather. The object requires both Description and Code properties to be present.

AvailableIndicator.description: Presence or absence indicator. Presence means the location is available for DCR/DCO.

flattened_text: This component, Availability_DCRAvailability, represents the status of DCR/DCO availability. It includes two properties: AvailableIndicator, which indicates if the location is available for DCR/DCO, and UnavailableReason, which provides a reference to a specific schema. The component is an object with an XML name of DCRAvailability.

Code.description:
Code for DCR/DCO unavailability. Valid values: 
01-Temporarily Unavailable 
02-Location Full
03-Unavailable
04-Weather

Description.description: Description for DCR/ DCO unavailability.

DCRAvailability_UnavailableReason.description: Container to hold shipping unavailable reason.

flattened_text: This data structure is used to store reasons why a delivery or collection request is unavailable. It includes a code (with specific values like "Temporarily Unavailable" or "Weather") and a description of the unavailability reason. The code and description are required fields, and the structure is named "UnavailableReason" in XML.

NonSecureURL.description: Non Secure URL for Location Image.

flattened_text: This defines a data structure called "DropLocation_LocationImage" that represents a location image. It contains two properties: "NonSecureURL" for a non-secure image URL and "SecureURL" for a secure image URL. Only one instance of this data structure is allowed.

This defines an object called SearchResults_AvailableLocationAttributes with properties OptionCode and OptionType. Both properties are required. The object is used to represent available location attributes in search results.

Code.description: Code for Option type.

Description.description: Description for Option type such as RetailLocation, AdditionalServices and ProgramType.

AvailableLocationAttributes_OptionType.description: OptionType is a container that indicates the type of the location attribute that are available. For example if the Option Type is RetailLocation the list of all available retail locations will be returned in 1 or many corresponding OptionCodes.

flattened_text: This object defines the type of location attributes available. For example, if the type is "RetailLocation," a list of retail locations will be returned with corresponding codes. It includes properties for code and description, with description being required. The object is named "OptionType."

AvailableLocationAttributes_OptionCode.description: **NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

flattened_text: This element, AvailableLocationAttributes_OptionCode, will always be returned as an array for versions equal to or greater than v2. For requests using version v1, it will be returned as an array if there is more than one object, and as a single object if there is only one.

Code.description: The valid list of codes and description for Retail Locations or Additional Services or Pro-gram Types that are currently available in the database. This can be obtained by a separate type of request (Request Option 8, 16, 24, 32, 40, 48 and 56).

Description.description: Description is only applicable for Program types and Additional Services. It is not provided with Location detail. It is only provided when the request is for All available additional ser-vices or all available Program types. Text will be displayed in the locale requested.

Name.description: Name will indicate the name of Location/Retail Location or Additional Services or Program Types depending on the option code. Text will be displayed in the locale requested.

AvailableLocationAttributes_OptionCodeEl.description: Option code is a container that contains the information of a particular retail location type or additional service or program type that is available currently. One or more of this container will be returned to give all the available codes for Retail Type or Additional Services or Program Type.

flattened_text: This data structure represents information about available location attributes, such as retail location types or additional services. It includes details like category, code, description, name, and transportation pickup schedule. The description and code are required fields, with the description specifically for program types and additional services. The information can be obtained through specific types of requests.

PickUp.description:
Container to hold information regarding pickup day of the week and details.

**NOTE:** For versions >= v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For requests using version = v1, this element will be returned as an array if there is more than one object and a single object if there is only 1.

AvailableLocationAttributesOptionCode_Tr.description: Container to hold information regarding pickup details for each day of the week.

flattened_text: This section defines the structure for transportation pickup schedules. It includes details for each day of the week. The "PickUp" property holds information about the pickup day and related details. Note that for versions equal to or greater than v2, this element will always be returned as an array. For version v1 requests, it will be returned as an array if there are multiple objects, and as a single object if there is only one.

DayOfWeek.description:
Day of the week for scheduled pickup. Valid values are:
- 1 - Sunday
- 2 - Monday
- 3 - Tuesday
- 4 - Wednesday
- 5 - Thursday
- 6 - Friday
- 7 - Saturday.

flattened_text: This schema defines the attributes for scheduling transportation pickups at available locations. It includes the day of the week for the pickup schedule (1-7 for Sunday to Saturday) and references additional pickup details. The `DayOfWeek` property is required and must be a single character string. The schema is represented as an object in XML with the name "PickUp."

PickUpTime.description: Time of pickup in military format (HHMM) e.g. 0930, 1700, 1845 etc. with exception for midnight. For midnight the time will be returned as 0.

NoPickUpIndicator.description:
Indicates whether or not there is a pickup time for the specified day of the week. Valid values:
- True-there is a pickup time
- False-there is not a pickup time.

AvailableLocationAttributes_PickUp_PickU.description: Container to hold information regarding pickup time and pickup availability indicator.

flattened_text: This section defines attributes related to pickup availability. It includes details about whether there is a pickup time on a specific day of the week and the time of pickup in military format (HHMM). The "NoPickUpIndicator" property indicates if there is a pickup time, while "PickUpTime" specifies the time in HHMM format, except for midnight which is represented as 0.
